00:28:45.505 --> 00:28:52.476
MATT: I'm going to go ahead and have... let's see.
Scanlan, roll a history check? And if you could

00:28:52.476 --> 00:28:54.391
roll an intelligence check.

00:28:54.391 --> 00:28:56.000
MARISHA: Why is it always intelligence?

00:28:56.000 --> 00:28:58.170
SAM: I've got a 15 history.

00:28:58.170 --> 00:29:00.377
MARISHA: Oh my god. I rolled a natural one.

00:29:00.377 --> 00:29:03.921
MATT: You know it's in the Ozmit Sea, but you've
never been there, you don't know where it is, you

00:29:03.921 --> 00:29:06.393
have no idea what the actual space is there.

00:29:06.393 --> 00:29:08.399
MARISHA: We don't communicate.

00:29:08.399 --> 00:29:12.836
MATT: You. Island of glass, and after thinking
about it hard, you're like, of course, it's the

00:29:12.836 --> 00:29:14.666
Isle of Glintshore.

00:29:14.666 --> 00:29:16.072
LAURA: Of course.

00:29:16.072 --> 00:29:28.296
MATT: It's part of a cluster of islands. You don't
know quite where it is, but you know of it. That's

00:29:28.296 --> 00:29:33.050
about all the information you have on it at the
moment. You don't know how far, the specific

00:29:33.050 --> 00:29:34.880
direction really.

00:29:34.880 --> 00:29:39.416
SAM: Well, it doesn't look like we can just
magically get to her.

00:29:39.416 --> 00:29:41.063
TRAVIS: Ooh, ooh.

00:29:41.063 --> 00:29:42.440
LAURA: Yes, Grog?

00:29:42.440 --> 00:29:45.579
TRAVIS: Aren't you two dweebs always wanting to
steal an airship?

00:29:45.579 --> 00:29:46.605
SAM and TALIESIN: Yes.

00:29:46.605 --> 00:29:47.640
TRAVIS: Don't they have one here?

00:29:47.640 --> 00:29:48.829
SAM and TALIESIN: Yes.

00:29:48.829 --> 00:29:52.129
TRAVIS: So... Do I have to say the third thing, or
are you going to get there?

00:29:52.129 --> 00:29:55.643
SAM: I would like to steal that airship, but even
then, though, it would take us a week.

00:29:55.643 --> 00:29:58.931
TALIESIN: It would take way too much time. We are
on a schedule.

00:29:58.931 --> 00:30:02.017
TRAVIS: What? Road trip, bitches. Come on. We got
to like, you know--

00:30:02.017 --> 00:30:08.326
SAM: Okay, let's game this out. What's the
worse-case scenario? She has one Vestige. She may

00:30:08.326 --> 00:30:09.446
have two.

00:30:09.446 --> 00:30:10.985
LIAM: What's left after that?

00:30:10.985 --> 00:30:13.548
MARISHA: I mean, we could let her do the hard work
for us.

00:30:13.548 --> 00:30:20.339
LIAM: She has the cloak, that we know of. She's on
top of the dagger almost.

00:30:20.339 --> 00:30:27.607
SAM: The Spire of Conflux, in the Abyssal Plane.
And the Plate of Dawnmartyr in the Elemental Plane

00:30:27.607 --> 00:30:31.386
of Fire. I mean, those are going to be super hard
to find, even for her.

00:30:31.386 --> 00:30:34.917
LIAM: I know, but if we're in an arms race and
she's on top of another, maybe we should head to

00:30:34.917 --> 00:30:37.394
the next that's out of her reach now.

00:30:37.394 --> 00:30:38.497
TRAVIS: That makes sense.

00:30:38.497 --> 00:30:42.774
MARISHA: The staff is in the plane of the Abyss.

00:30:42.774 --> 00:30:45.026
LAURA: That's a very scary place.

00:30:45.026 --> 00:30:49.767
TRAVIS: The only problem with that is she only has
one now and if she has two, she might be a bit

00:30:49.767 --> 00:30:50.649
harder--

00:30:50.649 --> 00:30:54.315
LAURA: Especially, imagine if one of us was
wearing all of the Vestiges.

00:30:54.315 --> 00:30:58.134
SAM: She has people working for her, clearly.

00:30:58.134 --> 00:31:00.159
LAURA: She's not going to give it up.

00:31:00.159 --> 00:31:03.384
SAM: No, but I mean it won't be her alone.

00:31:03.384 --> 00:31:06.906
LIAM: And we're not going to get there in time to
stop her from getting that dagger.

00:31:06.906 --> 00:31:10.313
TALIESIN: But we might be able to take them from
her and perhaps even finally put her down before

00:31:10.313 --> 00:31:13.114
she puts more of those bloody things into the
world.

00:31:13.114 --> 00:31:15.117
MARISHA: Can I also ask another question, Percy?

00:31:15.117 --> 00:31:16.314
TALIESIN: Sure.

00:31:16.314 --> 00:31:20.021
MARISHA: Why does she want these Vestiges in the
first place? I have a feeling she doesn't want to

00:31:20.021 --> 00:31:21.118
fight dragons.

00:31:21.118 --> 00:31:24.107
SAM: She might want to join up with the dragons.

00:31:24.107 --> 00:31:26.347
MARISHA: Do you know?

00:31:26.347 --> 00:31:27.385
TALIESIN: I don't--

00:31:27.385 --> 00:31:30.026
LIAM: I mean, there's many reasons to amass
power.

00:31:30.026 --> 00:31:34.711
LAURA: Could she be the one letting the dragons
know about-- could she be the spy?

00:31:34.711 --> 00:31:43.601
TALIESIN: I spent less than a week in her company
in my life. I know very little about her other

00:31:43.601 --> 00:31:53.483
than-- I spent a week in her company and I spent I
don't know how much time trying to track her down

00:31:53.483 --> 00:32:02.575
and all I really know is she's very smart and she
is the worst person I've ever met.

00:32:02.575 --> 00:32:09.493
MARISHA: Why would you say that exactly? Because
we've met a lot of terrible people.

00:32:09.493 --> 00:32:10.651
SAM: Kevdak.

00:32:10.651 --> 00:32:11.829
TALIESIN: People don't frighten me.

00:32:11.829 --> 00:32:13.438
MARISHA: Their dad.

00:32:13.438 --> 00:32:14.993
TALIESIN: He doesn't frighten me.

00:32:14.993 --> 00:32:19.980
MARISHA: Saundor was pretty shitty. Clarota.

00:32:19.980 --> 00:32:24.235
SAM: Well, let's not rank the bad people we've
met.

00:32:24.235 --> 00:32:34.390
TALIESIN: I don't even know if she wants anything.
Maybe she wants nothing.

00:32:34.390 --> 00:32:38.193
TRAVIS: Are you genuinely afraid of her?

00:32:38.193 --> 00:32:40.130
TALIESIN: Yes, very much so.

00:32:40.130 --> 00:32:41.775
TRAVIS: Oh.

00:32:41.775 --> 00:32:45.038
LAURA: Fuck, why didn't we kill her when we had
her in our--

00:32:45.038 --> 00:32:47.419
SAM: She got away. We tried.

00:32:47.419 --> 00:32:57.750
TALIESIN: I made a terrible trade. I made the
wrong trade and I made a terrible decision. I know that.

00:32:57.750 --> 00:33:02.080
(laughter)

00:33:02.080 --> 00:33:07.650
TALIESIN: The table on the left is completely
incapable--

00:33:07.650 --> 00:33:10.888
TRAVIS: The player on your right--

00:33:10.888 --> 00:33:13.552
LIAM: A little mug interference.

00:33:13.552 --> 00:33:22.690
TALIESIN: Let me get this enchantment off my gun.
Let's find somebody who can pull it off and put it

00:33:22.690 --> 00:33:28.660
onto something else and leave it here. And then
let's run screaming to this island and see if we

00:33:28.660 --> 00:33:36.430
can catch her and if she's not there, we spend 24
hours where I will recount every desperate attempt

00:33:36.430 --> 00:33:41.669
I have made to try and kill her in the last few
years of my life and then we head back and deal

00:33:41.669 --> 00:33:45.006
with the other monstrosities that are waiting for
us back home.

00:33:45.006 --> 00:33:47.093
SAM: I don't know that we'll get there in time.

00:33:47.093 --> 00:33:48.755
LIAM: How do we get there?

00:33:48.755 --> 00:33:52.958
MARISHA: We had to fly across the Ozmit Sea to get
to Marquet.

00:33:52.958 --> 00:34:00.096
MATT: It took you about a week to get to
Vasselheim via skyship from Emon and that's

00:34:00.096 --> 00:34:08.951
normally a two-and-a-half week journey by boat.
You guys got to Marquet via your Transport Via

00:34:08.951 --> 00:34:12.302
Plants. Oh no, sorry, you got to Marquet via the
Teleportation Circle that--

00:34:12.302 --> 00:34:14.181
MARISHA: Gilmore made for us.

00:34:14.181 --> 00:34:16.363
LAURA: Are we by the ocean at all?

00:34:16.363 --> 00:34:18.345
MARISHA: But the ocean's above us, right?

00:34:18.345 --> 00:34:23.848
MATT: You have a mountain range that is at the
top, the northern part of the desert, probably a

00:34:23.848 --> 00:34:29.590
day and a half of foot travel and the mountain
range, you're not sure how big that is. From what

00:34:29.590 --> 00:34:35.420
you know of loose geography-- Scanlan, you
probably know this better than anybody-- that

00:34:35.420 --> 00:34:42.131
Ank'Harel and this part of the desert is not too
far from the northern shore of Marquet, compared

00:34:42.131 --> 00:34:50.892
to the rest of it. The entire continent is like a
big U and this is the Ozmit Sea up here. This is

00:34:50.892 --> 00:34:53.754
Marquet. Ank'Harel's right there and then this is
the ocean.

00:34:53.754 --> 00:34:56.551
LAURA: Can Misty Step travel faster than a boat?

00:34:56.551 --> 00:35:02.051
MATT: Of an ocean boat? Yes, probably twice as
fast.

00:35:02.051 --> 00:35:05.869
LAURA: So if it took her a week to get where she
is now, we could probably get there--

00:35:05.869 --> 00:35:09.266
TALIESIN: In three days. But where do you rest in
the--

00:35:09.266 --> 00:35:11.652
SAM: Yes. We'd have to rest in order to do Misty
Step--

00:35:11.652 --> 00:35:15.413
LIAM: If your magic runs out while we're flying
over the ocean, what happens, we drown?

00:35:15.413 --> 00:35:18.393
LAURA: We don't necessarily drown immediately.

00:35:18.393 --> 00:35:21.473
TALIESIN: Also, if we can find a way to teleport
to the island, if there's a way that we can.

00:35:21.473 --> 00:35:23.360
LIAM: But how?

00:35:23.360 --> 00:35:24.963
SAM: We have one teleportation circle.

00:35:24.963 --> 00:35:26.992
MARISHA: I mean, I could teleport us--

00:35:26.992 --> 00:35:28.498
LIAM: You have to have a circle to a circle.

00:35:28.498 --> 00:35:36.193
MARISHA: I could teleport us to the edge of the
continent, we could sleep, and then Misty Step

00:35:36.193 --> 00:35:37.899
lasts eight hours.

00:35:37.899 --> 00:35:39.341
MATT: Yeah. Wind Walk, you mean?

00:35:39.341 --> 00:35:40.606
MARISHA: Wind Walk, whatever.

00:35:40.606 --> 00:35:43.408
MATT: It's a different spell, but yeah. It's 30
feet.

00:35:43.408 --> 00:35:44.627
LIAM: That wouldn't do it.

00:35:44.627 --> 00:35:45.584
MATT: Little different.

00:35:45.584 --> 00:35:46.926
MARISHA: Wind Walk lasts eight hours.

00:35:46.926 --> 00:35:58.417
SAM: She's on a boat. She's not on a magic boat.
She can't magically get back to the shore without

00:35:58.417 --> 00:36:04.129
sailing there. If we sail out on an airship or a
boat--

00:36:04.129 --> 00:36:05.912
LAURA: We could bomb her!

00:36:05.912 --> 00:36:10.431
SAM: Well yes! She's slow moving, she's on a boat,
it'll take her days to get wherever she's going,

00:36:10.431 --> 00:36:16.117
we need to find her, and we can keep scrying on
the airship, and catch up to her slowly, she's a

00:36:16.117 --> 00:36:18.051
slow moving target, even after she--

00:36:18.051 --> 00:36:19.837
LIAM: I like that you're assuming we'll have an
airship.

00:36:19.837 --> 00:36:23.043
SAM: We don't right now, but we will soon.

00:36:23.043 --> 00:36:25.641
MARISHA: It could take us a while to even get the
airship.

00:36:25.641 --> 00:36:29.478
SAM: Nope. One day. Me and Percy. Maybe two
hours.

00:36:29.478 --> 00:36:35.135
TRAVIS: I actually agree with that strategy. It is
a bit like fish in a barrel because she is limited

00:36:35.135 --> 00:36:36.401
by her speed.

00:36:36.401 --> 00:36:38.283
LAURA: Will we be able to find her in the middle
of the ocean?

00:36:38.283 --> 00:36:39.806
SAM: We can keep scrying from the airship.

00:36:39.806 --> 00:36:40.885
LIAM: That's true.

00:36:40.885 --> 00:36:42.020
TALIESIN: We can keep scrying.

00:36:42.020 --> 00:36:46.962
TALIESIN: The first thing we have to do is remove
this enchantment and I'm very open to ideas on how

00:36:46.962 --> 00:36:47.864
to do that.

00:36:47.864 --> 00:36:52.476
TRAVIS: Wait, but play it out. How do we see where
she is in comparison to a giant body of water?

00:36:52.476 --> 00:36:56.234
SAM: Well, we use what sailors do.

00:36:56.234 --> 00:36:57.634
TRAVIS: Look up at the stars?

00:36:57.634 --> 00:37:00.427
SAM: Up at the stars, right? We scry at night.

00:37:00.427 --> 00:37:03.789
TRAVIS: We're looking at her, right, not up, can
we, like, go like that--

00:37:03.789 --> 00:37:05.178
LAURA: No, you can scry up, yeah.

00:37:05.178 --> 00:37:07.550
MATT: Focused around the target of the scrying.

00:37:07.550 --> 00:37:09.947
LIAM: Are either of you gentlemen smart enough to
do that?

00:37:09.947 --> 00:37:12.123
MARISHA: We can't tilt the camera up a little
bit?

00:37:12.123 --> 00:37:17.053
MATT: No. You can, but you'll see a blurred
skyline--

00:37:17.053 --> 00:37:22.384
SAM: We can listen for clues. Maybe the crew
members will shout out a, "Oh, we're at longitude

00:37:22.384 --> 00:37:25.865
"blah blah blah latitude blah blah blah!"

00:37:25.865 --> 00:37:30.018
MATT: For you, when you scry on something, imagine
it, like, super high depth of field, so like what

00:37:30.018 --> 00:37:34.579
you're looking at is super in-focus and most
everything else is very blurred and out of focus.

00:37:34.579 --> 00:37:42.418
SAM: Okay, wait, to play this out a bit more: we
know where she's going. We know where Glintshore

00:37:42.418 --> 00:37:44.393
is roughly if we got a local--

00:37:44.393 --> 00:37:45.483
LIAM: Do you know where that island is?

00:37:45.483 --> 00:37:49.789
SAM: Well we can find a local who does. A sailor
or something who can help us navigate our way there.

00:37:49.789 --> 00:37:51.410
LAURA: Maybe somebody in an airship.

00:37:51.410 --> 00:37:55.365
TRAVIS: We could, but we might just be chasing, as
long as we're all right with that. We'll just be

00:37:55.365 --> 00:37:56.609
chasing.

00:37:56.609 --> 00:37:59.482
LAURA: We'll keep scrying until we see if she's
found it.

00:37:59.482 --> 00:38:00.764
TALIESIN: Until we see a tree.

00:38:00.764 --> 00:38:05.010
TRAVIS: Vax does have a point, though. If we're
just chasing, we could get the jump on other ones.

00:38:05.010 --> 00:38:09.671
TALIESIN: Here's the terrifying notion: if you see
a tree in any of your scries, can you teleport to it?

00:38:09.671 --> 00:38:10.880
MARISHA: Yes, I can.

00:38:10.880 --> 00:38:12.684
TALIESIN: So as long as she gets next to a tree--

00:38:12.684 --> 00:38:14.449
SAM: I don't think she's getting next to a tree.

00:38:14.449 --> 00:38:15.767
MARISHA: She's in the middle of the ocean.

00:38:15.767 --> 00:38:18.759
TALIESIN: Once she's on the island, if the island
has a tree...

00:38:18.759 --> 00:38:20.583
LAURA and LIAM: It's possible.

00:38:20.583 --> 00:38:24.257
SAM: It was near. It was near the island of
glass.

00:38:24.257 --> 00:38:26.996
TALIESIN: We're going to be looking for her.
That's where I would set up shop if I were--

00:38:26.996 --> 00:38:31.349
LIAM: I mean, Percival is correct, the first thing
we have to do is get that gun unfucked, but then

00:38:31.349 --> 00:38:35.397
after we have to decide if we are chasing her
down-- and it seems 50-50 to me, not impossible,

00:38:35.397 --> 00:38:39.872
but not a sure thing at all-- or do we head to the
next Vestige to keep it out of her hands?

00:38:39.872 --> 00:38:41.299
LAURA: Into the Plane of Abyss?

00:38:41.299 --> 00:38:44.073
LIAM: Well isn't that where we have to go anyway?

00:38:44.073 --> 00:38:47.507
TRAVIS: Let's get the gun unfucked, and we'll
simmer on it.

00:38:47.507 --> 00:38:55.450
SAM: Wait, before we get the gun unfucked, is
there any use to it being fucked? Like, can we

00:38:55.450 --> 00:39:01.126
have play-acting conversations around it like "Oh,
this is where we should go next, hope you're

00:39:01.126 --> 00:39:01.949
"listening!"

00:39:01.949 --> 00:39:06.163
TALIESIN: That is deeply assuming that it actually
conveys sound, which it may not.

00:39:06.163 --> 00:39:10.210
MARISHA: Yeah, we have no idea what it actually
is, let's go get it.

00:39:10.210 --> 00:39:14.870
TALIESIN: Yeah, we're going to have to move that
enchantment onto something else.

00:39:14.870 --> 00:39:18.352
SAM: We can go to that place where-- back to the
asshole.

00:39:18.352 --> 00:39:20.402
TALIESIN: I know what he wants, no.

00:39:20.402 --> 00:39:21.562
SAM: What does he want?

00:39:21.562 --> 00:39:22.599
LAURA: He wants whitestone.

00:39:22.599 --> 00:39:23.837
SAM: So give him whitestone.

00:39:23.837 --> 00:39:24.729
TALIESIN: Absolutely not.

00:39:24.729 --> 00:39:28.455
MARISHA: He's going to take one really close look
at that gun and see a lot of whitestone in it.

00:39:28.455 --> 00:39:30.864
TRAVIS: I got two chunks of whitestone in the Bag
of Holding.

00:39:30.864 --> 00:39:34.448
TALIESIN: He wants the green gems, and I'm not
prepared to make that deal.

00:39:34.448 --> 00:39:40.942
SAM: We can make him a fake one and give it to him
for one favor. We can make a fake gem, how hard is that?

00:39:40.942 --> 00:39:42.076
LAURA: He's going to know.

00:39:42.076 --> 00:39:44.426
TRAVIS: I got a bunch of gems in the Bag of
Holding.

00:39:44.426 --> 00:39:46.837
TALIESIN: It's not going to work.

00:39:46.837 --> 00:39:48.611
LAURA: Do you have green gems?

00:39:48.611 --> 00:39:50.092
TRAVIS: Gems, lots of gems.

00:39:50.092 --> 00:39:52.180
LAURA: No, but the green gems from Whitestone?

00:39:52.180 --> 00:39:59.071
LIAM: Whitestone is much further away from the
Ozmit Sea than where we are now, right?

00:39:59.071 --> 00:40:02.808
MATT: Whitestone is &lt;i&gt;much&lt;/i&gt; further away, yes.

00:40:02.808 --> 00:40:04.652
LIAM: Way, way, other side of the continent
right?

00:40:04.652 --> 00:40:07.623
MATT: Across a vast ocean, and then across the
continent.

00:40:07.623 --> 00:40:18.149
SAM: One thing that occurred to me, that may not
help us at all. Mistress Asharru, the dead girl:

00:40:18.149 --> 00:40:23.416
she was part of an organization?

00:40:23.416 --> 00:40:24.561
TALIESIN: Yes.

00:40:24.561 --> 00:40:27.051
SAM: Maybe they would want to help us because of
revenge?

00:40:27.051 --> 00:40:30.731
TALIESIN: Here's the question, and this is what
I've been thinking about sitting here for the last

00:40:30.731 --> 00:40:38.114
few minutes, is either way this is terrible:
either we don't tell them and leave town and

00:40:38.114 --> 00:40:43.662
eventually they find her and she's got strange
holes in her from some strange thing that could

00:40:43.662 --> 00:40:49.846
possibly be a thing that a man with white hair who
breezed through town a week ago was holding, or we

00:40:49.846 --> 00:40:56.859
go and tell them, and I cannot believe this is
about to come out of my mouth, that it wasn't me,

00:40:56.859 --> 00:41:00.077
it was a one armed woman, who had--

00:41:00.077 --> 00:41:01.572
SAM: A fugitive?

00:41:01.572 --> 00:41:08.271
TALIESIN: An identical, thank you, weapon, of this
one of a kind weapon that no one bloody saw.

00:41:08.271 --> 00:41:13.174
LAURA: No, but here's the thing, maybe somebody
did see her.

00:41:13.174 --> 00:41:17.119
TALIESIN: Maybe somebody did see her, and maybe
they'll know where to get the gun.

00:41:17.119 --> 00:41:23.978
MARISHA: Even if they did see her, we know she
knows how to alter her appearance. Also, no

00:41:23.978 --> 00:41:29.182
offense Percy, but I feel like we need to be
careful on who you expose that gun to, from here

00:41:29.182 --> 00:41:30.051
on out.

00:41:30.051 --> 00:41:31.402
TALIESIN: I am keenly aware.

00:41:31.402 --> 00:41:37.160
MARISHA: Not only, one, for people who might think
you're the culprit, but two, for people who are

00:41:37.160 --> 00:41:39.445
going to want to rip you off again.

00:41:39.445 --> 00:41:45.318
TALIESIN: She's the only person who's ever gotten
a good look at it. She's the only one.

00:41:45.318 --> 00:41:54.263
SAM: So other than chasing her, going for the next
Vestige on the list, the third option is wish her

00:41:54.263 --> 00:41:58.965
good luck and continue on with our mission
ignoring the fact that she exists.

00:41:58.965 --> 00:42:00.632
MARISHA: Maybe she'll die in the Ozmit Sea.

00:42:00.632 --> 00:42:02.968
TALIESIN: She won't.

00:42:02.968 --> 00:42:04.791
LIAM: How long's it been since we left Draconia?

00:42:04.791 --> 00:42:10.933
MATT: Five days?

00:42:10.933 --> 00:42:12.329
LAURA: Not five days?!

00:42:12.329 --> 00:42:18.907
MATT: From your travel from Draconia, back to
Whitestone, to resting in Whitestone, heading from

00:42:18.907 --> 00:42:26.064
there to the southern city, then travelling from
there to Ank'Harel, then you've had--

00:42:26.064 --> 00:42:30.914
TALIESIN: A lot of that was instantaneous. We did
camp three or four days--

00:42:30.914 --> 00:42:34.916
MATT: Well no, yeah about four or five days
because you travelled then from Whitestone to

00:42:34.916 --> 00:42:40.981
south of Ank'Harel, then you wind walked to
Ank'Harel, but then camped outside of Ank'Harel,

00:42:40.981 --> 00:42:45.675
because the time you got there was night, then you
made it into the city, then you stayed for the

00:42:45.675 --> 00:42:50.295
evening, you slept again and the next night you
went ahead and went into the casino, then slept

00:42:50.295 --> 00:42:52.604
the night there, so yeah, it's been about five
days.

00:42:52.604 --> 00:42:58.750
MARISHA: Is it like a flying from east to west
thing where we gain back a day when we go back?

00:42:58.750 --> 00:43:00.108
MATT: No.

00:43:00.108 --> 00:43:02.906
LAURA: But we don't have to fly, we just have to
teleport there.

00:43:02.906 --> 00:43:04.552
TALIESIN: So long as we teleport we're fine.

00:43:04.552 --> 00:43:12.008
LAURA: But we don't have a plan. We have five days
to figure out how to fucking kill a dragon. Oh Jesus.

00:43:12.008 --> 00:43:16.563
MARISHA: And we didn't get the Vestige we came
here for, so--

00:43:16.563 --> 00:43:18.302
TALIESIN: No we did not, in fact, it's worse.

00:43:18.302 --> 00:43:23.397
MATT: Well two weeks was the agreement, so you
have more than five. Nine.

00:43:23.397 --> 00:43:25.816
LIAM: You can do anything in nine days.

00:43:25.816 --> 00:43:28.776
TRAVIS: We don't even have to keep the agreement,
come on.

00:43:28.776 --> 00:43:33.236
LAURA: Potentially.

00:43:33.236 --> 00:43:39.247
TRAVIS: Just saying. We getting the gun un-fucked
or what?

00:43:39.247 --> 00:43:41.278
TALIESIN: Let's go downstairs and talk to her
employer.

00:43:41.278 --> 00:43:42.391
LAURA: Treev?

00:43:42.391 --> 00:43:44.881
MATT: Treev, yes. All right.

00:43:44.881 --> 00:43:47.047
TALIESIN: I'm going to leave the gun upstairs
still.

00:43:47.047 --> 00:43:52.026
MARISHA: Wait, what? Don't we need it to tap the
gun to--

00:43:52.026 --> 00:43:53.821
SAM: Well we got to find out who's going to
un-fuck it.

00:43:53.821 --> 00:43:56.120
LAURA: Is Treev downstairs?

00:43:56.120 --> 00:44:03.143
MATT: All right, you head down into the tavern,
and at this time of day it's a little empty, a

00:44:03.143 --> 00:44:09.014
little sparse, maybe like, four patrons. Two in
discussions, one that's deep in the cups and one

00:44:09.014 --> 00:44:14.045
in the midst of going through paperwork and in the
far back you see Treev once again has his heavy

00:44:14.045 --> 00:44:17.802
spectacles on and is currently looking through
that same book he was before, doesn't seem to pay

00:44:17.802 --> 00:44:19.574
any mind to you until you approach him.

00:44:19.574 --> 00:44:21.242
LAURA: Treev?

00:44:21.242 --> 00:44:25.977
MATT: "Oh, aye, good to see you. What can I do for
you?"

00:44:25.977 --> 00:44:29.656
LAURA: We need to talk to you. It's rather
urgent.

00:44:29.656 --> 00:44:36.908
MATT: "Then talk to me." Puts his book away,
glasses on it, leans forward.

00:44:36.908 --> 00:44:47.158
TALIESIN: There's been a complication. The
mistress is-- she's been assassinated.

00:44:47.158 --> 00:44:53.337
MARISHA: We hadn't heard anything in these past
few days, we decided to pay her a call.

00:44:53.337 --> 00:45:02.300
MATT: He leans forward a little bit on the bar.
Vex, Vax and Keyleth. You notice that the hooded

00:45:02.300 --> 00:45:05.702
figure, that originally delivered the note, is
back in the far corner, where it was and it seems

00:45:05.702 --> 00:45:09.033
to have stepped a couple inches out of the shadows as
well, paying very close attention to this

00:45:09.033 --> 00:45:10.418
conversation.

00:45:10.418 --> 00:45:12.704
TALIESIN: Did we bring the note with us? Good.

00:45:12.704 --> 00:45:18.079
MATT: Goes, "So you are saying that the mistress
was assassinated?"

00:45:18.079 --> 00:45:19.689
TALIESIN: And the cloak stolen.

00:45:19.689 --> 00:45:21.488
MATT: "Cloak?"

00:45:21.488 --> 00:45:23.381
TALIESIN: The cloak she wore.

00:45:23.381 --> 00:45:27.036
MATT: "And you know this how?"

00:45:27.036 --> 00:45:28.757
LAURA: We found her body.

00:45:28.757 --> 00:45:31.681
MATT: "Where?"

00:45:31.681 --> 00:45:33.155
LAURA: In her home.

00:45:33.155 --> 00:45:34.816
SCANLAN: Don't think that was her home.

00:45:34.816 --> 00:45:36.252
MARISHA: In her hideout.

00:45:36.252 --> 00:45:39.317
TALIESIN: In her room beneath the house.

00:45:39.317 --> 00:45:41.583
MATT: "How do you know where she lived?"

00:45:41.583 --> 00:45:51.972
TALIESIN: We are very clever. But not clever
enough to stop this. This appears to have happened

00:45:51.972 --> 00:45:56.191
possibly before we even-- we don't know when it
happened. It happened a while ago.

00:45:56.191 --> 00:45:58.107
LAURA: About a week ago. I think.

00:45:58.107 --> 00:46:00.413
MATT: Percy, make a persuasion check.

00:46:00.413 --> 00:46:10.789
TALIESIN: 13.

00:46:10.789 --> 00:46:19.499
MATT: Okay. Treev puts one hand out on the bar,
he's got a big heavy coin in it, he's nervously

00:46:19.499 --> 00:46:22.618
tapping it. (few knocks on wood)

00:46:22.618 --> 00:46:26.222
TALIESIN: We think we know who did it. In fact, we
are near positive we know who did it.

00:46:26.222 --> 00:46:31.105
MATT: You hear (door closing) as the door of the
tavern closes and all the patrons you saw are now

00:46:31.105 --> 00:46:36.924
standing up completely sober and they're all
taking a circle to the outside of your group. He's

00:46:36.924 --> 00:46:45.920
leaning forward, going, "All right, so you're
clever. You came looking for the mistress, she

00:46:45.920 --> 00:46:48.525
"suddenly winds up dead. You found her body."

00:46:48.525 --> 00:46:51.463
TALIESIN: And we tell you this as opposed to
leaving.

00:46:51.463 --> 00:46:53.595
LAURA: We had nothing to do with it. We could've
left town.

00:46:53.595 --> 00:46:57.192
MARISHA: Clearly we know how this looks, which is
why we came to you first.

00:46:57.192 --> 00:46:59.361
TALIESIN: We are desperate in finding who did
this.

00:46:59.361 --> 00:47:01.257
LIAM: What's the hooded figure doing right now?

00:47:01.257 --> 00:47:07.577
MATT: Still sitting in the back of that shadowed
alcove between a bunch of barrels that are stacked

00:47:07.577 --> 00:47:09.170
and part of the bar side.

00:47:09.170 --> 00:47:10.718
LIAM: I'm going to keep focused there.

00:47:10.718 --> 00:47:11.918
TRAVIS: Is he still tapping the coin?

00:47:11.918 --> 00:47:13.172
MATT: No, the coin tapping has stopped.

00:47:13.172 --> 00:47:17.991
MARISHA: And what are the people around us doing?
Are they, like, drawing their weapons?

00:47:17.991 --> 00:47:18.901
MATT: No.

00:47:18.901 --> 00:47:20.102
MARISHA: Do they seem armed?

00:47:20.102 --> 00:47:22.675
MATT: Do you take a look around?

00:47:22.675 --> 00:47:24.144
MARISHA: I want to just glance.

00:47:24.144 --> 00:47:27.282
TRAVIS: I take a very blatant look around.

00:47:27.282 --> 00:47:35.606
MATT: Okay. None of them appear to be armed, but
they're all looking very closely upon you. You can

00:47:35.606 --> 00:47:37.688
make a perception check, Keyleth and Grog, if
you'd like.

00:47:37.688 --> 00:47:42.167
TRAVIS: 13.

00:47:42.167 --> 00:47:43.609
MARISHA: Not bad.

00:47:43.609 --> 00:47:45.167
TRAVIS: There is a ceiling.

00:47:45.167 --> 00:47:48.060
MARISHA: Straight perception? 25.

00:47:48.060 --> 00:47:51.036
MATT: Okay. Yeah, you see them staring. They look
pretty normal.

00:47:51.036 --> 00:47:53.002
TRAVIS: They look pretty.

00:47:53.002 --> 00:47:58.803
MATT: You do notice, what you didn't quite notice
before, when you first entered, but a lot of these

00:47:58.803 --> 00:48:04.507
tables have like small cubbies on the edges, and
each one of them are standing very close to one.

00:48:04.507 --> 00:48:10.712
One you see a little bit of a pommel that is
barely poking out and they're all at the

00:48:10.712 --> 00:48:17.669
ready. This tavern definitely is-- Mercenary band
uses this tavern as their base of operation and has

00:48:17.669 --> 00:48:23.418
definitely seemingly outfitted it to be functionally
good place for mercenaries when they need to be.

00:48:23.418 --> 00:48:28.770
MARISHA: I look down in front of me. Is there any
hidden cubbies in the table that we are at?

00:48:28.770 --> 00:48:30.543
MATT: That you are at?

00:48:30.543 --> 00:48:31.606
MARISHA: Yeah.

00:48:31.606 --> 00:48:35.341
MATT: You have to get down to really inspect. You
want to do that?

00:48:35.341 --> 00:48:36.348
MARISHA: No.

00:48:36.348 --> 00:48:40.754
MATT: Okay. At initial glance you don't see
anything, because everything is close to you, it's

00:48:40.754 --> 00:48:45.133
from a top-down perspective and you're blocked from
seeing anything beneath.

00:48:45.133 --> 00:48:53.013
TALIESIN: For what it's worth, we will not draw
first. We want to find her. Have any of your

00:48:53.013 --> 00:49:00.414
people seen a woman with one metal arm? She's so
dangerous and now so much more dangerous.

00:49:00.414 --> 00:49:12.399
MATT: He goes ahead and puts his finger up this
way and marks this direction. The figure that

00:49:12.399 --> 00:49:19.988
you're watching, Vax, steps out from the shadow and
walks very calmly across the room, through all of

00:49:19.988 --> 00:49:26.812
you right to the edge of the bar by the door and
goes-- not breaking eye contact with you, speaks

00:49:26.812 --> 00:49:35.575
out of the side of his mouth, Treev goes, "Go
ahead and check their story. See her abode. We're

00:49:35.575 --> 00:49:40.016
"all going to wait here nice and patiently together
until we figure out what the fuck is going on."

00:49:40.016 --> 00:49:44.397
TRAVIS: Makes sense. Do you have any mead?

00:49:44.397 --> 00:49:46.091
MATT: "We got mead."

00:49:46.091 --> 00:49:52.659
TALIESIN: In the meantime, I'd like to at least to
start to tell you what we need next, for when our

00:49:52.659 --> 00:49:54.050
story is confirmed.

00:49:54.050 --> 00:49:58.799
MATT: "Well, you've certainly got a captive audience,
so go ahead."

00:49:58.799 --> 00:50:08.547
TALIESIN: This woman has been tracking us. She
placed a mystical tracker upon us at some point.

00:50:08.547 --> 00:50:17.733
We've just discovered it and we need to find a way
to move it away and put it somewhere she does not

00:50:17.733 --> 00:50:25.437
suspect that we know that she placed it and does
not see us coming when it's time for us to kill her.

00:50:25.437 --> 00:50:30.688
MATT: "So you're saying this woman that you're
chasing is the one that killed the mistress?"

00:50:30.688 --> 00:50:33.051
TALIESIN: Yes. We believe so.

00:50:33.051 --> 00:50:40.804
LAURA: Your mistress has-- had a very powerful item on
her. It's why we sought her out as well.

00:50:40.804 --> 00:50:44.975
MATT: "More so blinded-sided at the idea that the
mistress was felled by someone. She could take

00:50:44.975 --> 00:50:47.137
"care of herself and has for quite some time."

00:50:47.137 --> 00:50:51.514
LAURA: From what I could see, her attackers were
not alone. There were five of them.

00:50:51.514 --> 00:50:53.552
LIAM: They had an unfair advantage.

00:50:53.552 --> 00:50:59.928
MATT: "Five of them and a woman, you say?" His
eyes narrow for a second. "Describe this woman."

00:50:59.928 --> 00:51:09.021
SAM: She disguises her appearance, so how we know
her might not be how you have seen her. She has

00:51:09.021 --> 00:51:12.513
sometimes shown herself as an old woman.

00:51:12.513 --> 00:51:20.136
MATT: "Old woman?" And he starts describing. "Sort
of a spindly gray-blonde hair, tumbles past the

00:51:20.136 --> 00:51:24.225
"shoulders, piercing blue-ish green eyes."

00:51:24.225 --> 00:51:25.928
TALIESIN: &lt;i&gt;Always&lt;/i&gt; piercing eyes.

00:51:25.928 --> 00:51:28.212
SAM: Did she come through here?

00:51:28.212 --> 00:51:32.062
MATT: "She was the last one to hire the mistress.
About a week before you came."

00:51:32.062 --> 00:51:33.173
TALIESIN: (sighs heavily)

00:51:33.173 --> 00:51:34.419
SAM: What was the job?

00:51:34.419 --> 00:51:35.597
MATT: "I don't know."

00:51:35.597 --> 00:51:38.723
SAM: And she had some fellows traveling with her?

00:51:38.723 --> 00:51:42.759
MATT: "She had five individuals following her,
aye."

00:51:42.759 --> 00:51:44.245
MARISHA: What did they look like?

00:51:44.245 --> 00:51:48.307
MATT: "Didn't get the best good look. Kept it very
hush-hush between me and the lady at the table.

00:51:48.307 --> 00:51:51.628
"Rest of them stayed at the back of the bar. Then
they went on their business."

00:51:51.628 --> 00:51:53.215
SAM: Where were they staying?

00:51:53.215 --> 00:51:54.180
MATT: "Here."

00:51:54.180 --> 00:51:55.467
SAM: In our rooms?

00:51:55.467 --> 00:51:56.995
MATT: "Aye."

00:51:56.995 --> 00:52:00.607
SAM: That gives me the heebie-jeebies.

00:52:00.607 --> 00:52:05.389
TALIESIN: That does not make me feel good. She is
so dangerous.

00:52:05.389 --> 00:52:07.634
MARISHA: How was she a full week ahead of us?

00:52:07.634 --> 00:52:10.223
LAURA: Oh shit. Treev--

00:52:10.223 --> 00:52:13.713
SAM: Because we went to Draconia.

00:52:13.713 --> 00:52:16.759
LAURA: I put Dust of Tracelessness on the ground.
In her home.

00:52:16.759 --> 00:52:18.851
MATT: "What's that mean?"

00:52:18.851 --> 00:52:24.834
TALIESIN: It's going to obfuscate any of the
scuffle. They're only going to find a body with

00:52:24.834 --> 00:52:26.206
holes in it.

00:52:26.206 --> 00:52:32.619
MATT: "So you're telling me that you came in here
with a story about a murder of one of my finest mercs."

00:52:32.619 --> 00:52:33.613
TALIESIN: Yes.

00:52:33.613 --> 00:52:39.323
MATT: "And you decided upon finding this murder to
get rid of all the evidence of said murder and

00:52:39.323 --> 00:52:41.925
"anything that could possibly point to you not
being the murderers."

00:52:41.925 --> 00:52:48.222
TALIESIN: I did point this out to everybody before
we came down here, but at the moment we were a

00:52:48.222 --> 00:52:51.054
little bit thrown by the dead woman.

00:52:51.054 --> 00:52:52.882
MATT: "I'm not going to lie, I mean as far as--"

00:52:52.882 --> 00:52:57.753
LIAM: Why would we come directly to you if that
were the case? Why wouldn't we have not just left?

00:52:57.753 --> 00:52:59.482
LAURA: Plus, you know what?

00:52:59.482 --> 00:53:02.450
TALIESIN: They will be able to tell the body is at
least a week old.

00:53:02.450 --> 00:53:06.771
LAURA: Exactly. Your man has seen a dead body
before. He's going to be able to tell that it's

00:53:06.771 --> 00:53:08.101
been there for a while.

00:53:08.101 --> 00:53:11.432
MARISHA: I'm sure you have a cleric in the circle.
Talk to her firsthand if you have to.

00:53:11.432 --> 00:53:15.785
LIAM: I'm curious if you can imagine a reason why
we would come to you with this rather than sneak

00:53:15.785 --> 00:53:17.109
away in the night.

00:53:17.109 --> 00:53:19.333
TRAVIS: Yeah, I'm just curious how much the mead
is?

00:53:19.333 --> 00:53:31.479
MATT: "On the house." He reaches under the bar and
pulls up one thick, dark, red ceramic bottle.

00:53:31.479 --> 00:53:35.559
Cap's already off. He's plucked it off with his
thumb and sets it in front of you.

00:53:35.559 --> 00:53:37.775
TRAVIS: My thanks.

00:53:37.775 --> 00:53:40.432
TALIESIN: I'm so sorry.

00:53:40.432 --> 00:53:52.209
MATT: "Guess it's possibly one of the major
setbacks of this line of business. Very few grow

00:53:52.209 --> 00:54:04.107
"too old and gray and get to die happy in their beds.
God knows I wasn't planning to." There's a long,

00:54:04.107 --> 00:54:12.014
awkward pause interspersed with bits of
conversation for about 15 minutes before the

00:54:12.014 --> 00:54:18.446
hooded figure returns, enters the door, comes over
and whispers for a good solid minute in the ear of

00:54:18.446 --> 00:54:29.804
Treev, before stepping back and calmly walking
back to its corner. Treev sits up. "Well, parts of

00:54:29.804 --> 00:54:36.775
"your story certainly hold up. The body has been
there for a while, at least from before I saw you.

00:54:36.775 --> 00:54:40.218
"Mind you, I don't know when you came into town. We
only met a few days ago."

00:54:40.218 --> 00:54:47.837
TALIESIN: If we were smart enough to take care of
her and smart enough to pull all of this off, this

00:54:47.837 --> 00:54:49.908
would be a ridiculous move.

00:54:49.908 --> 00:54:53.642
LAURA: (laughs) That we would come to hire her after
we had already--

00:54:53.642 --> 00:54:54.709
MARISHA: Killed her?

00:54:54.709 --> 00:54:56.345
TALIESIN: I would beg you to explain why we're
having this conversation.

00:54:56.345 --> 00:55:01.207
MATT: "Oh, believe me. A lot of &lt;i&gt;you&lt;/i&gt; doesn't make
sense, period. So I'm just trying to figure it all

00:55:01.207 --> 00:55:06.690
"out." And he rubs the end of his long draconian
snout.

00:55:06.690 --> 00:55:12.329
TALIESIN: The woman in question helped murder my
entire family, took great pleasure and delight in

00:55:12.329 --> 00:55:14.897
it. I have been tracking her for years.

00:55:14.897 --> 00:55:17.048
MATT: "What you plan to do when you find her,
then?"

00:55:17.048 --> 00:55:24.872
TALIESIN: Kill her. That's all. I've lost my taste
for anything beyond that, but she is dangerous and

00:55:24.872 --> 00:55:26.183
she is evil.

00:55:26.183 --> 00:55:29.177
LIAM: In this moment, everyone in this room wants
the same thing.

00:55:29.177 --> 00:55:37.577
MARISHA: We didn't come to you because we
necessarily needed to go through the proper

00:55:37.577 --> 00:55:42.641
channels, we did it because we were trying to be
forthcoming. Clearly you are all a talented bunch,

00:55:42.641 --> 00:55:44.615
so are we.

00:55:44.615 --> 00:55:49.894
TALIESIN: My feelings for her have become very
complex. I don't care who kills her at this point.

00:55:49.894 --> 00:55:52.055
She just needs to be removed from the earth.

00:55:52.055 --> 00:55:55.236
MATT: "Which one of you is your dealmaker?"

00:55:55.236 --> 00:55:59.794
LIAM: I boot Scanlan forward on the tush.

00:55:59.794 --> 00:56:01.740
SAM: Hello, hi.

00:56:01.740 --> 00:56:02.974
MATT: "This one?"

00:56:02.974 --> 00:56:06.459
SAM: I make the best deals, I know the best
words.

00:56:06.459 --> 00:56:11.770
MATT: "&lt;i&gt;This&lt;/i&gt; one?"

00:56:11.770 --> 00:56:17.528
SAM: Sometimes it's Vex, but many times it's me.

00:56:17.528 --> 00:56:27.237
MATT: He leans over the bar and gets real close up
to you, and takes a moment to (sniffs). "Aye, you

00:56:27.237 --> 00:56:31.872
"smell like trouble. I like that." Make a
persuasion check.

00:56:31.872 --> 00:56:33.556
SAM: What am I persuading him to do?

00:56:33.556 --> 00:56:36.298
MATT: This is your essence of presence and telling
him that you're the kind of person that--

00:56:36.298 --> 00:56:37.619
SAM: Oh, my general charm?

00:56:37.619 --> 00:56:38.564
MATT: Your general charm.

00:56:38.564 --> 00:56:41.982
TALIESIN: I don't know what he's wearing, but it's
very nice.

00:56:41.982 --> 00:56:44.819
SAM: Persuasion, you say? 29.

00:56:44.819 --> 00:56:55.104
MATT: "How is this for a deal? I got a nice fine
look at your faces, I got friends all across these

00:56:55.104 --> 00:57:06.680
"lands. If what you say is true, you go. We let you
leave. You find this murdering bitch, you kill

00:57:06.680 --> 00:57:15.429
"her. I want one thing, her good hand. I think that
would be vengeance enough for the mistress."

00:57:15.429 --> 00:57:18.024
MARISHA: I mean, we don't have any use for it.

00:57:18.024 --> 00:57:20.012
TALIESIN: I feel &lt;i&gt;very&lt;/i&gt; good about that deal.

00:57:20.012 --> 00:57:21.341
LIAM: Good terms.

00:57:21.341 --> 00:57:24.378
MATT: "Not talking to you. I'm talking to &lt;i&gt;you&lt;/i&gt;."

00:57:24.378 --> 00:57:28.219
SAM: That's lovely, but we can't find her without
some assistance.

00:57:28.219 --> 00:57:33.472
MATT: "Well, you've come to the right place. What
assistance do I have to give you, what do you need?"

00:57:33.472 --> 00:57:37.923
SAM: We need to get this curse off of the thing
that found your assassin.

00:57:37.923 --> 00:57:41.607
MATT: "Can't really help you with that, sorry,
mate."

00:57:41.607 --> 00:57:44.404
SAM: Don't have any magic wielders among you?

00:57:44.404 --> 00:57:48.617
MATT: "We've got scattered mercs throughout the
city, aye, but they work for coin, and half of

00:57:48.617 --> 00:57:49.952
"them are busy in other jobs."

00:57:49.952 --> 00:57:51.178
LIAM: We have coin.

00:57:51.178 --> 00:57:54.275
MATT: "How much you got?"

00:57:54.275 --> 00:57:56.067
LIAM: What do we got?

00:57:56.067 --> 00:57:57.667
TRAVIS: Enough.

00:57:57.667 --> 00:58:04.349
TALIESIN: Let us know what it takes. Money is
money and we have a long way to go and a lot to

00:58:04.349 --> 00:58:07.146
deal with, but we are happy to pay for the work
that is done.

00:58:07.146 --> 00:58:09.532
MATT: "All right. I can call someone in."

00:58:09.532 --> 00:58:14.629
SAM: We also may need some naval assistance--

00:58:14.629 --> 00:58:17.249
LAURA: Specifically an airship of sorts--

00:58:17.249 --> 00:58:22.273
TALIESIN: Or transportation, she's heading, she's
on a boat, she's heading north to the island of--

00:58:22.304 --> 00:58:23.911
TRAVIS: Glintshore.

00:58:23.911 --> 00:58:28.611
MARISHA: Or, you know, even if you know of any
trees, big trees.

00:58:28.611 --> 00:58:37.219
MATT: He goes "Hmm. Ships, no, not much in the way
of ships here in the middle of a desert, you're

00:58:37.219 --> 00:58:41.686
"looking for them sky-buggers. Looking for a ship
like that for seafaring types you're going to want

00:58:41.686 --> 00:58:47.322
"to go past the Agrin Mountains, then make your way
towards the Bay of Gifts."

00:58:47.322 --> 00:58:48.954
MARISHA and TALIESIN: Bay of Gifts.

00:58:48.954 --> 00:58:50.920
MATT: "That's where you'll find the port town of
Shamal."

00:58:50.920 --> 00:58:52.886
MARISHA: Port town of Shamal?

00:58:52.886 --> 00:59:00.502
MATT: "Shamal. The mountain range is vast in
itself, you're looking at, oh, at least a week on

00:59:00.502 --> 00:59:02.555
"foot to try and traverse those mountains."

00:59:02.555 --> 00:59:03.928
LIAM: Did you say Bay of Gifs?

00:59:03.928 --> 00:59:05.358
SAM: Bay of Jifs, it's pronounced.

00:59:05.358 --> 00:59:08.129
MATT: "I'm going to fucking fuck you."

00:59:08.129 --> 00:59:11.838
(laughter)

00:59:11.838 --> 00:59:15.438
TALIESIN: It's a local joke, I'm so sorry.

00:59:15.438 --> 00:59:20.643
MARISHA: The port of Shamal?

00:59:20.643 --> 00:59:23.637
SAM: There is a skyport near here, is that true?

00:59:23.637 --> 00:59:26.113
MATT: "Aye, it's over by the--"

00:59:26.113 --> 00:59:28.891
SAM: Controlled by the local government?

00:59:28.891 --> 00:59:32.732
MATT: "There's no one fucking controls the
skyport."

00:59:32.732 --> 00:59:35.514
TALIESIN: We're not asking you, we have other
friends as well.

00:59:35.514 --> 00:59:41.043
MATT: "Well, if you're looking for speed, it's
probably your best bet. Ships on this ocean, let's

00:59:41.043 --> 00:59:44.296
"say the weather's not usually handy."

00:59:44.296 --> 00:59:47.758
TALIESIN: We are looking for speed, and a crazy
captain.

00:59:47.758 --> 00:59:51.552
MATT: "Well, wish you the best of luck."

00:59:51.552 --> 00:59:52.716
LAURA: Thank you.

00:59:52.716 --> 01:00:00.233
MATT: "Now, go! Kill her. Give me her hand. I
figure if time goes by and I haven't heard from

01:00:00.233 --> 01:00:04.017
"you, you've either died or I'll be sending some of
our mercs to come find you."

01:00:04.017 --> 01:00:07.001
LIAM: Yeah, but the magic thing with the gun.

01:00:07.001 --> 01:00:11.148
SAM: How long would it take to get this person who
can remove a curse?

01:00:11.148 --> 01:00:13.981
TALIESIN: Or if you were going to go do something
like this, who would you find in town?

01:00:13.981 --> 01:00:18.292
MATT: "If you're looking for fast, speedy, and
immediate assistance with this, well, that's going

01:00:18.292 --> 01:00:23.903
"to have to run the cost up a bit, see. We have
quite an enchanter that could probably help you

01:00:23.903 --> 01:00:24.803
"with that."

01:00:24.803 --> 01:00:25.757
LAURA: Oh really?

01:00:25.757 --> 01:00:34.776
MATT: "Aye. See if in the next hour I could bring
him in, but it'll run you, full disillusion or

01:00:34.776 --> 01:00:38.726
"whatever you need, 750 gold."

01:00:38.726 --> 01:00:41.553
TALIESIN: Not full disillusion, how about a
transference?

01:00:41.553 --> 01:00:43.464
MATT: "Transference--"

01:00:43.464 --> 01:00:45.320
TALIESIN: To move the enchantment to another
object.

01:00:45.320 --> 01:00:46.771
MATT: "Well, takes--"

01:00:46.771 --> 01:00:50.037
LAURA: It's a much easier enchantment.

01:00:50.037 --> 01:00:55.038
MATT: "Moving something takes a little bit longer
than to just get rid of something."

01:00:55.038 --> 01:00:56.317
TALIESIN: How much longer?

01:00:56.317 --> 01:01:01.318
MATT: "I dunno, not one of them types. But I mean,
we've had a couple of enchantments moved in the

01:01:01.318 --> 01:01:04.655
"past, and that was anywhere from a few days to a
few weeks, get that done."

01:01:04.655 --> 01:01:07.229
MARISHA: Why don't we call them in and have them
look at it?

01:01:07.229 --> 01:01:08.501
MATT: "All right."

01:01:08.501 --> 01:01:09.607
SAM: 750? Do we have that to spare?

01:01:09.607 --> 01:01:10.454
TRAVIS: Yes.

01:01:10.454 --> 01:01:11.879
TALIESIN: That's worth its weight.

01:01:11.879 --> 01:01:14.353
MATT: "750."

01:01:14.353 --> 01:01:18.457
LAURA: 750, or if you have a need of gems, we have
gems.

01:01:18.457 --> 01:01:22.875
LIAM: You don't get fast and cheap.

01:01:22.875 --> 01:01:23.955
TALIESIN: I know.

01:01:23.955 --> 01:01:25.252
SAM: Are you a gem lover?

01:01:25.252 --> 01:01:30.253
MATT: "I carry a bit of jewelry on occasion."

01:01:30.253 --> 01:01:32.555
SAM: I like you. What do we have?

01:01:32.555 --> 01:01:36.508
LAURA: So many things. You should call your
enchanter.

01:01:36.508 --> 01:01:44.973
MATT: "All right," and he goes ahead and pulls out
a small tome of blank sheets, many you see have

01:01:44.973 --> 01:01:49.773
been torn out, and he makes a quick note on one,
rolls it up very simply, doesn't do the usual

01:01:49.845 --> 01:01:58.523
rigmarole of an official writ, but hands it to the
masked hooded figure in the corner who walks out

01:01:58.523 --> 01:02:02.980
and darts off. "Kyme'll be here in a hour."

01:02:02.980 --> 01:02:04.015
LAURA: An hour.

01:02:04.015 --> 01:02:04.893
SAM: Kine?

01:02:04.893 --> 01:02:05.782
MATT: "Kyme."

01:02:05.782 --> 01:02:07.129
LAURA: Kynan?

01:02:07.129 --> 01:02:10.549
LIAM: Sorry, that rang a bell. Sorry.

01:02:10.549 --> 01:02:13.871
MATT: "Payment?"

01:02:13.871 --> 01:02:17.325
LAURA: Payment?

01:02:17.325 --> 01:02:18.743
SAM: Up front? Wow.

01:02:18.743 --> 01:02:21.114
LAURA: But we don't even know what he's doing
yet.

01:02:21.114 --> 01:02:23.604
MATT: "Do you trust in my service?"

01:02:23.604 --> 01:02:28.842
LAURA: Of course, I don't know what we're going to
have him do, that's all.

01:02:28.842 --> 01:02:32.248
MATT: "Well if you'd much rather, we could go
ahead and clean out your guts here in the floor,

01:02:32.248 --> 01:02:35.177
"wouldn't be the first time I had to swab the
floors here."

01:02:35.177 --> 01:02:44.046
LAURA: How about these two beautiful sapphires?
They're quite lovely.

01:02:44.046 --> 01:02:45.878
MATT: "All right."

01:02:45.878 --> 01:02:50.863
LAURA: And-- and I pull out a giant raw ruby as
well.

01:02:50.863 --> 01:02:58.837
MATT: He knocks the countertop and gestures for
you to put them down. He looks over at one of the

01:02:58.901 --> 01:03:04.649
guys in the bar. They've all relaxed a bit now,
two of them have sat down. One of them approaches;

01:03:04.649 --> 01:03:14.649
human, a little scruffy, looks like he's a little
ill to be honest, like he's probably not had a

01:03:14.649 --> 01:03:21.121
good week of food. He, however, walks up and
fumbles through a small pouch and pulls out a

01:03:21.121 --> 01:03:30.436
small jeweler's eyepiece and takes them up and
inspects each of them independently. How much are

01:03:30.436 --> 01:03:31.894
they worth?

01:03:31.894 --> 01:03:36.572
LAURA: 200 each for the sapphires, and the ruby is
150.

01:03:36.572 --> 01:03:38.169
SAM: Jesus, Laura.

01:03:38.169 --> 01:03:40.553
LAURA: It's only a hundred gold short!

01:03:40.553 --> 01:03:53.318
MATT: "I'd take it." Sits back down. "Very well,
debt is paid." Takes the gems, pops them in his

01:03:53.318 --> 01:03:57.635
little side pouch. Do you guys wait for the hour?

01:03:57.635 --> 01:04:03.887
TALIESIN: I was going to say, if somebody wants to
go booking passage on an airship, my personal

01:04:03.887 --> 01:04:07.559
feeling is that Grog and Scanlan would be the
people to send on such an adventure.

01:04:07.559 --> 01:04:13.528
SAM: Grog? I mean, yes, Grog would be good at
that, yes, let's do that.

01:04:13.528 --> 01:04:16.514
TALIESIN: I'm only saying Grog because then they
know what they're getting into.

01:04:16.514 --> 01:04:18.073
SAM: I like that idea.

01:04:18.073 --> 01:04:19.992
TRAVIS: Are you trying to get me out of the room?

01:04:19.992 --> 01:04:26.048
TALIESIN: No! Well, yes. Would you rather sit for
an hour in here or would you rather go outside and

01:04:26.048 --> 01:04:28.080
talk to somebody about a giant flying boat?

01:04:28.080 --> 01:04:29.939
TRAVIS: The last one.

01:04:29.939 --> 01:04:34.905
LIAM: Perfect, it's like Hannibal and Mr. T,
together, that's what you want.

01:04:34.905 --> 01:04:38.168
TALIESIN: I don't know, that's my opinion,
personally, unless anybody else--

01:04:38.168 --> 01:04:40.045
TRAVIS: Just call me Baracus, let's go.

01:04:40.045 --> 01:04:42.543
SAM: All right, we'll go.

01:04:42.543 --> 01:04:45.445
TALIESIN: Our friends are going to arrange travel
for us, the rest of us are going to stay here, is

01:04:45.445 --> 01:04:46.830
that appropriate?

01:04:46.830 --> 01:04:55.137
MATT: "Certainly. Sit, I'll get you some food." So
is it going to be just you two?

01:04:55.137 --> 01:04:57.691
SAM: I guess we're going to go try to find an
airship.

01:04:57.789 --> 01:05:02.067
TRAVIS: Yeah, Twins! Schwarzenegger and DeVito, at
it again!

01:05:02.067 --> 01:05:04.391
(laughter)

01:05:04.391 --> 01:05:05.642
TALIESIN: Julius, my god!

01:05:05.642 --> 01:05:07.310
SAM: Which one's which?

01:05:07.310 --> 01:05:10.644
LIAM: Vincent, you are my twin.

01:05:10.644 --> 01:05:17.165
TALIESIN: I'm pregnant, Vincent. Oh, wrong one,
sorry. I always thought it was the same guy. In my

01:05:17.165 --> 01:05:18.648
head. It's a sequel.

01:05:18.648 --> 01:05:25.591
MATT: All right, so, as the rest of you guys stay
behind you get a fair meal, the two of you begin

01:05:25.591 --> 01:05:36.740
making your way through Ank'Harel. You're making
your way over towards the edge of the Suncut

01:05:36.740 --> 01:05:42.662
Bazaar towards the Sand Herald district right on
that cusp there is where you saw the skyport in

01:05:42.662 --> 01:05:47.335
the distance. Go ahead and make an investigation
check. You can make one as well, Grog.

01:05:47.335 --> 01:05:49.316
SAM: 25.

01:05:49.316 --> 01:05:53.078
TRAVIS: 17!

01:05:53.078 --> 01:05:57.307
MATT: All right. Where normally it would be
confusing to find where the base of it is as it is

01:05:57.307 --> 01:06:03.083
obfuscated by a series of other larger buildings,
you guys ask a couple of folks rather quickly that

01:06:03.083 --> 01:06:08.780
know the layout of the town really well, and with
enough of a flash of a smile and a flash of a

01:06:08.780 --> 01:06:18.437
really intense arm muscle, within the next 30
minutes or so find yourself at the base of the

01:06:18.437 --> 01:06:20.676
actual skyport. It is called the Indala Skyport.

01:06:20.676 --> 01:06:22.608
SAM: (sings) Indala.

01:06:22.608 --> 01:06:31.486
MATT: Not as tall as the one in Emon which lays on
the outskirts of the Cloudtop District, but it

01:06:31.486 --> 01:06:39.677
appears to be on the level, it's maybe a good
five stories up. The outside of it is a similar

01:06:39.677 --> 01:06:44.260
chain lifted platform as the tower at the Cerulean
Palace that you guys traversed earlier in your

01:06:44.260 --> 01:06:50.366
time in Ank'Harel. There is a large stone scaffold
with no walls, sitting there on the ground. As you

01:06:50.366 --> 01:06:56.007
approach, there are two people dressed in simple
clothing, you see some dust and dirt on their

01:06:56.007 --> 01:07:00.427
hands, they're in the midst of moving crates up
and down and you see they're moving some barrels

01:07:00.427 --> 01:07:06.313
off of the platform, putting them up onto a cart
that's probably going to be wheeled deeper into

01:07:06.313 --> 01:07:16.201
the city. As you approach the platform you see one
of them is by a bell mechanism, attached to part

01:07:16.201 --> 01:07:21.721
of the platform, a small block that's about
shoulder high, and there's a bell on the end of it

01:07:21.721 --> 01:07:23.071
with a ringer.

01:07:23.071 --> 01:07:29.274
TRAVIS: Wait, before we ring Indala: have you ever
rented a skyship before?

01:07:29.274 --> 01:07:31.002
SAM: No, I have no idea what we're doing here.

01:07:31.002 --> 01:07:32.201
TRAVIS: Oh really?

01:07:32.201 --> 01:07:38.811
SAM: I mean, I assume we're trying to find out how
much it costs for a seven day rental including a

01:07:38.811 --> 01:07:40.103
pilot or two?

01:07:40.103 --> 01:07:41.923
TRAVIS: So we're doing this like the straight and
narrow way.

01:07:41.923 --> 01:07:44.110
SAM: We're getting the information, probably come
back and steal it.

01:07:44.110 --> 01:07:47.624
TRAVIS: Ooh, okay, I'll be quiet, you talk.

01:07:47.624 --> 01:07:50.642
SAM: Okay, well, you're pretty good at this too.

01:07:50.642 --> 01:07:55.083
TRAVIS: Yeah, well. (singing) Indala, Indala

01:07:55.083 --> 01:07:57.005
LIAM: Help, help, it's happening.

01:07:57.005 --> 01:07:58.582
TALIESIN: Help, help, it's actually happening.

01:07:58.582 --> 01:08:00.117
TRAVIS: Do you mind if I ring the bell?

01:08:00.117 --> 01:08:02.927
SAM: Yeah, go for it.

01:08:02.927 --> 01:08:06.306
TRAVIS: Can I ring the fucking shit out of that
bell?

01:08:06.306 --> 01:08:10.298
MATT: As you step up onto the stone platform both
of you, the two guys that are working, the guy

01:08:10.298 --> 01:08:14.451
keeps putting the barrels, there's like two or
three on the side there, and he goes ahead and

01:08:14.451 --> 01:08:21.809
sets one of the three up, staring at you as you
approach. The other guy is to the side, goes, "Can

01:08:21.809 --> 01:08:27.430
"I help you?" As you walk past and turn back and
smile and (bell ringing) start ringing the crap

01:08:27.430 --> 01:08:32.245
out of it. Make a strength check.

01:08:32.245 --> 01:08:38.288
TRAVIS: Aww no, oh that's not too bad. 13.

01:08:38.288 --> 01:08:45.791
MATT: 13, okay. You have enough control over your
physical brawn as to not snap or destroy the bell,

01:08:45.791 --> 01:08:51.125
however, what happens is after you ring the bell
for a few seconds, the guy goes, "Wait, no!" And

01:08:51.125 --> 01:08:58.585
before anything else happens, the chains that were
slack tighten up, and the platform begins to lift

01:08:58.585 --> 01:09:04.305
up. The guy who had two barrels left on the
platform still is like "No, wait!" And goes over

01:09:04.305 --> 01:09:07.927
and tries to grab one of the barrels as it tumbles
off and breaks on the ground next to him.

01:09:07.927 --> 01:09:12.622
(yelling in Marquesian) and is raising his fists.

01:09:12.622 --> 01:09:15.236
SAM: We're on an elevator?

01:09:15.236 --> 01:09:20.510
MATT: Yeah, and it's now lifting up and it's about
15-20 feet off the ground and it's going up to the

01:09:20.510 --> 01:09:25.990
top. The bell seemed to have notified whatever
crew is bringing the platform up, but he didn't

01:09:25.990 --> 01:09:29.116
get a chance to finish bringing his load off the
platform before you rung the bell.

01:09:29.116 --> 01:09:30.314
TRAVIS: I think we're doing it right.

01:09:30.314 --> 01:09:31.391
SAM: I think so.

01:09:31.391 --> 01:09:37.482
MATT: As you leave the two gentlemen below, as the
two of you lift up on this platform, you make your

01:09:37.482 --> 01:09:45.615
way up to the elevated terrace that marks the
actual skyport and it's a large, wide, thick

01:09:45.615 --> 01:09:50.679
platform that's built atop a series of warehouses
that fill out this district, and this was a newer

01:09:50.679 --> 01:09:58.189
addition to it as this technology became
available. Go ahead and roll a history check.

01:09:58.189 --> 01:10:00.589
SAM: Natural 20.

01:10:00.589 --> 01:10:05.397
TRAVIS: Wow!

01:10:05.397 --> 01:10:06.812
SAM: Love me some airships.

01:10:06.812 --> 01:10:12.708
MATT: Actually, skyships originated in Ank'Harel.
This is where the crystals that hold them aloft

01:10:12.708 --> 01:10:19.769
are enchanted. There have been other ships. There
are different designs that are constructed in

01:10:19.769 --> 01:10:26.511
different towns. You do know that there is no
skyship transport to Wildemount, and that was part

01:10:26.511 --> 01:10:35.438
of the reason why the Sovereign Uriel was trying
to make that deal with the Briarwoods under the

01:10:35.438 --> 01:10:42.716
idea that it would open trade with Wildemount.
It's pretty insular, locked off from the larger

01:10:42.716 --> 01:10:46.779
countries here that work together. The skyport
here is probably the first skyport that was built

01:10:46.779 --> 01:10:54.092
and this is the origin of that tech. As you come
to the very top of the platform,

01:10:54.092 --> 01:11:01.372
it eventually stops and you see one
gentleman there who's essentially working this

01:11:01.372 --> 01:11:05.010
large crank that brings the platform up and it has
a series of thick chains that wind on themselves.

01:11:05.010 --> 01:11:10.017
As soon as he finishes and you guys get to the top
he turns. "What, yes, what. Hello?"

01:11:10.017 --> 01:11:11.343
TRAVIS: Meep-meep!

01:11:11.343 --> 01:11:21.229
SAM: Be pleased. We are here to inquire about some
business if you don't mind.

01:11:21.229 --> 01:11:25.540
MATT: He points that way, and you guys look right,
and the rest of this terrace for the record--

01:11:25.540 --> 01:11:35.273
there are two skyships that are currently docked
here at the moment. One that has a very nice,

01:11:35.273 --> 01:11:43.299
thick, heavy design, it has beautiful gems
encrusted in the side and there's brass and gold

01:11:43.299 --> 01:11:48.641
inlay that twists into this turquoise transition
to the bottom. It's a beautiful ship. You can see

01:11:48.641 --> 01:11:54.914
there's a crew of about 12, that are currently
loading things onto it right now. There's a big,

01:11:54.914 --> 01:11:57.762
crane-like apparatus similar to what you had in
Emon that is currently putting things onto the

01:11:57.762 --> 01:12:01.817
ship. It looks like it's being heavily loaded for
transport somewhere. There's another ship, it

01:12:01.817 --> 01:12:07.717
looks familiar, it's actually very similar to the
Emon designs that you guys saw at the skyports

01:12:07.717 --> 01:12:14.878
over there that appears to be, by about six heavy 
chains, locked to the opposite side of this skyport and doesn't

01:12:14.926 --> 01:12:20.378
seem to have any apparent hustle bustle of crew
around. It's a little bit smaller than the more

01:12:20.378 --> 01:12:26.329
intricate design. The one that has all the work
around it does match some of the design aesthetic

01:12:26.329 --> 01:12:30.680
of some of the higher end areas of Ank'Harel, so
that you probably imagine it was one of the

01:12:30.680 --> 01:12:35.771
original skyships that was built here. The other
one you saw has the small fins on the side,

01:12:35.771 --> 01:12:40.705
similar to the one you rode across to Vasselheim.
You do also notice that there are about six Hands

01:12:40.705 --> 01:12:45.985
of Ord scattered across the terrace in full armor
that are basically keeping an eye out and watching

01:12:45.985 --> 01:12:56.796
everything, making sure that no bullshit goes
down. You do see a small building that's in the

01:12:56.796 --> 01:13:04.027
center of this terrace, that maybe has about three
or four different rooms. Apparently, the

01:13:04.027 --> 01:13:11.465
individual who was overseeing this entire process
with the one big ship is walking back and forth

01:13:11.465 --> 01:13:14.431
between with instructions to the foreman who's
yelling out to the crewmen who are loading up this

01:13:14.431 --> 01:13:16.529
big ship. That'll probably be the place to go to
inquire.

01:13:16.529 --> 01:13:17.973
SAM: Okay. We go over there.

01:13:17.973 --> 01:13:22.135
MATT: All right. As you walk in--

01:13:22.135 --> 01:13:23.506
SAM: We die.

01:13:23.506 --> 01:13:28.382
MATT: Suffer a horrible stroke and fall to the
ground. Scanlan is no more.

01:13:28.382 --> 01:13:30.782
TRAVIS: Green dragon unveils herself and we die.

01:13:30.782 --> 01:13:33.550
LIAM: My barrels! (dragon roaring noise)

01:13:33.550 --> 01:13:39.405
TRAVIS: Shit, literally in the last place we would have
looked.

01:13:39.405 --> 01:13:58.072
MATT: So as you walk into the room, it's fairly
quiet. There appears to be a clerk office there

01:13:58.072 --> 01:14:04.723
with a bunch of ledgers stacked up, and you can
see a layout of a number of days with notes

01:14:04.723 --> 01:14:11.980
scrawled in a language that you don't recognize.
There are a couple of small clockwork timepieces

01:14:11.980 --> 01:14:16.494
that are against the walls there. And you see a
younger woman, probably mid-20s, but going gray a

01:14:16.494 --> 01:14:21.965
little early all on one side of her head, who is
currently going through one of these books. She

01:14:21.965 --> 01:14:29.597
has a quill between her teeth right now, she's
thumbing through the pages. Looks up, "Can I help

01:14:29.597 --> 01:14:32.226
"you?" Takes the quill out, sets it down.

01:14:32.226 --> 01:14:39.579
SAM: Hello, Be pleased, beep beep. My associate
and I would like to inquire about renting an

01:14:39.637 --> 01:14:41.041
airship.

01:14:41.041 --> 01:14:43.250
MATT: "Renting an airship."

01:14:43.250 --> 01:14:46.028
SAM: Chartering it for a trip.

01:14:46.028 --> 01:14:56.408
MATT: "Okay, well for now, let's see. Ship Vusin
is already chartered and is loading up to be

01:14:56.408 --> 01:15:04.791
"heading northward towards Issylra. That is not
available. The other one which is the Deera has

01:15:04.791 --> 01:15:10.903
"been docked for about four weeks without use. So
you could go inquire with the captain there."

01:15:10.903 --> 01:15:15.548
SAM: Is that the crappier one or the better one?

01:15:15.548 --> 01:15:16.839
MATT It's the smaller one.

01:15:16.839 --> 01:15:22.145
SAM: Okay, so we would charter from the captain
themself, not from you?

01:15:22.145 --> 01:15:33.566
MATT: "Well the captain would pay us a cut based
on what the destination is."

01:15:33.566 --> 01:15:36.801
SAM: So I can do my homework, how much do you
think a week's charter would run on an airship?

01:15:36.801 --> 01:15:38.551
MATT: "That is for you to negotiate with the
captain."

01:15:38.551 --> 01:15:41.215
TRAVIS: Yes, is there any way to book passage on
the ship that's already moving northward?

01:15:41.215 --> 01:15:43.355
SAM: As passengers.

01:15:43.355 --> 01:15:48.563
MATT: "That is not a passenger-based ship,
unfortunately that is actually working for one of

01:15:48.563 --> 01:15:52.606
"the guilds. It is paid for use of their mercantile
only."

01:15:52.606 --> 01:15:55.376
SAM: Okay.

01:15:55.376 --> 01:15:58.746
TRAVIS: How fast is that smaller ship?

01:15:58.746 --> 01:16:05.949
MATT: "Unloaded, pretty quick. The cargo can load
down ships."

01:16:05.949 --> 01:16:07.405
TRAVIS: Hmm, yes.

01:16:07.405 --> 01:16:10.673
MATT: "Depends on how fast you wish to go and
where you are going. May I ask where you are

01:16:10.673 --> 01:16:11.915
"planning to charter this to?"

01:16:11.915 --> 01:16:15.891
SAM: Our mission is a bit of a hush-hush one, we
better not disclose that.

01:16:15.891 --> 01:16:26.079
TRAVIS: Yeah, we are going to an ocean.

01:16:26.079 --> 01:16:29.974
MATT: "Perhaps it is best that we negotiate the
price here than as opposed to with the captain."

01:16:29.974 --> 01:16:34.095
SAM: Yes, that would be preferable for sure.

01:16:34.095 --> 01:16:37.572
TRAVIS: Wait, why? Who's the captain?

01:16:37.572 --> 01:16:45.401
MATT: She stands up and walks over to one of the
small windows that leads out to the terrace and

01:16:45.401 --> 01:16:51.763
you can see another bell that's out there and she
grabs the edge (bell ringing) on the bell, goes

01:16:51.763 --> 01:16:59.965
back to her seat. "I'm calling the captain, he'll
be here." A few minutes pass, in the distance out

01:16:59.965 --> 01:17:11.269
the window you can see a small rope ladder drops,
and a figure makes their way over and walks in.

01:17:11.269 --> 01:17:18.960
Inside, in gold-trimmed armor is a familiar sight,
this is Captain Damon, the guy who actually

01:17:18.960 --> 01:17:21.950
brought you guys across the Ozmit Sea.

01:17:21.950 --> 01:17:24.566
SAM: It's our guy! Damon!

01:17:24.566 --> 01:17:28.877
MARISHA: Are there not that many pilots in the
world?

01:17:28.877 --> 01:17:41.036
MATT: There aren't a &lt;i&gt;lot&lt;/i&gt; of skyships. You would
know, there's probably six in commission.

01:17:41.036 --> 01:17:43.676
SAM: How fast did this one make the Kessel Run?

01:17:43.676 --> 01:17:49.882
MATT: It was a week across the entire Ozmit Sea,
that was with some cargo on board, so it wasn't

01:17:49.882 --> 01:17:55.609
very slow. It would have taken a normal ship two
and a half weeks.

01:17:55.609 --> 01:17:57.202
SAM: Does Damon recognize us?

01:17:57.202 --> 01:18:00.499
MATT: As he walks in he goes "Yes, are we ready
to--"

01:18:00.499 --> 01:18:03.753
MARISHA: Wyverns attacked us!

01:18:03.753 --> 01:18:04.969
LIAM: (whispering) We're not there.

01:18:04.969 --> 01:18:07.016
MARISHA: I'm not there at all!

01:18:07.016 --> 01:18:12.362
TRAVIS: What did you end up drinking in that damn
tavern?

01:18:12.362 --> 01:18:16.446
SAM: Captain Damon! Hello.

01:18:16.446 --> 01:18:17.648
MATT: "Wait, I know you."

01:18:17.648 --> 01:18:20.891
SAM: Yes, we've flown together before. On the
friendly skies.

01:18:20.891 --> 01:18:24.890
MATT: "Yes, that was a dangerous journey."

01:18:24.890 --> 01:18:32.143
SAM: It was, and would have been more dangerous
had we not been there. To protect you and your ship.

01:18:32.143 --> 01:18:37.294
MATT: "Indeed. We appreciate that. What can I do
for you?" And he looks over towards the clerk who

01:18:37.294 --> 01:18:41.121
goes, "They are looking to charter a ship
northward. I know nothing else more, but I figured

01:18:41.121 --> 01:18:45.877
"the confusion here would allow us at least both to
discuss this so we can negotiate the proper

01:18:45.877 --> 01:18:50.726
"price. So you talk, I'll be here to keep record."
And she opens a fresh page in her tome, dips her quill--

01:18:50.726 --> 01:18:52.632
TRAVIS: Mmm. Ledgers.

01:18:52.632 --> 01:18:55.127
SAM: Oh, maybe we don't want any of this on the
record for right now.

01:18:55.127 --> 01:18:58.864
MATT: "Okay. Remember that for the negotiation."

01:18:58.864 --> 01:19:00.989
SAM: Oh shit.

01:19:00.989 --> 01:19:08.985
MATT: Captain winks at her. "All right, so, we're
very busy, our books are full and we have a few

01:19:08.985 --> 01:19:15.360
"other individuals that are currently seeking use
of our ship. So what is it you need, where are you

01:19:15.360 --> 01:19:16.689
"going and for how long?"

01:19:16.689 --> 01:19:21.281
SAM: This would be a week or less for the
mission.

01:19:21.281 --> 01:19:24.063
TRAVIS: Looking to leave quite soon.

01:19:24.063 --> 01:19:25.393
SAM: Maybe even tomorrow morning.

01:19:25.393 --> 01:19:26.571
MATT: "All right."

01:19:26.571 --> 01:19:28.924
SAM: We'd be going north. Correct?

01:19:28.924 --> 01:19:29.892
TRAVIS: Yes.

01:19:29.892 --> 01:19:35.805
SAM: Into the Ozmit Sea, and to a location that we
would disclose to you once we get airborne.

01:19:35.805 --> 01:19:41.405
MATT: You hear a voice in the back, "Also consider
that in the negotiation."

01:19:41.405 --> 01:19:49.200
SAM: But also consider this. We are on a mission
that's very important to the security of both

01:19:49.200 --> 01:19:54.946
Marquet and other continents, and we have friends
in high places. And I will flash our little badge.

01:19:54.946 --> 01:19:56.247
TRAVIS: Yes!

01:19:56.247 --> 01:19:59.482
SAM: The badge that J'Mon Sa Ord gave us.

01:19:59.482 --> 01:20:02.071
LIAM: Not your fake little star from pre-show?

01:20:02.071 --> 01:20:05.231
MATT: He looks down and he goes, "That looks very
pretty."

01:20:05.231 --> 01:20:09.133
TRAVIS: Oh, this is given from J'mon Sa Ord.

01:20:09.133 --> 01:20:13.673
MATT: "I don't know who that is."

01:20:13.673 --> 01:20:16.262
SAM: Yes, I didn't think you would--

01:20:16.262 --> 01:20:20.056
MATT: The clerk, however, says, "Wait, you're
saying you got something from J'mon Sa Ord. You

01:20:20.056 --> 01:20:22.607
"saw J'mon Sa Ord, and you were given something."

01:20:22.607 --> 01:20:23.895
TRAVIS and SAM: Yes.

01:20:23.895 --> 01:20:26.541
MATT: (laughter) "Let me see this."

01:20:26.541 --> 01:20:27.905
SAM: I hand it over.

01:20:27.905 --> 01:20:31.023
MATT: She looks at it. (laughter fades)

01:20:31.023 --> 01:20:37.307
(laughter)

01:20:37.307 --> 01:20:41.011
MATT: "Very well."

01:20:41.055 --> 01:20:45.677
TRAVIS: Consider that in negotiation.

01:20:45.677 --> 01:20:56.789
MATT: She looks over and meets eyes with the
captain and goes, "We're going to go ahead, you

01:20:56.789 --> 01:21:00.564
"let me know the price and the palace is going to
pay for this expedition."

01:21:00.564 --> 01:21:03.886
SAM: I didn't know it would do that!

01:21:03.886 --> 01:21:10.088
LAURA: That is the most valuable necklace!

01:21:10.088 --> 01:21:17.681
MATT: Opens the book and begins writing down a
series of charges and is racking up--

01:21:17.681 --> 01:21:19.336
LIAM: You just Babe Ruth-ed that shit!

01:21:19.336 --> 01:21:21.659
MARISHA: Company card, man.

01:21:21.659 --> 01:21:27.111
SAM: We'll probably need sparkling water, stat.
Lots of brandy for the trip.

01:21:27.111 --> 01:21:30.803
TRAVIS: Maybe some servants and some masseuses.

01:21:30.803 --> 01:21:38.089
SAM: Yes. I will definitely need someone with a
knowledge of the sea, both in the air and down

01:21:38.089 --> 01:21:39.722
below, the waters below.

01:21:39.722 --> 01:21:47.370
MATT: The captain says, "Actually we've got an
individual just for that." He looks back to the

01:21:47.370 --> 01:21:54.145
clerk, "Are you sure?" "Yes, it's fine, not a
worry. We'll talk when they leave."

01:21:54.145 --> 01:22:00.932
TRAVIS: Don't mind me, but I have violence on the
mind at all times. Is there any customary weaponry

01:22:00.932 --> 01:22:05.302
or defense that you can put on this airship during
our travels? Just in case we run into the same

01:22:05.302 --> 01:22:08.224
shit we did last time.

01:22:08.224 --> 01:22:14.615
MATT: The captain goes, "Actually, after the
encounter we had over the Ozmit last time, I

01:22:14.615 --> 01:22:22.656
"managed to outfit this ship with a brand new
series of dragon arbalests, so this is going to be

01:22:22.656 --> 01:22:23.909
"a well-defended journey."

01:22:23.909 --> 01:22:25.479
TRAVIS: Nice. Do they aim in all directions?

01:22:25.479 --> 01:22:26.744
MATT: "You'll see."

01:22:26.744 --> 01:22:27.779
TRAVIS: Nice.

01:22:27.779 --> 01:22:34.505
MATT: And you do recall seeing them when you were
in Vasselheim, you saw them being brought down and

01:22:34.505 --> 01:22:36.849
installed on the ship. But that was last time you
saw the ship.

01:22:36.849 --> 01:22:41.038
SAM: Can the ship be prepared to leave tomorrow
morning?

01:22:41.038 --> 01:22:47.335
MATT: "We can leave in the next hour, if you
want."

01:22:47.335 --> 01:22:51.297
TRAVIS: Stand at the ready, our business is of
great import.

01:22:51.297 --> 01:22:57.489
SAM: Yes, Grog. Yes it is. I think you should ring
the bell to make this an official deal.

01:22:57.489 --> 01:22:58.687
TRAVIS: Can I ring the bell?

01:22:58.687 --> 01:23:00.482
MATT: You can if you want to.

01:23:00.482 --> 01:23:03.778
TRAVIS: But I don't grab it and ring it, I go
(clang) one loud time.

01:23:03.778 --> 01:23:14.649
MATT: The ringing is discordant and painful in
proximity and the clerk went (groaning). The

01:23:14.649 --> 01:23:20.526
captain chuckles to himself. "So. In the
morning."

01:23:20.526 --> 01:23:24.154
SAM: We'll have to discuss with our associates,
but be prepared as quickly as possible.

01:23:24.154 --> 01:23:26.323
MATT: "All right. I'll assemble the crew and we'll
be ready within the hour."

01:23:26.323 --> 01:23:27.824
SAM: Excellent.

01:23:27.824 --> 01:23:35.408
TRAVIS: How many of your crew will you have with
you? Just ballpark it.

01:23:35.408 --> 01:23:44.409
MATT: It would be a crew of eight. "Normally
seven, but we have eight now."

01:23:44.409 --> 01:23:49.174
TRAVIS: And I'm sure this crew is your finest. No
greenhorns. Men you've spent years with, trust

01:23:49.174 --> 01:23:50.067
your life with.

01:23:50.067 --> 01:23:51.188
MATT: "Most of them, yes."

01:23:51.188 --> 01:23:53.726
TRAVIS: Most of them. How many do you not trust
your life with?

01:23:53.726 --> 01:23:56.764
MATT: "There is one we've had on board for a short
time, but she's definitely proven worthy."

01:23:56.764 --> 01:24:01.523
TRAVIS: Perhaps she should stay behind on this
voyage.

01:24:01.601 --> 01:24:04.356
MATT: "She's the one with the mastery of the
ocean."

01:24:04.356 --> 01:24:08.450
TRAVIS: She's coming with us.

01:24:08.517 --> 01:24:15.230
SAM: Thank you, Damon. Oh, one more thing. I asked
you this last time, but are you still single?

01:24:15.298 --> 01:24:17.484
MATT: "Yes?"

01:24:17.484 --> 01:24:19.000
SAM: Okay, good to know.

01:24:19.000 --> 01:24:22.777
TRAVIS: Don't worry about him, there's a hubbub
down in the quarter. People talking. It's the gold

01:24:22.777 --> 01:24:23.807
armor.

01:24:23.807 --> 01:24:25.841
MATT: "I'm going to go ready my ship."

01:24:25.841 --> 01:24:31.853
TRAVIS: Yep. Good! We'll be back. Why did you ask
him if he was single? That was so awkward.

01:24:31.853 --> 01:24:33.965
SAM: Because Vex really liked him last time.

01:24:33.965 --> 01:24:35.972
TRAVIS: Yeah, I know, but he thought you liked
him. Now we have to--

01:24:35.972 --> 01:24:38.646
SAM: You know what, everyone thinks I like them.
That's part of my wink-y charm.

01:24:38.646 --> 01:24:41.049
TRAVIS: I thought you said that it's part of your
winky, I'm like, that's not--

01:24:41.049 --> 01:24:42.471
SAM: (nudge-wink sound)

01:24:42.471 --> 01:24:50.537
MATT: All right. You guys seemingly locked
passage.

01:24:50.537 --> 01:24:52.815
TRAVIS: Boom. For free, bitch! On the house!

01:24:52.815 --> 01:24:54.333
SAM: We could have been using this all over the
place!

01:24:54.333 --> 01:24:56.858
TRAVIS: I know. It's an AmEx Black Card.

01:24:56.858 --> 01:25:00.699
SAM: Real quick, guys. Real quick.

01:25:00.699 --> 01:25:02.105
TRAVIS: We make our way back.

01:25:02.105 --> 01:25:09.489
SAM: Real quick, though, on the way back I'm going
to go to the casino. Just real quick.

01:25:09.489 --> 01:25:10.720
LAURA: (yells) Scanlan!

01:25:10.720 --> 01:25:11.996
TALIESIN: No, hold out. Let's see this.

01:25:11.996 --> 01:25:14.180
TRAVIS: Yep. I'm with him. I'm with you.

01:25:14.180 --> 01:25:20.823
MATT: Now you, guiding back, head right towards
the Luck's Run.

01:25:20.823 --> 01:25:25.156
TRAVIS: I don't know if this is where our friends
are.

01:25:25.156 --> 01:25:26.541
SAM: It's a shortcut, friend.

01:25:26.541 --> 01:25:27.612
TRAVIS: Oh, okay.

01:25:27.612 --> 01:25:33.021
SAM: We get outside, I pull Grog into a little
alleyway and I say: Listen, friend. I'm going to

01:25:33.021 --> 01:25:36.191
go in there and do a little business. Can you do
me a favor?

01:25:36.191 --> 01:25:38.771
TRAVIS: Play some music outside while you go
number two?

01:25:38.771 --> 01:25:44.481
SAM: I need you to keep your eyes open. Can I
Minor Illusion a face of one of those guys who did

01:25:44.481 --> 01:25:46.192
the deal with me?

01:25:46.192 --> 01:25:50.289
MATT: Yeah, you could. It's a still image, it
makes no sound. It's very much an illusion--

01:25:50.289 --> 01:25:57.653
SAM: Yeah, it's for him. To show him what he looks
like. This face, look at it. Lock it in. I do the

01:25:57.653 --> 01:26:00.418
other face as well. This face, you see it?

01:26:00.418 --> 01:26:01.794
TRAVIS: Is there a test on this later?

01:26:01.794 --> 01:26:04.653
SAM: There's only one test. If you see these
people, grab them.

01:26:04.653 --> 01:26:05.976
TRAVIS: Grab them. And then what?

01:26:05.976 --> 01:26:07.989
SAM: Do what Grog does best.

01:26:07.989 --> 01:26:10.792
TRAVIS: Just do what I do best when I see them?

01:26:10.792 --> 01:26:15.697
SAM: Yes. But you won't see them unless they leave
the casino. Just stay out here at the door.

01:26:15.697 --> 01:26:16.520
TRAVIS: Outside?

01:26:16.520 --> 01:26:17.493
SAM: Yes.

01:26:17.493 --> 01:26:18.639
TRAVIS: Cool.

01:26:18.639 --> 01:26:20.124
SAM: You're my lookout man.

01:26:20.124 --> 01:26:23.736
TRAVIS: Should I have a code word if you know
they're coming out, like--

01:26:23.736 --> 01:26:27.886
SAM: Yeah, let's come up with one right now.
Yeah.

01:26:27.886 --> 01:26:30.575
TRAVIS: Dijon.

01:26:30.575 --> 01:26:33.515
SAM: Yeah. There it is. Dijon.

01:26:33.515 --> 01:26:36.996
MATT: All right. Grog, you taking watch, you head
into the casino.

01:26:36.996 --> 01:26:40.115
SAM: Oh! Before I go in, hat of disguise on.

01:26:40.115 --> 01:26:44.775
MATT: What do you wish to look like?

01:26:44.775 --> 01:26:57.280
SAM: Adult human male. Goatee, pork pie hat, black
jacket. Just an ordinary man.

01:26:57.336 --> 01:26:59.537
LIAM: Yeah, Mr. Shorthalt! Yeah!

01:26:59.537 --> 01:27:02.082
TALIESIN: Is it Abbott or Costello? I'm not sure
which.

01:27:02.082 --> 01:27:07.154
MATT: And you walk into the Luck's Run. Being
midday, it's not as busy as the evening you saw

01:27:07.154 --> 01:27:12.534
previously but I'd say about half the tables are
still running and they have clientele throughout.

01:27:12.534 --> 01:27:18.336
SAM: I'm looking, in the interest of time, going
to look around for any of those two faces.

01:27:18.336 --> 01:27:21.002
MATT: Make a perception check.

01:27:21.002 --> 01:27:22.617
LIAM: That's bardic magic, bitch.

01:27:22.617 --> 01:27:23.940
SAM: Nine.

01:27:23.940 --> 01:27:31.413
MATT: You spend the better part of a half an hour
scoping through each floor. No sign.

01:27:31.413 --> 01:27:35.024
SAM: I didn't go into their office, though,
right?

01:27:35.024 --> 01:27:40.901
MATT: No. Through the bottom floor, and going up
and checking hallways. And the third floor, which

01:27:40.901 --> 01:27:46.172
you hadn't been before, which is more of a lounge
patio. It has more of the higher stakes games. You

01:27:46.172 --> 01:27:48.550
can see there are some more of the higher rollers
and--

01:27:48.550 --> 01:27:52.466
SAM: And can I make my way to the office area,
where they led me?

01:27:52.466 --> 01:27:54.169
MATT: Yeah. I mean, the door is closed.

01:27:54.169 --> 01:27:55.945
SAM: Can I listen outside?

01:27:55.945 --> 01:27:59.930
MATT: Yeah, you take a listen. Doesn't appear to
be any sound from the other side.

01:27:59.930 --> 01:28:00.825
SAM: Damn it.

01:28:00.825 --> 01:28:04.300
TRAVIS: Can I go to the corner where I can see the
front entrance and the side alley where I was and

01:28:04.300 --> 01:28:06.570
look and see if I see either of those two faces?

01:28:06.570 --> 01:28:08.301
MATT: Sure, make a perception check.

01:28:08.301 --> 01:28:11.505
TRAVIS: This will go well. Total shit. Six.

01:28:11.505 --> 01:28:14.943
MATT: Six. No sign of them.

01:28:14.943 --> 01:28:17.031
TRAVIS: Cool. I'm looking at the wall.

01:28:17.031 --> 01:28:19.456
SAM: Damn it. All right. I'll quickly Dimension
Door inside the office.

01:28:19.456 --> 01:28:26.364
MATT: (whoosh) Inside the office. Thankfully you
have your gnomish dark vision. It is dark in here,

01:28:26.364 --> 01:28:31.201
there are no lights. The table and chairs and the
general decor of the room seemingly untouched

01:28:31.201 --> 01:28:32.604
since last time you were in here.

01:28:32.604 --> 01:28:37.378
SAM: All right. Is there any source of light
around here?

01:28:37.378 --> 01:28:39.794
MATT: There are a couple of lanterns in the corner
that could be lit.

01:28:39.794 --> 01:28:41.078
SAM: I will light one.

01:28:41.078 --> 01:28:46.139
MATT: All right. (whoosh) You turn the lantern up.
Light glows.

01:28:46.139 --> 01:28:52.713
SAM: Going right into the desk, looking for
anything. Keys, gold, contraband, weapons.

01:28:52.713 --> 01:28:54.153
MATT: Investigation check.

01:28:54.153 --> 01:28:56.451
SAM: 23.

01:28:56.451 --> 01:29:09.800
MATT: 23. Scanning through you find the odd four
copper pieces. You find a couple of small books.

01:29:09.800 --> 01:29:15.739
One looks like it's on etiquette, and the other is
written in a language you don't understand. But

01:29:15.739 --> 01:29:25.555
you gather it's Marquesian. You do also find some
small notes-- like a little name that is drawn on

01:29:25.555 --> 01:29:29.982
the inside of one of the drawers. Looks old, like
it's been there for a long time, and says "Lelan."

01:29:29.982 --> 01:29:41.897
And you find-- that's about it. You get the sense
this isn't a stationary room that they use as a

01:29:41.897 --> 01:29:44.988
base of operations, it's almost like a rental
space used when people want to come in here and do

01:29:44.988 --> 01:29:48.354
business. Which happens often in a casino
establishment. They want to make sure that they

01:29:48.354 --> 01:29:52.569
provide their clientele with all the necessary
needs, and a lot of the rooms on this center floor

01:29:52.569 --> 01:29:57.814
are to facilitate the meetings between the top and
the bottom.

01:29:57.814 --> 01:30:01.084
SAM: Damn it. All right, I'll do one more
investigation check to see if there's any hidden

01:30:01.084 --> 01:30:04.574
compartments in the desk or around it.

01:30:04.574 --> 01:30:06.971
TRAVIS: Burn it to the ground.

01:30:06.971 --> 01:30:08.627
SAM: 24.

01:30:08.627 --> 01:30:16.367
MATT: 24. Nothing under the desks, but the table
that you're at, there is a small false bottom on

01:30:16.367 --> 01:30:23.597
each side. You pull it open and there is a single
dagger on each end. Apparently for those that

01:30:23.597 --> 01:30:29.622
know, they're provided as a means of defense in
case things in one of these meetings go wrong. But

01:30:29.622 --> 01:30:32.374
who knows who knows this information. It looks
like they haven't been used in a while.

01:30:32.374 --> 01:30:33.207
SAM: All right.

01:30:33.207 --> 01:30:35.206
TRAVIS: Can I look around and see if I see the two
faces now?

01:30:35.206 --> 01:30:37.913
MATT: Sure, make another perception check.

01:30:37.913 --> 01:30:40.034
TRAVIS: 18.

01:30:40.034 --> 01:30:41.550
MATT: Nope.

01:30:41.550 --> 01:30:50.773
SAM: All right, fine. I will take the daggers,
take the Marquesian book, whatever that was, take

01:30:50.773 --> 01:30:59.889
a huge dump on the desk, and take one of the
daggers and dig a big piece of it and write on the

01:30:59.889 --> 01:31:02.011
wall, "The Meat Man cometh."

01:31:02.011 --> 01:31:03.774
(laughing)

01:31:03.774 --> 01:31:07.803
TALIESIN: Wouldn't it be, "The Meat Man goeth?" Oh
well, never mind.

01:31:07.803 --> 01:31:09.804
SAM: And then I'll let myself out.

01:31:09.804 --> 01:31:18.121
MATT: Okay. You open the door. There are two
people walking through. They glance over at you

01:31:18.121 --> 01:31:23.331
and keep walking. You close the door behind you
and you have left your mark.

01:31:23.331 --> 01:31:27.070
SAM: Okay. On the way out of the casino do I see
any familiar faces?

01:31:27.070 --> 01:31:28.718
MATT: Make a perception check.

01:31:28.718 --> 01:31:29.836
SAM: 18!

01:31:29.836 --> 01:31:30.954
MATT: 18. Nah.

01:31:30.954 --> 01:31:32.101
SAM: Ah, fuck you!

01:31:32.101 --> 01:31:35.802
MATT: They seemingly know better than to return to
the scene of the crime.

01:31:35.802 --> 01:31:37.813
SAM: All right.

01:31:37.813 --> 01:31:44.864
MATT: For lesser folk, 400 gold can keep you going
for quite some time.

01:31:44.864 --> 01:31:47.208
TRAVIS: Put some money on red or black while
you're in there. Just once.

01:31:47.208 --> 01:31:50.193
SAM: All right.

01:31:50.193 --> 01:31:53.396
LAURA: You should try the dice game just once.

01:31:53.396 --> 01:31:54.944
SAM: The dice game?

01:31:54.944 --> 01:31:55.845
LAURA: Yeah.

01:31:55.845 --> 01:31:56.868
SAM: All right. Grog?

01:31:56.868 --> 01:31:57.848
TRAVIS: Yeah.

01:31:57.848 --> 01:32:00.244
SAM: Want to come in and play once with me?

01:32:00.244 --> 01:32:01.268
TRAVIS: No.

01:32:01.268 --> 01:32:02.437
SAM: Okay, great.

01:32:02.437 --> 01:32:04.606
(laughter)

01:32:04.606 --> 01:32:06.026
SAM: I'll do the dice game once.

01:32:06.026 --> 01:32:12.584
MATT: Okay, all right. So you walk in to the
table. There's three other individuals there. Hold

01:32:12.584 --> 01:32:17.585
on, let me get prepared here. Since this is the
first time we're really doing this here, which is

01:32:17.585 --> 01:32:20.156
kind of fun. All righty.

01:32:20.156 --> 01:32:21.670
TALIESIN: No, this is like, the third run.

01:32:21.670 --> 01:32:23.405
LAURA: Isn't this the seven or the twelve game?

01:32:23.405 --> 01:32:25.758
MATT: Oh, the dice game! Dice game, I'm sorry.

01:32:25.758 --> 01:32:28.364
SAM: What's the other game?

01:32:28.364 --> 01:32:32.806
MATT: Well the dice game's cool. There's the dice
game, the lizards, and the card game. Your call.

01:32:32.806 --> 01:32:34.177
MARISHA: What's the card game?

01:32:34.177 --> 01:32:35.354
MATT: Dice game is the 2d6--

01:32:35.354 --> 01:32:38.159
SAM: What's the fastest one? Let's do that one.

01:32:38.159 --> 01:32:39.990
MATT: The fastest one is the dice game. The card
game takes a little more time.

01:32:39.990 --> 01:32:41.298
SAM: Okay.

01:32:41.298 --> 01:32:46.262
MATT: All right, so. That is a 25 gold minimum buy
in for Avandra's Favor.

01:32:46.262 --> 01:32:48.160
TRAVIS: Even in the middle of the day, the
minimums don't go down?

01:32:48.160 --> 01:32:50.202
LAURA: I know, I feel like the minimums should go
down in the middle of the day.

01:32:50.202 --> 01:32:51.304
SAM: 50 gold.

01:32:51.304 --> 01:32:52.793
MATT: You've never been to Ank'Harel!

01:32:52.793 --> 01:32:54.688
SAM: 50 gold!

01:32:54.688 --> 01:32:56.172
TRAVIS: Well I've been to Harrah's!

01:32:56.172 --> 01:32:57.953
MATT: The minimums stay where they are.

01:32:57.953 --> 01:32:59.225
SAM: 50 gold.

01:32:59.225 --> 01:33:05.526
MATT: All right, you throw 50 gold down. As you
slap it down, still in your human guise, an

01:33:05.526 --> 01:33:12.718
individual to the left of you goes, "Whew. All
right. Big, strong opening and strong scent."

01:33:12.718 --> 01:33:17.485
Scoots over a bit to the right. Go ahead and roll
your dice.

01:33:17.485 --> 01:33:18.910
SAM: Six.

01:33:18.910 --> 01:33:19.939
MATT: Six.

01:33:19.939 --> 01:33:21.031
LAURA: Double down!

01:33:21.031 --> 01:33:23.195
MATT: He goes, "Mm. That's unfortunate."

01:33:23.195 --> 01:33:24.876
TALIESIN: Six is the double down, isn't it? Six is
the double down.

01:33:24.876 --> 01:33:25.806
LAURA: Yeah!

01:33:25.806 --> 01:33:28.865
MATT: "You can go ahead and double the price to
add an additional 1d6. You're going for seven or 12."

01:33:28.865 --> 01:33:30.556
SAM: Sure, yeah.

01:33:30.556 --> 01:33:31.963
TALIESIN: So roll one more die.

01:33:31.963 --> 01:33:34.681
MATT: "So 100 gold on the table. Roll one more
dice. You want a one--"

01:33:34.681 --> 01:33:36.173
MARISHA: --or a six.

01:33:36.173 --> 01:33:37.773
SAM: I got a five.

01:33:37.773 --> 01:33:38.882
MARISHA: Aww.

01:33:38.882 --> 01:33:43.673
MATT: "I am very sorry my friend." Shifts the coin
away. 100 gold down now.

01:33:43.673 --> 01:33:47.677
SAM: I just say: I hate this casino.

01:33:47.677 --> 01:33:49.561
(laughter)

01:33:49.561 --> 01:33:51.305
MATT: Any other games you want to play?

01:33:51.305 --> 01:34:02.500
SAM: No! No, I leave. Goddammit. Wait, what was
the names? The names that they gave me? The two

01:34:02.500 --> 01:34:04.226
guys gave me?

01:34:04.226 --> 01:34:06.007
MATT: Oh! Oh, right.

01:34:06.007 --> 01:34:07.177
SAM: Grug, or something.

01:34:07.177 --> 01:34:15.170
MATT: That was Rutur was the half orc. And I have
to go look up what the other one was.

01:34:15.170 --> 01:34:20.905
SAM: It's fine. I'll ask the dealer, or the dicer,
if he's seen Rutur around.

01:34:20.905 --> 01:34:23.602
MATT: He kind of--

01:34:23.602 --> 01:34:30.891
SAM: Jesus Christ. Five more gold.

01:34:30.891 --> 01:34:38.087
MATT: "Ah, yes. Rutur makes his way around here on
occasion. Every couple weeks, maybe."

01:34:38.087 --> 01:34:40.211
(laughter)

01:34:40.211 --> 01:34:43.169
LIAM: This city has had its way with you, Scanlan
Shorthalt.

01:34:43.169 --> 01:34:45.062
TALIESIN: You're never going to get a kiss.

01:34:45.062 --> 01:34:47.324
TRAVIS: Take your finger out of my asshole, Gary.

01:34:47.324 --> 01:34:50.679
MATT: "He doesn't seem to carry much change with
him."

01:34:50.679 --> 01:34:55.490
(laughter)

01:34:55.490 --> 01:34:59.172
SAM: Are you trying to do this to me on purpose?

01:34:59.172 --> 01:35:03.558
MATT: He looks at you strangely. "Hm?"

01:35:03.558 --> 01:35:06.272
LIAM: You talking to Matt?

01:35:06.272 --> 01:35:08.203
MATT: You keep coming back man, I don't know.

01:35:08.203 --> 01:35:10.629
SAM: Fine.

01:35:10.629 --> 01:35:13.827
TRAVIS: Do I see any half orcs outside?

01:35:13.827 --> 01:35:16.502
MATT: You do not at the moment.

01:35:16.502 --> 01:35:17.591
TRAVIS: Damn it.

01:35:17.591 --> 01:35:21.612
MATT: There is still Quon A Drensal or Gambit of
Ord if you're feeling lucky and you want to make

01:35:21.612 --> 01:35:22.571
your money back.

01:35:22.571 --> 01:35:33.042
SAM: Not in a million years, no! This place, it
sucks all my mojo. It's like the anti-mojo.

01:35:33.042 --> 01:35:37.641
TALIESIN: I feel a valuable lesson has finally
been learned, for the first time in this game.

01:35:37.641 --> 01:35:43.822
SAM: All right, I leave. And I go out and I say,
Grog, let's go home. But before we do, slap me in

01:35:43.822 --> 01:35:45.129
the face really hard.

01:35:45.129 --> 01:35:46.011
TRAVIS: You're sure?

01:35:46.011 --> 01:35:47.391
SAM: Yes, I need it. I need it.

01:35:47.391 --> 01:35:49.377
TRAVIS: Really hard. You want me to use the
gauntlets or no?

01:35:49.377 --> 01:35:50.176
SAM: No.

01:35:50.176 --> 01:35:52.111
LIAM: If he doesn't roll for damage then I'm going
to be offended.

01:35:52.111 --> 01:35:58.602
TRAVIS: All right, I take the Titanstone Knuckle
off my left hand and I slap him.

01:35:58.602 --> 01:36:02.479
MATT: All right. Go ahead and roll a strength
check.

01:36:02.479 --> 01:36:07.546
TRAVIS: 18.

01:36:07.546 --> 01:36:13.126
MATT: All right. You take five points of damage.

01:36:13.126 --> 01:36:18.188
TALIESIN: Is he still wearing the disguise? Is he
wearing the hat of disguise?

01:36:18.188 --> 01:36:19.277
SAM: Yes. Of course.

01:36:19.277 --> 01:36:20.172
MATT: He is.

01:36:20.172 --> 01:36:22.252
TALIESIN: So would his head not be, necessarily,
where his--

01:36:22.252 --> 01:36:27.474
MATT: That's true, and with Grog being not the one
who would remember that or recall that, he goes--

01:36:27.474 --> 01:36:31.993
SAM: I can't even get slapped in the face right!

01:36:31.993 --> 01:36:35.115
TALIESIN: I will ruin everything! I will ruin
everything!

01:36:35.115 --> 01:36:37.189
MATT: It's a valid point, thank you for
remembering.

01:36:37.189 --> 01:36:40.019
TRAVIS: I was so confused why a stranger would ask
me to slap him.

01:36:40.019 --> 01:36:44.107
(laughter)

01:36:44.107 --> 01:36:45.941
SAM: We go home.

01:36:45.941 --> 01:36:51.376
LIAM: Wait. So way faster than the casino trip,
while we've been waiting so long, Percival has

01:36:51.376 --> 01:36:55.498
been acting fucking twitchy since we found that
body so I walk over to him sitting off at a table.

01:36:55.498 --> 01:37:01.512
Hey, Mr. Cool-as-a-cucumber. Shush. Or come with
me, come have a seat.

01:37:01.512 --> 01:37:03.186
LAURA: Okay, all right, I'm here.

01:37:03.186 --> 01:37:09.400
LIAM: What's the matter? Yeah, it's her again.
We're going to find her. It's fine. You're huffing

01:37:09.400 --> 01:37:14.641
and hawing since we found her body. It's fine.
What's going on?

01:37:14.641 --> 01:37:26.517
TALIESIN: I was really hoping she was going to go
away. That's all. I was really hoping that she was

01:37:26.517 --> 01:37:28.116
just going to go away.

01:37:28.116 --> 01:37:30.459
LIAM: Well she's going to go away, Percival. If
not now, later.

01:37:30.459 --> 01:37:45.861
TALIESIN: Every second she's alive is untold
damage to the world. Do you know how every now and

01:37:45.861 --> 01:37:48.035
then I say something awful?

01:37:48.035 --> 01:37:49.398
LAURA: Mm-hmm.

01:37:49.398 --> 01:37:59.817
TALIESIN: I love you both very much for that. When
I think of that terrible person inside of me I see

01:37:59.817 --> 01:38:15.607
her face. She has a very active imagination. She
knows how to make these machines, and her

01:38:15.607 --> 01:38:31.512
imagination terrifies me. If you knew that that
was me, would you let me live? Has she made ten

01:38:31.512 --> 01:38:39.698
more of these things, has she made 100? Does she
hand them out to people? Maybe, I don't know,

01:38:39.698 --> 01:38:45.869
maybe she's running around and torturing people's
parents and siblings to death and then handing

01:38:45.869 --> 01:38:49.176
them a gun and kicking them out into the world to
see what will happen because it could be funny.

01:38:49.176 --> 01:38:55.031
LIAM: You're probably right, Percival. She
probably is. This is not Lord and Lady Briarwood

01:38:55.031 --> 01:38:56.495
over again, though.

01:38:56.495 --> 01:38:57.487
TALIESIN: No, it's not.

01:38:57.487 --> 01:38:58.859
LIAM: And you're not alone.

01:38:58.859 --> 01:38:59.905
TALIESIN: No, I'm not.

01:38:59.905 --> 01:39:04.601
LIAM: You have me, you have her. You have her. You
have the other two Laurel and Hardy motherfuckers

01:39:04.601 --> 01:39:05.631
who aren't back yet.

01:39:05.631 --> 01:39:07.417
TALIESIN: I was so hoping that maybe--

01:39:07.417 --> 01:39:11.811
MARISHA: I slam some mead in front of him.

01:39:11.811 --> 01:39:16.650
TALIESIN: Thank you. I was hoping something heavy
had fallen on her from a great height, saving the

01:39:16.650 --> 01:39:20.089
world a few thousand lives.

01:39:20.089 --> 01:39:25.030
LAURA: Well, we're going to be above her. Maybe we
can be the one to drop something heavy.

01:39:25.030 --> 01:39:26.956
TALIESIN: That's really what I'm hoping.

01:39:26.956 --> 01:39:29.928
MARISHA: Oh, I've been practicing that actually. I
can be really heavy.

01:39:29.928 --> 01:39:31.224
TALIESIN: That may help.

01:39:31.224 --> 01:39:31.975
MARISHA: Yeah.

01:39:31.975 --> 01:39:38.985
TALIESIN: She is the biggest mistake I've made,
and I'm horrified by who's paid the price.

01:39:38.985 --> 01:39:43.817
LIAM: All the more reason for you to be the same
cold-hearted asshole you've been for the last

01:39:43.817 --> 01:39:47.567
year. Why change now? Get the job done, Percival.

01:39:47.567 --> 01:39:49.675
TALIESIN: I'm counting to a hundred. I'll be
fine.

01:39:49.675 --> 01:39:52.989
MARISHA: It's not very often we see you shaky,
Percy.

01:39:52.989 --> 01:39:59.460
TALIESIN: Once we're out of here, I'll feel fine.
Once that thing is off my machine I will feel

01:39:59.460 --> 01:40:06.514
fine. And I'm thinking of something else. I'm
thinking of building something awful to help deal

01:40:06.514 --> 01:40:07.707
with her.

01:40:07.707 --> 01:40:13.681
MARISHA: Hang on. Wait. Hang on. I was about to
ask if you ever have regrets of building something

01:40:13.681 --> 01:40:18.550
awful and releasing it into this world, and now
you just said you're going to double down,

01:40:18.550 --> 01:40:19.752
essentially?

01:40:19.752 --> 01:40:26.993
TALIESIN: I've been thinking long and hard about
it. I think inevitably, anytime I think of

01:40:26.993 --> 01:40:33.854
something it might be too late. I think I'm going
to be very careful about what I build. I'm going

01:40:33.854 --> 01:40:41.745
to be very careful about where it goes, and I'm
also going to ask anybody, if-- when I die, destroy

01:40:41.745 --> 01:40:50.491
everything. Please. This is why I don't write down
notes. Any of my sketches, they're put away, and

01:40:50.491 --> 01:40:58.866
they're put in a place where I can remove them
once the job is done. But I sketch my idle

01:40:58.866 --> 01:41:04.569
thoughts, and right now I'm having an idle thought
for her and it's simple, it's nothing complicated,

01:41:04.569 --> 01:41:06.395
it's just vicious.

01:41:06.395 --> 01:41:11.658
LIAM: Well all right, we can do that. We can
destroy anything you make, but for now, Percy.

01:41:11.658 --> 01:41:14.499
Keep your head, man.

01:41:14.499 --> 01:41:16.266
TALIESIN: One night of sleep, I'll be there.

01:41:16.266 --> 01:41:22.164
MARISHA: What exactly are you thinking of making?
Just because we could destroy your notes, I mean,

01:41:22.164 --> 01:41:26.714
you're still alive and your guns still got into
the world.

01:41:26.714 --> 01:41:35.317
LAURA: Regardless of what he makes, who wields it?
Fenthras is a horrible weapon wielded by a

01:41:35.317 --> 01:41:40.784
horrible being before I had it. A gun can do the
same thing.

01:41:40.784 --> 01:41:45.784
MARISHA: You're arguably one of the greatest minds
in existence right now, Percival.

01:41:45.784 --> 01:41:47.688
TALIESIN: That's a terrible thought.

01:41:47.688 --> 01:41:52.270
MARISHA: But you are. And Vex isn't wrong.

01:41:52.270 --> 01:42:01.428
TALIESIN: I know. There are things that one day I
will speak of that I'm not really ready to deal

01:42:01.428 --> 01:42:06.605
with yet. But I think I may even have something
that could help us with the dragons. I have a

01:42:06.605 --> 01:42:10.797
thought. I'm going to work on it on our way to the
island.

01:42:10.797 --> 01:42:12.316
LIAM: Now I'm nervous.

01:42:12.316 --> 01:42:20.307
TALIESIN: It will be something that once the
dragons are felled I plan on destroying

01:42:20.307 --> 01:42:28.122
immediately after. And I think you'll be all right
with it when you see it, it's too complicated for

01:42:28.122 --> 01:42:32.767
any one person to really deal with. But I will
feel much better if she is in the ground.

01:42:32.767 --> 01:42:34.440
LAURA: Well I'm interested in seeing it.

01:42:34.440 --> 01:42:40.932
MARISHA: Percy. You know you can talk to us,
right? You never share ideas with us.

01:42:40.932 --> 01:42:45.784
TALIESIN: I do. I told you my idea of killing all
the dragonborn to start a war between the

01:42:45.784 --> 01:42:47.210
dragons.

01:42:47.210 --> 01:42:48.887
MARISHA: All right, well.

01:42:48.887 --> 01:42:51.255
TALIESIN: That's why I don't share those ideas,
I'm not proud of them.

01:42:51.255 --> 01:42:57.014
LAURA: Is this thing you're building going to kill
a lot of people in addition to the dragon?

01:42:57.014 --> 01:43:02.864
TALIESIN: I hope not, but it could. It could make
it very easy to kill a lot of people.

01:43:02.864 --> 01:43:08.851
LIAM: One day at a time, gang. Let's deal with
Ripley first.

01:43:08.851 --> 01:43:15.249
TALIESIN: Let's deal with Ripley. Let's collect a
few more things that will help us deal with home.

01:43:15.249 --> 01:43:25.681
Let's save home. And then I will spend some good
time undoing some of the damage that I've done. I

01:43:25.681 --> 01:43:27.991
should have killed her. I should have.

01:43:27.991 --> 01:43:37.408
MARISHA: You shouldn't feel regret about not
taking another person's life. It's a moment of

01:43:37.408 --> 01:43:38.746
humanity.

01:43:38.746 --> 01:43:43.633
TALIESIN: It wasn't. I was not being kind, I was
being selfish. I didn't kill her because the

01:43:43.633 --> 01:43:48.858
Briarwoods mattered more to me, even though I
knew that she was far more dangerous. That if

01:43:48.858 --> 01:43:56.424
they had escaped, the world would be darker, two
more vampires or whatever, but she was the genie

01:43:56.424 --> 01:44:05.603
and I knowingly and very willingly said, I'm fine
with that. And I knew at that moment, this was not

01:44:05.603 --> 01:44:10.904
a thought I had later, in my head, I went, she is
going to kill hundreds of people. And that's okay

01:44:10.904 --> 01:44:11.979
right now.

01:44:11.979 --> 01:44:18.995
LAURA: Percy, if you had stayed with her and let
the Briarwoods go, a god, a terrible god, would

01:44:18.995 --> 01:44:21.773
probably be loosed on the land right now. I
think you chose correctly.

01:44:21.773 --> 01:44:26.306
TALIESIN: I think I stumbled into the correct
answer, I'm not sure I chose correctly. I think I

01:44:26.306 --> 01:44:27.823
got lucky.

01:44:27.823 --> 01:44:33.897
MARISHA: Did you not want to kill her because in a
way you feel responsible for who she is?

01:44:33.897 --> 01:44:40.205
TALIESIN: Oh, I feel absolutely responsible for
inspiring a maniac, of course I do.

01:44:40.205 --> 01:44:45.436
LIAM: Look. We're going to help you get to her.
You're going to get her. You've got to let us in

01:44:45.436 --> 01:44:47.264
on it a bit, though, all right?

01:44:47.264 --> 01:44:52.751
TALIESIN: Once I have something drawn I'll show
you what it is. And I'll have something drawn by

01:44:52.751 --> 01:44:54.109
tomorrow. Something simple.

01:44:54.109 --> 01:44:55.188
LIAM: That's a promise?

01:44:55.188 --> 01:44:56.188
TALIESIN: That is absolutely a promise.

01:44:56.188 --> 01:45:00.531
MARISHA: Also I know you're really smart, but
we're smart too. Don't insult our intelligence by

01:45:00.531 --> 01:45:04.216
assuming we can't comprehend one of your ideas.

01:45:04.216 --> 01:45:10.484
TALIESIN: Oh no you'll comprehend it, and it's not
that I don't think you can comprehend it, I know

01:45:10.484 --> 01:45:14.942
you can, it's that I know what it says about me
that I even thought it.

01:45:14.942 --> 01:45:19.170
MARISHA: Percy. Percy.

01:45:19.170 --> 01:45:21.101
TALIESIN: You've been drinking.

01:45:21.101 --> 01:45:22.340
MARISHA: I have!

01:45:22.340 --> 01:45:27.828
LAURA: Oh, Keyleth! Really? Hold off of the
alcohol. We have a lot to do today.

01:45:27.828 --> 01:45:30.499
MARISHA: We've been through so much!

01:45:30.499 --> 01:45:34.893
LIAM: I think my point has been made. I start
moving Keyleth towards that door for some fresh air.

01:45:34.893 --> 01:45:36.758
LAURA: Please, get her some fresh air.

01:45:36.758 --> 01:45:38.186
MARISHA: I want more mead!

01:45:38.186 --> 01:45:39.241
LIAM: Come on.

01:45:39.241 --> 01:45:40.518
TALIESIN: I'm sorry I'm an idiot.

01:45:40.518 --> 01:45:42.681
MARISHA: I love you, but I hate you, but I love
you.

01:45:42.681 --> 01:45:43.952
LAURA: Percy.

01:45:43.952 --> 01:45:45.705
TALIESIN: I'm fond of you as well. Yes, dear.

01:45:45.705 --> 01:45:47.270
LAURA: You're a better man than you believe.

01:45:47.270 --> 01:45:58.336
TALIESIN: Thank you. I accept that compliment. You
as well, you are a better woman than you believe.

01:45:58.336 --> 01:46:01.269
Doesn't feel good, does it? There you are.

01:46:01.269 --> 01:46:02.907
LAURA: No, it doesn't. Shit.

01:46:02.907 --> 01:46:05.110
TALIESIN: That's what you get for saying things
like that. Terrible person.

01:46:05.110 --> 01:46:07.640
LIAM: Thought for a second you also had one ball.

01:46:07.640 --> 01:46:12.795
MATT: All right. So your companions arrive.

01:46:12.795 --> 01:46:14.007
TRAVIS: We're back!

01:46:14.007 --> 01:46:18.580
SAM: We're back. Good news, Grog sweet-talked them
into giving us an airship for free.

01:46:18.580 --> 01:46:19.949
LIAM: No shit, Grog!

01:46:19.949 --> 01:46:21.213
SAM: Grog did the whole thing himself.

01:46:21.213 --> 01:46:22.063
LAURA: Wait, what?!

01:46:22.063 --> 01:46:22.873
LIAM: How did you do it?

01:46:22.873 --> 01:46:29.623
TRAVIS: Well, it's a very intricate and detailed
process. Involves a lot of-- you know what? It'll

01:46:29.623 --> 01:46:33.002
be all over your heads, so just say thank you.

01:46:33.002 --> 01:46:36.008
SAM: Let's just say that he's a good reader of
body language.

01:46:36.008 --> 01:46:37.446
LAURA: What the fuck did you do? Did you really?

01:46:37.446 --> 01:46:39.254
SAM: We got an airship for free.

01:46:39.254 --> 01:46:40.532
LIAM: Who's excited now?

01:46:40.532 --> 01:46:42.965
TALIESIN: I'm very excited, that's the best thing
I've heard all day.

01:46:42.965 --> 01:46:44.321
LAURA: Did you steal it? Tell me you didn't do
anything--

01:46:44.321 --> 01:46:50.462
SAM: We did nothing illegal. And to sweeten the
deal, Captain Damon will be our Damon pilot.

01:46:50.462 --> 01:46:52.572
TALIESIN: That Captain Damon.

01:46:52.572 --> 01:46:54.088
TRAVIS: "Our Damon pilot."

01:46:54.088 --> 01:46:59.055
MARISHA: Did you tell him we were the ones with
the wyverns? Because that's what I would have told

01:46:59.055 --> 01:47:02.179
him. Had I been there, theoretically.

01:47:02.179 --> 01:47:04.746
SAM: That thought popped right into my head.

01:47:04.746 --> 01:47:06.004
MARISHA: Really? Okay.

01:47:06.004 --> 01:47:12.574
SAM: And on the way back I won back the 50 gold I
lost on the fusaka.

01:47:12.574 --> 01:47:13.474
TRAVIS: You did!

01:47:13.474 --> 01:47:14.339
SAM: Yeah, yep.

01:47:14.339 --> 01:47:15.416
TALIESIN: Well done!

01:47:15.416 --> 01:47:18.711
SAM: So I'm going to leave Marquet totally
evens.

01:47:18.711 --> 01:47:20.972
LAURA: That's great!

01:47:20.972 --> 01:47:21.911
TALIESIN: That's amazing.

01:47:21.911 --> 01:47:23.067
SAM: Yup, pretty good.

01:47:23.067 --> 01:47:24.055
TALIESIN: I wish I could say that.

01:47:24.055 --> 01:47:25.192
LIAM: Oh cheers to that, cheers.

01:47:25.192 --> 01:47:30.380
SAM: Still batting a thousand, this guy. Unstoppable
me!

01:47:30.380 --> 01:47:33.078
TRAVIS: Now we can leave whenever we're ready.

01:47:33.078 --> 01:47:34.596
SAM: Oh, yeah, let's pack our bags.

01:47:34.596 --> 01:47:35.520
LAURA: Right now?

01:47:35.520 --> 01:47:37.086
SAM: Oh, wait no, we still have to de-curse the
thing.

01:47:37.086 --> 01:47:38.736
LAURA: Oh the enchantment! Right. We're waiting on
that, that's why we're fucking here.

01:47:38.736 --> 01:47:42.129
MATT: You guys go back down to the main area?

01:47:42.129 --> 01:47:43.379
LIAM: So many things.

01:47:43.379 --> 01:47:48.126
LAURA: Shall we bring the weapon down there?

01:47:48.126 --> 01:47:49.579
LIAM: That seems like a bad idea.

01:47:49.579 --> 01:47:51.601
TALIESIN: Once they're here. Actually, yes, why
not?

01:47:51.601 --> 01:47:54.511
LAURA: Yay, then Trinket's with us again.

01:47:54.511 --> 01:47:59.388
MATT: Yes. All so you guys head back down to the
main thoroughfare, or the main area of the

01:47:59.388 --> 01:48:00.884
tavern?

01:48:00.884 --> 01:48:01.957
TRAVIS: Yeah.

01:48:01.957 --> 01:48:09.861
MATT: There you see the same folks are there. You
see Treev is there, and you see a shifty-looking

01:48:09.861 --> 01:48:19.709
guy. A rather pointed nose, very shallow features.
And his hands are together, he has a satchel over

01:48:19.709 --> 01:48:25.272
his shoulder, and these long, plain looking robes.
And his thinning, short, dark hair is slicked

01:48:25.272 --> 01:48:30.820
against his skull. He has a thin mustache goatee
right there, and he's sitting at the edge of the

01:48:30.820 --> 01:48:32.186
bar, talking to Treev.

01:48:32.186 --> 01:48:33.732
LAURA: So he looks totally trustworthy.

01:48:33.732 --> 01:48:34.990
MATT: Totally trustworthy.

01:48:34.990 --> 01:48:36.971
MATT: As soon as you guys walk down the stairs--

01:48:36.971 --> 01:48:39.663
LIAM: Is he that picture of you on the carousel?

01:48:39.663 --> 01:48:42.271
MATT: Basically yes, but with the shorter slicked
hair.

01:48:42.271 --> 01:48:44.780
TALIESIN: I'm glad that's a thing again. I really
missed that.

01:48:44.780 --> 01:48:48.708
MATT: I don't know how to take that actually,
based on how I just described the NPC.

01:48:48.708 --> 01:48:50.836
LIAM: It's more the grimace.

01:48:50.836 --> 01:48:54.604
TALIESIN: I suddenly can hear thousands of Twitch
viewers Googling. Googling like mad!

01:48:54.604 --> 01:48:55.922
MATT: Noted.

01:48:55.922 --> 01:48:57.783
LIAM: Whoops. "And then Vax died."

01:48:57.783 --> 01:49:04.504
MATT: Disadvantage for the rest of the episode.
No. Treev goes, "Oh and here they are, the ones

01:49:04.504 --> 01:49:12.685
"who hired your help. Folks, I'd like to introduce
you to Kyme, he's one of our fine allies in the

01:49:12.685 --> 01:49:19.356
"Omnival Library here in the city, and I believe he
can take care of your little problem. So talk."

01:49:19.356 --> 01:49:27.881
And the guy spins around on the stool at the edge
of the bar, and goes, "Okay, so I have been told

01:49:27.881 --> 01:49:39.328
"that you require some sort of disenchantment
type thing. Who am I talking to here? There's a

01:49:39.453 --> 01:49:43.552
"lot of you. You? Okay, come."

01:49:43.552 --> 01:49:52.151
TALIESIN: All right. I have an object-- so
hard to talk to that face.

01:49:52.151 --> 01:49:56.450
LAURA: Scanlan. He seems like the type, you might
want to try selling him some of that fusaka.

01:49:56.450 --> 01:50:00.853
TALIESIN: I have an object that I own that someone
is tracking me with. They are aware of my

01:50:00.853 --> 01:50:05.038
whereabouts, they've put some kind of enchantment
on it. I was wondering if I could transfer that

01:50:05.038 --> 01:50:10.107
enchantment to another object, and send it in a
different direction so that they don't know that we're

01:50:10.107 --> 01:50:11.902
following them.

01:50:11.902 --> 01:50:14.459
MATT: "That's possible, yes."

01:50:14.459 --> 01:50:19.060
TALIESIN: I would even be willing, if possible, to
remove part of the object that I currently own,

01:50:19.060 --> 01:50:21.970
and then replace it with something else if
necessary.

01:50:21.970 --> 01:50:27.536
MATT: "Depending on the strength of the
enchantment, that can take anywhere within the

01:50:27.536 --> 01:50:29.570
"next few weeks."

01:50:29.570 --> 01:50:31.369
TALIESIN: Can I get you a drink? Are you all
right?

01:50:31.369 --> 01:50:33.574
MATT: "Why? Why do you ask?"

01:50:33.574 --> 01:50:34.692
LAURA: Can I insight check him?

01:50:34.692 --> 01:50:35.818
MATT: Make an insight check, yeah.

01:50:35.818 --> 01:50:38.424
LIAM: Yay.

01:50:38.424 --> 01:50:47.271
SAM: May I make a physiological check of his mouth
shape? His jaw seems--

01:50:47.271 --> 01:50:49.715
LIAM: New Matt character!

01:50:49.715 --> 01:50:51.528
TALIESIN: I know.

01:50:51.528 --> 01:50:54.355
LAURA: 19.

01:50:54.355 --> 01:50:56.134
MATT: 19.

01:50:56.134 --> 01:51:01.810
SAM: You know at shop.geekandsundry.com, there's a
lot of new items up for sale.

01:51:01.810 --> 01:51:02.942
MARISHA: That's true.

01:51:02.942 --> 01:51:04.094
TALIESIN: There's the mug.

01:51:04.094 --> 01:51:06.116
LIAM: Do they have the model airship yet?

01:51:06.116 --> 01:51:07.568
SAM: There's the mug, there's rings, patches.
What?

01:51:07.568 --> 01:51:08.683
LIAM: The model airship?

01:51:08.683 --> 01:51:16.687
SAM: The model airship, it's life-sized. Nail wraps
by Espionage Cosmetics, only 12 dollars. And don't

01:51:16.687 --> 01:51:21.508
forget, one week left on pre-orders for those
silicon bracelets and the enamel pins guys.

01:51:21.508 --> 01:51:23.138
MATT: All righty.

01:51:23.138 --> 01:51:25.214
SAM: Backblaze!

01:51:25.214 --> 01:51:31.760
TALIESIN: So I'm going to show him the gun, and
I'm going to say, what do you think? And I'm going

01:51:31.760 --> 01:51:33.307
to show him where the enchantment is.

01:51:33.307 --> 01:51:35.164
SAM: You're showing him the gun? We just said
don't show people the gun.

01:51:35.164 --> 01:51:36.853
LAURA: We need to remove the enchantment from it.

01:51:36.853 --> 01:51:37.670
SAM: Okay.

01:51:37.670 --> 01:51:41.719
LAURA: If we can remove the enchantment, if it
takes a long time to transfer, maybe you can keep

01:51:41.719 --> 01:51:44.253
transferring it after we've left? Is that a
thing?

01:51:44.253 --> 01:51:52.631
MATT: "I can get rid of the enchantment
immediately, but it's gone. Transfer, that's a

01:51:52.631 --> 01:51:58.785
"time-taking process, it's much more expensive than
what I was promised as part of this contract."

01:51:58.785 --> 01:52:04.084
Looks back to Treev. Treev's leaning back and he's
like, "I just brought you here to talk with them."

01:52:04.084 --> 01:52:13.115
TALIESIN: We just want to know our options, sir, and time is
sadly of the essence. What can you tell us about this?

01:52:13.115 --> 01:52:19.275
MATT: "Strange construction."

01:52:19.275 --> 01:52:21.544
TALIESIN: Yes.

01:52:21.544 --> 01:52:33.404
MATT: "Ah. I see what you're talking about." He
starts glancing-- shut up!-- Glancing at the

01:52:33.404 --> 01:52:47.176
bottom of Retort. "It is a variation on a scrying
enchantment, with a hint of a message-type base.

01:52:47.176 --> 01:52:50.074
"It's audio only, not visual."

01:52:50.074 --> 01:52:52.065
MARISHA: Son of a bitch!

01:52:52.065 --> 01:52:54.727
TALIESIN: Can they track where we are?

01:52:54.727 --> 01:53:04.139
MATT: "They cannot track location, but this is a
joint enchantment, there are two pieces to this.

01:53:04.139 --> 01:53:11.892
"And it would appear that, wherever the receiving
end is, they can probably hear everything around it."

01:53:11.892 --> 01:53:16.674
MARISHA: Guys, this could be a gift, think of the
possibilities.

01:53:16.674 --> 01:53:18.284
TRAVIS: She's hearing this right now.

01:53:18.284 --> 01:53:19.442
SAM: If she's listening.

01:53:19.442 --> 01:53:23.454
MATT: "Oh, I'm sure whoever has the other side of
this enchantment is now well aware of everything

01:53:23.454 --> 01:53:24.910
"we've just discussed."

01:53:24.910 --> 01:53:26.044
LAURA: Great.

01:53:26.044 --> 01:53:27.392
SAM: Maybe we should take it out of the room.

01:53:27.392 --> 01:53:28.725
TALIESIN: Shh, no.

01:53:28.725 --> 01:53:32.995
MATT: "Who has the other side of this enchantment
by the way?" And he suddenly looks extremely

01:53:32.995 --> 01:53:35.877
nervous. Beads of sweat start showing up on his
forehead.

01:53:35.877 --> 01:53:42.980
TALIESIN: I'll tell you what. You do the work
quickly, you do the work well, and you follow a

01:53:42.980 --> 01:53:47.550
few other instructions of ours, and I will not say
her name out loud right now. How does that sound

01:53:47.550 --> 01:53:48.751
to you?

01:53:48.751 --> 01:53:52.728
MATT: What do you want? Disenchantment,
transference, tell me.

01:53:52.728 --> 01:54:01.179
TALIESIN: Not anymore, we just want the
enchantment destroyed. And I will not say her

01:54:01.179 --> 01:54:05.576
name, so that she will know that you do not know
who she is.

01:54:05.576 --> 01:54:09.107
MATT: What does that mean? What does that mean?
What's he saying? What is he saying?

01:54:09.107 --> 01:54:10.660
SAM: For your own protection.

01:54:10.660 --> 01:54:19.236
TALIESIN: This is me, giving you a deal, good sir.
This is me, showing you respect. And you, if you

01:54:19.236 --> 01:54:27.346
can hear me, and I get the sneaking suspicion you
can, I'm not ignoring you anymore.

01:54:27.346 --> 01:54:40.042
SAM: Wait, before you do, a quick word, is there a
way to reverse the direction? Okay.

01:54:40.042 --> 01:54:50.374
MATT: Reaches into a little pouch of components on
the side. Takes things, crushes them, sprinkles

01:54:50.374 --> 01:54:57.728
them on. Looks about. "Ahem, it's done, it's gone,
here."

01:54:57.728 --> 01:55:00.289
LAURA: What?! Really?

01:55:00.289 --> 01:55:02.047
MARISHA: Can I check it?

01:55:02.047 --> 01:55:02.941
MATT: Yeah.

01:55:02.941 --> 01:55:04.246
MARISHA: Scanlan, help me check this.

01:55:04.246 --> 01:55:05.247
LAURA: That fast?

01:55:05.247 --> 01:55:06.147
SAM: All right.

01:55:06.147 --> 01:55:07.669
LAURA: You are very powerful, you.

01:55:07.669 --> 01:55:10.243
MARISHA: What do we do here?

01:55:10.243 --> 01:55:11.715
MATT: Make an arcana check.

01:55:11.715 --> 01:55:12.702
MARISHA: Scanlan, help.

01:55:12.702 --> 01:55:15.709
SAM: Yeah, I got a natural one, sister.

01:55:15.709 --> 01:55:17.632
MARISHA: Oh boy. 16.

01:55:17.632 --> 01:55:25.050
MATT: As you're staring at it, you watch as the
Ripley signature that's very, very small, put in

01:55:25.050 --> 01:55:30.807
the bottom of the piece of whitestone, begins to
glow. Suddenly, he goes, "By the way, it takes a

01:55:30.807 --> 01:55:38.919
"moment. Put your face away please!" And as you
pull it back, it flashes, and then goes dark

01:55:38.919 --> 01:55:42.670
again. "And... now it's done."

01:55:42.670 --> 01:55:45.990
MARISHA: Okay, I'll look at it again. What does it
look like?

01:55:45.990 --> 01:55:47.346
MATT: Looks the same.

01:55:47.346 --> 01:55:48.750
MARISHA: What do you mean it looks the same?

01:55:48.750 --> 01:55:53.182
MATT: Meaning like, the signature's still there,
the stone is still there, but that slight essence

01:55:53.182 --> 01:55:55.979
of slight enchantment that was there before is
gone.

01:55:55.979 --> 01:56:01.442
TALIESIN: You wouldn't happen to know where to get
some construction materials on very quick notice?

01:56:01.442 --> 01:56:04.760
MATT: "No!"

01:56:04.760 --> 01:56:06.847
LAURA: You wouldn't be able to identify something
for me, would you?

01:56:06.847 --> 01:56:08.584
TALIESIN: Oh yes, go ahead, do that.

01:56:08.584 --> 01:56:11.104
LAURA: You seem so smart, is all.

01:56:11.104 --> 01:56:14.376
MATT: "This was not part of the agreement."

01:56:14.376 --> 01:56:17.133
LAURA: Darling, we're already here, please?

01:56:17.133 --> 01:56:18.702
TALIESIN: And we didn't say your name.

01:56:18.702 --> 01:56:20.022
MATT: Make a persuasion check.

01:56:20.022 --> 01:56:21.505
MARISHA: "And we didn't say your name."

01:56:21.505 --> 01:56:26.157
LAURA: Oh, damn it. I will pay you.

01:56:26.157 --> 01:56:29.630
MATT: "How much?"

01:56:29.630 --> 01:56:31.928
LAURA: How much do you want?

01:56:31.928 --> 01:56:36.661
MATT: Looks back at Treev. Treev goes--

01:56:36.661 --> 01:56:38.583
LAURA: Just to identify something, that's all
dear.

01:56:38.583 --> 01:56:39.758
TALIESIN: Something simple.

01:56:39.758 --> 01:56:42.504
MATT: "100 gold, please."

01:56:42.504 --> 01:56:52.731
LAURA: 100 gold. Darling. It seemed effortless for
you to do that before. Is it hard?

01:56:52.731 --> 01:56:54.679
MATT: "I have a shop to get back to. I'm sorry, I
can't be here any longer."

01:56:54.679 --> 01:56:55.747
LAURA: Fine, fine.

01:56:55.747 --> 01:56:56.860
MATT: And he gets up from the stool.

01:56:56.860 --> 01:57:01.646
LAURA: Shit! Fine. A hundred gold, whatever. I
just want to know, can you look at this please?

01:57:01.646 --> 01:57:08.255
It's a tea set, it's gold. Isn't it beautiful?

01:57:08.255 --> 01:57:13.972
MATT: Takes it from you and his hands are clammy,
as he pulls it out of your grasp. And he looks

01:57:13.972 --> 01:57:18.417
over the tea set, and it's in his hands, he
doesn't really know what to do with it. And he

01:57:18.417 --> 01:57:29.680
places it on the side. "Okay." Begins breathing
heavily, and it's fogging the side of the metallic

01:57:29.680 --> 01:57:34.079
tea set. And you see this sweat dripping off of
his nose. He's still very nervous about this

01:57:34.079 --> 01:57:42.573
endeavor and wants to get out of here as soon as
possible. "All right, this is a tea set of

01:57:42.573 --> 01:57:50.501
"envenoming. Whenever you produce some sort of a
liquid imbibement within the tea set, it's

01:57:50.501 --> 01:57:54.041
"guaranteed to be a bad day for whoever drinks from
it."

01:57:54.041 --> 01:57:56.111
LAURA: It's so good we didn't drink from it.

01:57:56.111 --> 01:57:59.929
TALIESIN: Does the liquid hold its potency or is
it just within the tea set?

01:57:59.929 --> 01:58:01.069
MATT: "For a day."

01:58:01.069 --> 01:58:02.109
TALIESIN: Good to know.

01:58:02.109 --> 01:58:02.939
LAURA: Lovely.

01:58:02.939 --> 01:58:03.696
TALIESIN: Excellent.

01:58:03.696 --> 01:58:04.845
SAM: Will someone die?

01:58:04.845 --> 01:58:09.107
MATT: "I'm not a master of poisons, I just know
that it poisons."

01:58:09.107 --> 01:58:10.571
LAURA: Thank you so much.

01:58:10.571 --> 01:58:14.656
MATT: And he takes it and holds it, and is like,
"100 gold."

01:58:14.656 --> 01:58:16.101
LAURA: Of course dear.

01:58:16.101 --> 01:58:21.376
MATT: "Thank you." And as soon as he gets it, he
lets go of it, puts it in his pouch. "And good

01:58:21.376 --> 01:58:29.783
"day. Treev, careful next time." And he darts off,
outside. Bursting through the door and into the

01:58:29.783 --> 01:58:32.312
alley. And Treev sits.

01:58:32.312 --> 01:58:37.617
TALIESIN: I was imagining the FBI agent from The
Frighteners, I was having a lot of that.

01:58:37.617 --> 01:58:42.251
MARISHA: I was imagining The Creep music video from
Lonely Island.

01:58:42.251 --> 01:58:54.058
MATT: Kind of. Yeah, actually. Treev is like, "Now
that was fun to watch."

01:58:54.058 --> 01:58:55.278
LAURA: That guy was weird.

01:58:55.278 --> 01:59:00.616
MATT: "He's a weird one. I knew he'd do the job,
but honestly I like watching him twitch."

01:59:00.616 --> 01:59:08.839
TALIESIN: Thank you, that was very helpful. That
was very helpful. They don't know that we're

01:59:08.839 --> 01:59:13.329
coming as they don't know how we're going or why,
because we have spoken all of that outside of the

01:59:13.329 --> 01:59:15.920
range of that device. They don't know any of
that.

01:59:15.920 --> 01:59:17.413
MARISHA: True, the gun was in the other room.

01:59:17.413 --> 01:59:21.863
TALIESIN: All they know is that we found the
enchantment and killed it.

01:59:21.863 --> 01:59:23.257
LIAM: Should we melt it just in case?

01:59:23.257 --> 01:59:37.041
TALIESIN: No. There will be no more melting of my
property for a little while yet. I have a bit of a

01:59:37.041 --> 01:59:44.110
quick shopping list before we head out of town. I
was wondering if it would be possible to gather

01:59:44.110 --> 01:59:48.821
some quick supplies, if some of your people knew
where to get simple construction materials,

01:59:48.821 --> 01:59:50.369
quickly. Today.

01:59:50.369 --> 01:59:52.241
LAURA: And potions of healing.

01:59:52.241 --> 01:59:58.658
MATT: "Potions, head to the Suncut Bazaar. I'm
sure you could find a few folks. We usually get ours

01:59:58.658 --> 02:00:02.665
"from--" And he starts looking through a list, he
goes, "Let's see, there's--"

02:00:02.665 --> 02:00:05.163
LIAM: Are we staying here for the night before
heading out in the morning?

02:00:05.163 --> 02:00:06.103
TRAVIS and TALIESIN: No.

02:00:06.103 --> 02:00:07.153
LIAM: So we're sleeping on the ship?

02:00:07.153 --> 02:00:08.190
TRAVIS and TALIESIN: Yes.

02:00:08.190 --> 02:00:10.649
MATT: "Nisaba are the two I know of, at least."

02:00:10.649 --> 02:00:11.846
LAURA: Saaba and what?

02:00:11.846 --> 02:00:14.290
MATT: "Usar and Nisaba."

02:00:14.290 --> 02:00:18.853
LAURA: They'll give a good deal?

02:00:18.853 --> 02:00:22.115
MATT: "Perhaps. You ask them nicely."

02:00:22.115 --> 02:00:31.632
TALIESIN: I need lumber, steel, lead, and a couple
other things. Very simple. Just some materials.

02:00:31.632 --> 02:00:35.460
I'll show you what I'm building and I'll have you
figure out the number.

02:00:35.460 --> 02:00:38.888
MATT: "Right."

02:00:38.888 --> 02:00:43.185
TALIESIN: Loaded straight on the ship.

02:00:43.185 --> 02:00:49.795
MATT: "What you're looking for is the Bone Garden.
It's the northernmost side of the Suncut Bazaar.

02:00:49.795 --> 02:00:59.043
"They deal with a lot of the not guild-run sales
of various construction means. More for the

02:00:59.043 --> 02:01:01.188
"residential folk here in Ank'Harel."

02:01:01.188 --> 02:01:02.584
TALIESIN: That'll do.

02:01:02.584 --> 02:01:08.842
MATT: For the sake of brevity, what are you
searching for?

02:01:08.842 --> 02:01:19.847
TALIESIN: I'm trying to get enough construction
material to build a very basic 125-pound mountable

02:01:19.847 --> 02:01:25.736
cannon that I can move around the ship on wheels,
and a little bit of shot for a cannon, about five

02:01:25.736 --> 02:01:30.685
pound shot. It's simple, but it's going to be a
son of a bitch.

02:01:30.685 --> 02:01:35.508
MATT: There are cannons made. That technology--

02:01:35.508 --> 02:01:41.241
TALIESIN: --does exist. But does something that
small that can move around a ship exist? This

02:01:41.241 --> 02:01:46.688
would be something that four people could pick up
and move around.

02:01:46.688 --> 02:01:59.876
MATT: That small? The few things they have here,
they're magically-based fire. It's similar to the

02:01:59.876 --> 02:02:09.956
dragon arbalist installation. It's not so much a
gunpowder-based explosion, since that is mostly

02:02:09.956 --> 02:02:17.977
unutilized. This is a metal tube that contains an
enchantment that throws out bursts of energy. You

02:02:17.977 --> 02:02:21.440
could purchase a base for one of those
constructs. That would cut down the time

02:02:21.479 --> 02:02:26.557
because if you're going to make a cannon, that's
going to be an endeavor, that'll take you a long time.

02:02:26.557 --> 02:02:32.739
TALIESIN: A base will do, and I need to build a
thing to build cannonballs.

02:02:32.739 --> 02:02:40.697
MATT: Takes you the better part of the day to even
find out, asking around because Treev doesn't know

02:02:40.697 --> 02:02:45.742
anything about where to find the base for a cannon
like that. Takes you the better part of the rest

02:02:45.742 --> 02:02:49.873
of the day, pushing into dusk, for you to find out where
that could be purchased. That's going to run you

02:02:49.908 --> 02:02:52.486
about 60 gold.

02:02:52.486 --> 02:02:54.724
TALIESIN: I'm good with that.

02:02:54.724 --> 02:02:56.222
MATT: It's not enchanted.

02:02:56.222 --> 02:03:04.701
TALIESIN: 60 gold and then a little extra to make
cannonballs and otherwise. Get them to deliver it

02:03:04.701 --> 02:03:08.201
to the ship and I'm sending everything to be
delivered immediately to the ship.

02:03:08.201 --> 02:03:12.236
MATT: Anything else anyone wants to prepare?

02:03:12.236 --> 02:03:14.866
LAURA: Potions. I need healing potions. Who needs
healing potions?

02:03:14.866 --> 02:03:15.790
SAM: All of us.

02:03:15.790 --> 02:03:16.763
TALIESIN: Everybody.

02:03:16.763 --> 02:03:17.877
MARISHA: Sure.

02:03:17.877 --> 02:03:23.382
MATT: On street-level sales, asking around, the
most you can acquire are probably any number of

02:03:23.382 --> 02:03:33.571
common, regular healing potions you may want.
Through conversations, at most five of the greater

02:03:33.571 --> 02:03:35.193
can be purchased.

02:03:35.193 --> 02:03:37.609
LAURA: Okay. Scanlan, can you come with me?

02:03:37.609 --> 02:03:38.912
SAM: Yes.

02:03:38.912 --> 02:03:41.594
LAURA: Can we find a Hand of Ord?

02:03:41.594 --> 02:03:46.799
MATT: Yeah, not too hard to find at all. Quick
look around, a Hand of Ord, especially here in the

02:03:46.799 --> 02:03:47.827
market.

02:03:47.827 --> 02:03:49.762
SAM: Flash the thing? What am I flashing it for?

02:03:49.762 --> 02:03:51.168
LAURA: I want to talk to him.

02:03:51.168 --> 02:03:52.537
LIAM: Get the cube out.

02:03:52.537 --> 02:03:59.616
SAM: Oi, mate. We're friends with J'mon Sa Ord.

02:03:59.616 --> 02:04:05.398
LAURA: We're not making a street deal right now.

02:04:05.398 --> 02:04:07.743
SAM: Oh! I thought everything was here.

02:04:07.743 --> 02:04:11.953
TALIESIN: This could be part of your problem here.

02:04:11.953 --> 02:04:14.758
MATT: He bends down after giving you a weird
eyebrow.

02:04:14.758 --> 02:04:16.961
SAM: I'm a normal, human man.

02:04:16.961 --> 02:04:19.692
MATT: You're still in your--

02:04:19.692 --> 02:04:21.332
SAM: I forgot to take it off.

02:04:21.332 --> 02:04:30.929
MATT: So you're a normal, human man in non-Ank'Harel
attire. Shows off the necklace. He looks at it.

02:04:30.929 --> 02:04:34.842
"How did you come about that?"

02:04:34.842 --> 02:04:40.523
LAURA: We met with J'mon Sa Ord earlier. We have
their blessing.

02:04:40.523 --> 02:04:43.294
MATT: Make a persuasion check.

02:04:43.294 --> 02:04:47.908
LAURA: 18.

02:04:47.908 --> 02:04:49.470
MATT: 18 total?

02:04:49.470 --> 02:04:50.418
LAURA: Yeah.

02:04:50.418 --> 02:04:54.326
MATT: He goes, "Okay, what can I be of service to
you?"

02:04:54.326 --> 02:05:00.200
LAURA: We're in need of some healing potions. I'm
assuming, as a guard of the city, you have access

02:05:00.200 --> 02:05:01.809
to quite a few?

02:05:01.809 --> 02:05:06.432
MATT: "Could probably muster a few from the
barracks, yes."

02:05:06.432 --> 02:05:10.382
LAURA: Some greater healing potions would be
wonderful.

02:05:10.382 --> 02:05:16.954
MATT: "I'll get what we can spare. We still have to
keep enough to maintain our watch."

02:05:16.954 --> 02:05:18.876
LAURA: Of course.

02:05:18.876 --> 02:05:21.776
MATT: "Wait here. Give me a half-hour."

02:05:21.776 --> 02:05:23.629
SAM: Okay.

02:05:23.629 --> 02:05:28.627
MATT: You guys wait for him and he comes back with
six regular healing potions and three greater.

02:05:28.627 --> 02:05:34.960
SAM: This thing is the best thing ever! I'm not
holding anything but it's still cool!

02:05:34.960 --> 02:05:37.245
(laughter)

02:05:37.245 --> 02:05:39.398
LAURA: Six regular?

02:05:39.398 --> 02:05:42.264
TRAVIS: And three greater.

02:05:42.264 --> 02:05:47.002
MATT: "This is what we can spare from the nearby
barracks."

02:05:47.002 --> 02:05:50.205
LAURA: Thank you so much. Your aid is
appreciated.

02:05:50.205 --> 02:05:54.308
MATT: "If I could have your names, just to be safe
that everything is--"

02:05:54.308 --> 02:05:56.975
LAURA: Be pleased. Vox Machina.

02:05:56.975 --> 02:05:59.127
MATT: "Vox Machina."

02:05:59.127 --> 02:06:06.640
LAURA: And then I want to buy like three more
greaters.

02:06:06.640 --> 02:06:08.394
MATT: All right. That is 1500 gold.

02:06:08.394 --> 02:06:10.566
LAURA: Can I say I haggled?

02:06:10.566 --> 02:06:12.798
MATT: Roll a persuasion check.

02:06:12.798 --> 02:06:18.275
(assorted muttering)

02:06:18.275 --> 02:06:19.637
LAURA: Shut up!

02:06:19.637 --> 02:06:20.666
MARISHA: Big money, no whammies.

02:06:20.666 --> 02:06:21.769
LAURA: Natural 20!

02:06:21.769 --> 02:06:22.998
ALL: Oh!

02:06:22.998 --> 02:06:25.358
TRAVIS: The sorcery is strong with this one,
apparently.

02:06:25.358 --> 02:06:31.779
MATT: Through diving between two different
locations that sell these potions and forcing them

02:06:31.779 --> 02:06:37.583
to basically bid back and forth for your business,
you manage to work it down to 1100 gold pieces for

02:06:37.583 --> 02:06:39.581
the three greater healing potions.

02:06:39.581 --> 02:06:43.509
TALIESIN: It's like you've got Amazon.com on your
phone and you're going, "Eh? Eh?"

02:06:43.509 --> 02:06:46.123
LAURA: All right, three more greater healing
potions.

02:06:46.123 --> 02:06:47.046
MATT: Yes.

02:06:47.046 --> 02:06:48.034
LAURA: Sounds good.

02:06:48.034 --> 02:06:53.790
SAM: You saved 400 gold! Want to kick some of that
to this guy? Well, I've been helping you all day,

02:06:53.790 --> 02:06:56.165
shuttling back and forth between those two.

02:06:56.165 --> 02:06:57.833
LAURA: Can I insight check him?

02:06:57.833 --> 02:06:59.020
MATT: Go for it.

02:06:59.020 --> 02:07:01.745
TALIESIN: It's not going to work but oh, I hope it
does.

02:07:01.745 --> 02:07:02.966
MATT: Make a deception check.

02:07:02.966 --> 02:07:04.320
LIAM: Oh, it's high.

02:07:04.320 --> 02:07:06.130
TRAVIS: (chuckles) You're fucked.

02:07:06.130 --> 02:07:07.372
SAM: It's not that good.

02:07:07.372 --> 02:07:08.406
LAURA: 27.

02:07:08.406 --> 02:07:10.782
MATT: Remember, you can also add your own
inspiration die if you want to.

02:07:10.782 --> 02:07:15.321
SAM: No, no need. Let's see here. You said 27?

02:07:15.321 --> 02:07:16.330
LAURA: Yeah.

02:07:16.330 --> 02:07:17.377
SAM: 26.

02:07:17.377 --> 02:07:18.776
(gasping)

02:07:18.776 --> 02:07:26.223
MATT: For the first time, you see a crack in
Scanlan Shorthalt's veneer. You see a bit of sweat

02:07:26.223 --> 02:07:33.176
at his brow and as he mentions this money,
suddenly you see this quiver to his smile. His

02:07:33.176 --> 02:07:41.098
teeth shine not as bright as you recall. And there's a
taste of desperation you never knew was there at

02:07:41.098 --> 02:07:42.289
the mention of money.

02:07:42.289 --> 02:07:43.778
TRAVIS: The faintest nosebleed.

02:07:43.778 --> 02:07:44.822
LAURA: Darling?

02:07:44.822 --> 02:07:45.992
SAM: (strained) Yes?

02:07:45.992 --> 02:07:48.843
LAURA: We all have off days.

02:07:48.843 --> 02:07:51.926
SAM: (strained) I've had a whole off city!

02:07:51.926 --> 02:07:54.399
LAURA: We're about to leave.

02:07:54.399 --> 02:07:56.577
SAM: (strained) Please, can we?

02:07:56.577 --> 02:07:59.254
LAURA: We can. I won't tell anyone.

02:07:59.254 --> 02:08:02.299
SAM: All right. So, like, 200 gold then?

02:08:02.299 --> 02:08:04.461
TRAVIS: Please, sir?

02:08:04.461 --> 02:08:08.284
LAURA: I give him 50. That's for lying to me.

02:08:08.284 --> 02:08:12.632
SAM: Thank you. I want to go away from this
place.

02:08:12.632 --> 02:08:18.861
LIAM: Can we get back to politics, please?

02:08:18.861 --> 02:08:23.377
LAURA: All right. Minus 1100.

02:08:23.377 --> 02:08:31.077
MATT: I like to imagine when this whole campaign's
over, Scanlan Shorthalt comes back and cleans out

02:08:31.077 --> 02:08:32.905
the casino in vengeance.

02:08:32.905 --> 02:08:35.148
LIAM: As the airship bears down on Ank'Harel.

02:08:35.148 --> 02:08:39.644
MATT: I meant monetarily, but that works too.

02:08:39.644 --> 02:08:41.486
LIAM: Scarface.

02:08:41.486 --> 02:08:44.404
TRAVIS: Even though it's dusk, should we mount up
tonight?

02:08:44.404 --> 02:08:46.285
SAM: Yes.

02:08:46.285 --> 02:08:48.101
LAURA: Yes, Let's go get on the boat.

02:08:48.101 --> 02:08:49.812
TRAVIS: Let's head to the skies.

02:08:49.812 --> 02:08:51.658
LIAM: This is really happening.

02:08:51.658 --> 02:08:53.000
TALIESIN: I'm so excited.

02:08:53.000 --> 02:08:54.477
LIAM: We've joked about it for ages.

02:08:54.477 --> 02:08:55.599
TRAVIS: (singing) Indalla!

02:08:55.599 --> 02:09:01.631
MATT: All right, you all make your way to the sky
port.

02:09:01.631 --> 02:09:02.807
TALIESIN: Yes.

02:09:02.807 --> 02:09:06.115
SAM: Ah, it would've been so much sweeter if we
could've stolen the airship, but getting it for

02:09:06.115 --> 02:09:07.349
free feels right.

02:09:07.349 --> 02:09:09.132
TALIESIN: We got it for a steal.

02:09:09.132 --> 02:09:16.018
MATT: All right, so you guys make your way up to
the terraced platform above the sky port. The

02:09:16.018 --> 02:09:19.704
larger ship you guys saw earlier is no longer
there, it has taken off, and now all you see

02:09:19.704 --> 02:09:25.774
before you is the ship Deera that is currently
down. The six chains have been reduced to two, and

02:09:25.774 --> 02:09:31.995
it appears to be at the ready. As opposed to its
resting position, now the fan on the sides is

02:09:31.995 --> 02:09:39.502
unfurled, the crystals themselves glow with a
faint blue energy signature, as the dusk sun

02:09:39.502 --> 02:09:46.707
begins to set. It's much more prominent now. And a
series of four rope ladders have been dropped from the

02:09:46.707 --> 02:09:50.029
side of the actual ship.

02:09:50.029 --> 02:09:52.633
SAM: Ladies, your chariot awaits.

02:09:52.633 --> 02:09:56.767
MARISHA: No. I make sure Scanlan goes first.

02:09:56.767 --> 02:09:58.179
SAM: All right.

02:09:58.179 --> 02:10:01.227
MATT: All right.

02:10:01.227 --> 02:10:04.156
LAURA: I turn around and wink at him as I go up.

02:10:04.156 --> 02:10:09.497
MATT: All right, you guys make your way up the
rope ladders. This is indeed the ship that you

02:10:09.497 --> 02:10:15.667
made across, although it has a new paint job on
it. It looks a little bit nicer, but it also seems

02:10:15.667 --> 02:10:21.992
to have seen some disuse. You make your way onto
the board and there you can see familiar ship

02:10:21.992 --> 02:10:27.277
hands that go around, nodding to you out of
recognition. Some of them are pulling up the rope

02:10:27.277 --> 02:10:32.235
ladders behind you. You see two on the bottom
there are now unchaining from the edge of where

02:10:32.235 --> 02:10:36.494
it's latched onto the side of the ship, on each
side, that keeps it latched into the skyport. And

02:10:36.494 --> 02:10:42.520
Captain Damon comes up to the top to greet you.
"Very well. I see that you've come to begin the

02:10:42.520 --> 02:10:48.738
"journey. Well, it is a pleasure to see you all
again, safe and sound, although you are missing

02:10:48.738 --> 02:10:51.279
"one. Two, actually."

02:10:51.279 --> 02:11:00.220
TALIESIN: Yes, we're a bit thinner. It has been
difficult and we have friends elsewhere preparing

02:11:00.220 --> 02:11:05.189
for more difficult times. Are you aware of what's
going on across the sea?

02:11:05.189 --> 02:11:11.662
MATT: "I'm very aware. That was the guild that
owned the ship and ran our business disappeared in

02:11:11.662 --> 02:11:18.216
"the attack, and we've been set adrift, making our
own money and making ends meet in the meantime,

02:11:18.216 --> 02:11:19.940
"doing odd jobs here and there."

02:11:19.940 --> 02:11:25.139
TALIESIN: Well, if you're interested, we are
definitely moving towards correcting some of these

