02:40:26.708 --> 02:40:28.010
tomorrow.

02:40:28.010 --> 02:40:36.172
TRAVIS: I pay super close attention, but after we
gave them the destination, did they tell us how

02:40:36.172 --> 02:40:37.485
long it would take?

02:40:37.485 --> 02:40:39.337
SAM: Two, three days.

02:40:39.337 --> 02:40:40.696
MATT: Depending on the weather.

02:40:40.696 --> 02:40:46.703
TRAVIS: What if we pass over the ship in the
night?

02:40:46.703 --> 02:40:49.963
TALIESIN: Then we'll attack them in the night.

02:40:49.963 --> 02:40:53.821
SAM: How will we see them? Is there someone who
stands watch at night?

02:40:53.821 --> 02:40:58.514
MARISHA: She knows where we're going, so she'll
let us know if we get there?

02:40:58.514 --> 02:41:02.040
SAM: But we're looking for the boat, not the
island.

02:41:02.040 --> 02:41:05.976
TALIESIN: The boat itself. There's work that
always needs to be done. There'll be lights,

02:41:05.976 --> 02:41:08.016
unless they are hiding.

02:41:08.016 --> 02:41:12.197
LIAM: You can alert one of us if we come upon a
ship in the night or day, correct?

02:41:12.197 --> 02:41:16.576
MATT: "I have to sleep at some point as well."

02:41:16.576 --> 02:41:18.738
LIAM: Of course, but someone is awake?

02:41:18.738 --> 02:41:22.273
MATT: "Deshall, who is my second in command, will
take over while I'm sleeping. There will be

02:41:22.273 --> 02:41:26.640
"someone here, along with a few hands, taking
shifts as well at all times."

02:41:26.640 --> 02:41:33.353
MARISHA: I describe the ship to them from what
I've seen.

02:41:33.353 --> 02:41:37.362
LAURA: But it's in the ocean, isn't it? And we're
very high above it?

02:41:37.362 --> 02:41:39.907
TRAVIS: Do we want to go lower?

02:41:39.907 --> 02:41:43.697
SAM: Yes.

02:41:43.697 --> 02:41:45.809
TRAVIS: How high off the deck, would you say?

02:41:45.809 --> 02:41:55.822
SAM: Off the sea? Three, maybe four feet? No. I
don't know, couple hundred feet? You're the captain.

02:41:55.822 --> 02:42:00.596
MATT: "We're okay for now. High is fine. But once
we get close to the archipelago we'll want to make

02:42:00.596 --> 02:42:06.135
"sure that we keep within 100 feet of the
surface. I could take it into the ocean. This can

02:42:06.135 --> 02:42:08.127
"work as a functional ship in the water."

02:42:08.127 --> 02:42:13.248
TRAVIS: Shut the hell up! Well, we want to stay
out, right now.

02:42:13.248 --> 02:42:25.535
MATT: "Well then, you seem weary enough. You may
have your rest, and rest assured that we'll be to

02:42:25.535 --> 02:42:32.443
"your destination as soon as this ship can carry
us. I'm going to rest myself." He goes down to his

02:42:32.443 --> 02:42:42.205
quarters and Deshall takes over, who is
mid-thirties, grizzled, scruff on his chin, but

02:42:42.205 --> 02:42:47.818
put together well, hair parted to one side, not a
man of many words. He takes over the helm and

02:42:47.907 --> 02:42:53.679
keeps it going through the night. You guys go
ahead and rest for the evening?

02:42:53.679 --> 02:42:57.187
LIAM: I'm going to meditate for an hour before
bed.

02:42:57.187 --> 02:43:05.044
TRAVIS: Could I take a shot of the sandkheg
bottle? I would like to slowly start building up

02:43:05.044 --> 02:43:06.507
an immunity.

02:43:06.507 --> 02:43:12.011
MATT: All righty. Make a constitution saving
throw, Grog.

02:43:12.011 --> 02:43:15.116
LIAM: (Grog voice) Meaning I would like to get 
fucked up on a regular basis.

02:43:15.210 --> 02:43:16.568
TRAVIS: 29.

02:43:16.568 --> 02:43:24.443
MATT: You drink it. You feel the sparkling
numbness begin to spread across your throat. It's

02:43:24.443 --> 02:43:30.311
strange. It's weird. It's exhilarating. It
triggers your adrenaline, and you almost go into a

02:43:30.311 --> 02:43:35.453
rage from the instinctual reaction of that sort of
chemical release in your brain. You hold it in

02:43:35.453 --> 02:43:40.181
place, and you sit there a second and stare as it
slowly goes down your system. You feel the warm,

02:43:40.181 --> 02:43:49.626
curling burn from inside your belly that fine
alcohol gives you, that little shimmer of pins and

02:43:49.626 --> 02:43:53.731
needles down the back of your neck and your spine.
Your vision begins to blur a little bit. It takes

02:43:53.731 --> 02:43:56.916
you a lot of alcohol to get trashed, but you're a
little buzzed.

02:43:56.916 --> 02:44:05.156
TRAVIS: Sick. Awesome. Well played, sandkheg. I go
to sleep.

02:44:05.156 --> 02:44:10.405
MATT: With your nightcap, you are good to go.
Looking under the stars, you finish your

02:44:10.405 --> 02:44:16.359
meditation. Everyone else, you go to rest fine.
Throughout the evening you sleep. The last thing

02:44:16.359 --> 02:44:24.681
you see before you go to bed is the edge of the
mountain range, late into the night, and a small

02:44:24.681 --> 02:44:38.207
sparkle in a crescent shape. You ask one of the
hands to the side. He points over and says, "The

02:44:38.207 --> 02:44:45.013
"Bay of Gifts." This is the northern side where you
see Shamal, the port city. That's the last little

02:44:45.013 --> 02:44:50.456
bastion of civilization of Marquet as it begins to
approach from underneath as you all go to sleep.

02:44:50.456 --> 02:44:53.966
The continent is behind you.

02:44:53.966 --> 02:44:57.579
MARISHA: How many hours has it been?

02:44:57.579 --> 02:45:00.311
MATT: When you come to consciousness after the
evening's rest--

02:45:00.311 --> 02:45:08.236
LAURA: I want to hold Fenthras in my hand and keep
thinking about the things Saundor said.

02:45:08.236 --> 02:45:17.574
MATT: After a good eight hour rest for all of you
to recover yourselves, hit points, everything,

02:45:17.574 --> 02:45:34.368
spells, you come to. The warmth of the sun is what
kicks you into consciousness. It's been about 13

02:45:34.368 --> 02:45:42.983
hours since you guys left. Eight hours of rest.
You had five hours of travel northward until you

02:45:42.983 --> 02:45:46.593
began to reach the northern end of the continent
on this skyship.

02:45:46.593 --> 02:45:52.107
TALIESIN: This might be the best sleep that we've
gotten in months, at this point. Like babies.

02:45:52.107 --> 02:45:57.786
SAM: Is it morning time?

02:45:57.786 --> 02:45:58.979
MATT: Yeah.

02:45:58.979 --> 02:46:01.003
SAM: You want to do that morning scry?

02:46:01.003 --> 02:46:03.997
MARISHA: Yeah, morning scry.

02:46:03.997 --> 02:46:06.763
TALIESIN: I'm going to sit down with a pen and
paper, ready to write!

02:46:06.763 --> 02:46:17.109
MARISHA: Yeah, morning constitutional, here we
come. Bust out whatever magazines they have

02:46:17.109 --> 02:46:21.481
nearby. Cup of coffee, first.

02:46:21.481 --> 02:46:27.884
MATT: All right. Using the same journal?

02:46:27.884 --> 02:46:33.352
TALIESIN: Let's use the gun now. Let's go nuts.

02:46:33.352 --> 02:46:35.845
SAM: Now that it's been de-cursed, will that mess
up--

02:46:35.845 --> 02:46:38.763
TALIESIN: It's got a lot of her work in it.

02:46:38.763 --> 02:46:42.271
MATT: All right, are you using the crystal first?

02:46:42.271 --> 02:46:45.347
MARISHA: Yeah. Crystal first.

02:46:45.347 --> 02:46:50.416
MATT: What's the crystal DC? Because it's not your
actual spell, which I should have remembered last

02:46:50.416 --> 02:46:55.009
time. I mean, she rolled low enough last time that
it wasn't an issue.

02:46:55.009 --> 02:46:57.430
MARISHA: It doesn't say.

02:46:57.430 --> 02:47:08.013
MATT: Okay, then it should be 15. That's a natural
one. As you're concentrating on the scry spell,

02:47:08.013 --> 02:47:16.689
your vision once again is thrust through the
clouds, thrown down over the ocean. You see for a

02:47:16.689 --> 02:47:28.486
brief moment a cluster of dark land, roughly in
the shape of a bean or a cashew from this

02:47:28.486 --> 02:47:36.939
perspective, and then it flashes downward and you
can see a ship. A ship that is on the water. It is

02:47:36.939 --> 02:47:38.160
stationary.

02:47:38.160 --> 02:47:40.222
MARISHA: Docked, like anchors down?

02:47:40.222 --> 02:47:43.107
MATT: Seemingly. The sails aren't up.

02:47:43.107 --> 02:47:45.688
TRAVIS: It's not at land? It's in the water?

02:47:45.688 --> 02:47:54.313
MATT: Yeah. Your vision flashes again and you can
see the crew have all gathered on the deck, though

02:47:54.313 --> 02:48:06.295
details of their visage are obscured by the spell.
You see Ripley there with her cloak. She is

02:48:06.295 --> 02:48:15.206
talking to the rest of the crew and goes, "All
right, so. We've located it. We have eight hours.

02:48:15.206 --> 02:48:22.730
"Gather your things and drink well." They all pull
out these small vials, uncork, and drink down.

02:48:22.730 --> 02:48:39.140
They all nod. One by one, they start diving off
the ship and into the water. Five people, you're

02:48:39.140 --> 02:48:46.326
not sure of the sex, and Ripley, dive off the
side. You're following her as she goes underwater;

02:48:46.326 --> 02:48:51.221
you can see the bubbles go past. Then the bubbles
are no more and you watch as she is now breathing

02:48:51.221 --> 02:48:57.344
the water like it's air. Swimming downward. All of
them are carrying, you see on the side, these

02:48:57.344 --> 02:49:02.649
heavy rock weights that are letting them guide
down deeper into the water as it gets darker,

02:49:02.649 --> 02:49:11.074
until there's almost nothing to see. Then there's
a flicker of light and you see Ripley is now

02:49:11.074 --> 02:49:17.112
holding her gun. There's a beam of light on the
end of it that's giving them torchlight as they go

02:49:17.112 --> 02:49:26.387
deeper in. Then the spell fades.

02:49:26.387 --> 02:49:30.372
MARISHA: She's found it. She's there.

02:49:30.372 --> 02:49:31.725
TRAVIS: She's got it?

02:49:31.725 --> 02:49:37.305
MARISHA: She doesn't have it, but she's found the
ship. She's right off the shore of the island.

02:49:37.305 --> 02:49:39.363
LAURA: Can you scry again immediately?

02:49:39.363 --> 02:49:43.114
MARISHA: She's under the water. I mean, I could.

02:49:43.114 --> 02:49:44.779
TRAVIS: How is she under the water?

02:49:44.779 --> 02:49:48.795
MARISHA: They all took water breathing potions.
Her plus five other people.

02:49:48.795 --> 02:49:55.827
TALIESIN: Was there anything around? Could you see
the island in sight?

02:49:55.827 --> 02:50:00.576
MARISHA: I saw the island. It was dark in
landscape.

02:50:00.576 --> 02:50:06.953
MATT: It was such a brief shot, because it wasn't
the focus of the scry spell. Even the fact that

02:50:06.953 --> 02:50:14.065
you caught a glimpse of it was a strange side
effect of the scry attempt.

02:50:14.065 --> 02:50:19.733
TALIESIN: Was the sun with the island, or was the
sun away from the island? Is there any way to even

02:50:19.733 --> 02:50:22.464
know that? Were they on the north side or the
south side?

02:50:22.464 --> 02:50:29.284
MATT: From what you can gather at this time, no.
That's part of the scry spell. You wouldn't be

02:50:29.284 --> 02:50:30.440
able to tell.

02:50:30.440 --> 02:50:35.213
LIAM: I'm heading over to find the captain and the
halfling to ask how far they estimate we are from

02:50:35.213 --> 02:50:36.571
the island.

02:50:36.571 --> 02:50:38.582
MARISHA: I heard Ripley say, "We have eight
hours."

02:50:38.582 --> 02:50:42.028
LAURA: That's how long the spell lasts.

02:50:42.028 --> 02:50:45.175
TRAVIS: I have two vials of underwater breathing.

02:50:45.175 --> 02:50:49.922
MARISHA: I'll take water breathing as a spell.

02:50:49.922 --> 02:50:52.265
LAURA: How many people can you cast it on?

02:50:52.265 --> 02:51:02.191
MATT: Water breathing as a spell actually lasts
for 24 hours. The potions only last for eight.

02:51:02.191 --> 02:51:04.330
MARISHA: Is it concentration?

02:51:04.330 --> 02:51:07.771
MATT: Nope. It grants up to ten willing creatures
you can see--

02:51:07.771 --> 02:51:09.566
MARISHA: What!? Ten willing?

02:51:09.566 --> 02:51:10.908
LAURA: That's sick.

02:51:10.908 --> 02:51:13.080
MARISHA: I got us on lock, you guys.

02:51:13.080 --> 02:51:16.629
TALIESIN: I had a plan. I'm putting it away.

02:51:16.629 --> 02:51:25.002
MATT: Yeah, so the potion enchantments are lesser
than the spell, but the actual druidic spell

02:51:25.002 --> 02:51:31.998
effect is much better. You see him looking off in
the distance as you're asking the question. He

02:51:31.998 --> 02:51:38.271
points and goes, "Well given &lt;i&gt;that&lt;/i&gt; might slow us
down a bit--" You look ahead and you now see,

02:51:38.271 --> 02:51:40.582
immediately visible from this point--

02:51:40.582 --> 02:51:44.662
LAURA: Don't be a green dragon!

02:51:44.662 --> 02:52:00.389
MATT: What you are able to make out, because it's
a familiar sight to you, are very tall, dark,

02:52:00.389 --> 02:52:08.459
distant thunderheads. The storm that you saw in
your first vision, Keyleth, apparently is still

02:52:08.459 --> 02:52:13.906
swirling its way through the middle of the ocean.
It's violent, it's visceral, and you can see the

02:52:13.906 --> 02:52:19.528
weight of the water giving it this deep, dark,
gray color, and the rest of the ocean below is

02:52:19.528 --> 02:52:26.228
obscured with the blur of rainfall. He goes,
"Those are high clouds. I can't get above them.

02:52:26.228 --> 02:52:31.739
"The enchantment is only so strong to get us into
that thinner air. So I recommend everyone hold on."

02:52:31.739 --> 02:52:33.618
LIAM: Is there anything you can do about this?

02:52:33.618 --> 02:52:35.212
MARISHA: I can. Get us closer.

02:52:35.212 --> 02:52:36.578
MATT: "What?"

02:52:36.578 --> 02:52:39.067
TALIESIN: Trust her. She's crazy.

02:52:39.067 --> 02:52:44.032
MARISHA: Straight through, fastest route,
captain.

02:52:44.032 --> 02:52:49.089
MATT: "Okay, I trust you." He brings it around and
begins pulling forward. You can see this little

02:52:49.089 --> 02:52:53.759
metallic rod on the side and he pushes it forward
even further. The crystals flicker for a second

02:52:53.759 --> 02:53:07.877
and the whole ship leans in a forward direction.
It takes about an hour before the shade from the

02:53:07.877 --> 02:53:14.023
thunderheads, which, you can't even see where they
stop, they go up and up and up, begin to meet.

02:53:14.023 --> 02:53:17.163
You're starting to see flashes in the clouds of
lightning.

02:53:17.163 --> 02:53:30.619
MARISHA: I go ahead and I start casting my first
8th-level spell, which is Control Weather. It's

02:53:30.619 --> 02:53:37.316
everything I've ever wanted, you guys!

02:53:37.316 --> 02:53:46.425
MATT: Yeah, concentration for up to eight hours.
So you guys watch as Keyleth stands at the bow of

02:53:46.425 --> 02:53:53.136
the ship, puts her arms out, and you see the
flashes of lightning in the cloud. A bolt strikes

02:53:53.136 --> 02:54:00.202
her in one arm. She holds it in place. The bolt
uses her as a conduit and then vanishes into her

02:54:00.202 --> 02:54:05.899
arm. Her other arm pulls another bolt to it, and
it vanishes into her arm. You can see the energy's

02:54:05.899 --> 02:54:11.047
now circling around. She brings her arms out and
thrusts them into the storm. The lightning

02:54:11.047 --> 02:54:17.364
protrudes out of each arm. As it hits the clouds,
the clouds seem to almost melt away and carve this

02:54:17.364 --> 02:54:24.478
central path. The clouds are being pushed back, at
gale force. These winds are separating them. You

02:54:24.478 --> 02:54:30.520
watch. For five miles around you, the storm
basically parts to nearly nothing except for the

02:54:30.520 --> 02:54:38.159
very peripheral to the right and left side. You
hear Captain Damon go, "Okay! I see your point."

02:54:38.159 --> 02:54:42.809
LIAM: Hot fucking damn, Keyleth!

02:54:42.809 --> 02:54:48.677
LAURA: You know, I thought it was a possibility,
but this is the first time I'm sure your

02:54:48.677 --> 02:54:50.841
girlfriend is way cooler than you.

02:54:50.841 --> 02:54:52.747
LIAM: Everyone knew that.

02:54:52.747 --> 02:55:02.748
MATT: So pushing forward, Keyleth is concentrating
at the edge of the ship. Her eyes spark with

02:55:02.748 --> 02:55:06.499
energy. You're almost like the mermaid at the
front of the ship at this point. You're right at

02:55:06.499 --> 02:55:07.596
the front, arms out.

02:55:07.596 --> 02:55:10.816
LIAM: You're like a reverse Pyro. You're undoing
all the violence.

02:55:10.816 --> 02:55:17.972
MATT: The shade fades away. The clear blue sky
above then invites these warm sun beams down upon

02:55:17.972 --> 02:55:19.446
the top of the ship.

02:55:19.446 --> 02:55:21.034
LAURA: I do some sunbathing.

02:55:21.034 --> 02:55:26.284
MARISHA: I make it temperate with a nice warm
breeze.

02:55:26.284 --> 02:55:30.666
SAM: Keyleth, can you make the breeze behind us,
and can you make it rather strong?

02:55:30.666 --> 02:55:33.752
MARISHA: Can I do that?

02:55:33.752 --> 02:55:38.746
TALIESIN: He's reading! He doesn't know.

02:55:38.746 --> 02:55:43.035
SAM: Well, you said it lasts eight hours.

02:55:43.035 --> 02:55:47.592
TALIESIN: He's checking to see if it's a thing you
can actually do.

02:55:47.592 --> 02:55:49.573
LIAM: Checking his stocks. Message from mom.

02:55:49.573 --> 02:56:00.477
MATT: What you can do is you can clear the storm
for five miles, and then subtly change to a wind

02:56:00.477 --> 02:56:03.979
stage behind you, yes. I'll let you do that,
sure.

02:56:03.979 --> 02:56:09.077
MARISHA: Make the winds in our favor! I'm drunk on
power!

02:56:09.077 --> 02:56:13.949
MATT: The wind begins to build from behind. Some
of you have to duck down now because it's starting

02:56:13.949 --> 02:56:21.154
to take. It almost takes your hat off, Scanlan.
You catch it. But it is picking up speed and you

02:56:21.154 --> 02:56:26.701
guys are beginning to coast forward. Occasionally
the winds die down as you have to clear more of

02:56:26.701 --> 02:56:33.016
the storm. Over the next six or so hours, you come
out the other side of the storm.

02:56:33.016 --> 02:56:39.574
MARISHA: I go into a deep meditation. This is some
Buddhist shit going on for me right now.

02:56:39.574 --> 02:56:53.064
MATT: Perfect. As the storm subsides, your ship
has a clear view of distant breaks in the patterns

02:56:53.064 --> 02:57:01.129
of waves on the horizon. Multiple chained islands,
many miles apart from each other, emerge. This,

02:57:01.129 --> 02:57:06.219
you've now begun to reach, is the Hespet
Archipelago. Each of the twelve islands vary in

02:57:06.219 --> 02:57:15.609
size from massive rock to pebble-like protrusions.
They span and are scattered, and the ship begins

02:57:15.609 --> 02:57:24.195
to veer to the left as the captain begins to zero
in on your destination. He yells out, "We're going

02:57:24.195 --> 02:57:33.407
"low! They have visibility!" The ship begins to go
into a relatively steep decline. You hear the wood

02:57:33.407 --> 02:57:42.014
creaking with the sudden shift in direction and
weight. The gem on the right side begins to

02:57:42.014 --> 02:57:47.979
brighten while the one on the left begins to
darken slightly, exemplifying the shift in energy

02:57:47.979 --> 02:57:52.782
and power. Eventually you're brought down, nearly
coasting on the surface of the ocean, and as you

02:57:52.782 --> 02:57:58.278
get to about 40, 50 feet above you see the waves
begin to part beneath it as whatever force is

02:57:58.278 --> 02:58:03.040
holding it there is now pushing the water down. He
brings it up a little so it's not breaking the

02:58:03.040 --> 02:58:12.543
surface and coasts at an even 60 feet above.
Pushing forward, you already begin to see what you

02:58:12.543 --> 02:58:22.542
assume is the Isle of Glintshore. In this clear,
sunlit moment, you also see, throughout the ocean,

02:58:22.542 --> 02:58:32.999
clusters of dangerous, jagged-looking reef, some
ten, 15 below the surface, some actually breaching

02:58:32.999 --> 02:58:39.725
the surface of the ocean, some even deeper. This
portion of the ocean is like a maze network of

02:58:39.725 --> 02:58:48.725
every ship captain's nightmare. You get the
feeling why this has become a favored place of

02:58:48.725 --> 02:58:58.196
criminals to avoid pursuers and also why people
who trade avoid it for many reasons, not just

02:58:58.196 --> 02:59:06.189
those who stay here. And also why the shipwreck
probably found its way here. As you begin to grow

02:59:06.189 --> 02:59:12.610
closer to the island, you see, as it begins to
come more into form, there is a singular mountain

02:59:12.610 --> 02:59:20.781
peak that's shifted mostly to the western side.
It's not a super peak. It's a gradual point. You

02:59:20.781 --> 02:59:28.773
can see a little bit of a brush-like detail of the
jungle that you had heard mentioned before. He

02:59:28.773 --> 02:59:36.161
begins to bring you up towards the southern shore
of the island. At this point of perspective, the

02:59:36.161 --> 02:59:42.694
sunlight that's hitting the island is causing a
glittery shift of thousands of points of light

02:59:42.694 --> 02:59:51.557
across the beach shoreline, deep into where the
blackened jungle tree line is. It's beautiful.

02:59:51.557 --> 02:59:59.735
It's a very strange and awe-inspiring sight, to be
such a small little forgotten part of the land and

02:59:59.735 --> 03:00:01.687
to look so pretty from this distance.

03:00:01.687 --> 03:00:08.525
The closer you get, the beauty begins to
fade as you see the black beaches. You can see the

03:00:08.525 --> 03:00:19.076
landscape is barren and broken, aside from the
ashen gray and black jungle plants and trees that

03:00:19.174 --> 03:00:24.236
have been left there, dead, for an extended period
of time. The mountain itself, the rock itself

03:00:24.236 --> 03:00:30.861
going from black to a ruddy red and brown color.
The sands themselves and the glass surface across

03:00:30.861 --> 03:00:38.599
the eastern shore that tends to reach out, almost
like a mouth of a creature, is rough and varied in

03:00:38.599 --> 03:00:47.705
topography. You also see, within that bay, a tiny
little thing that looks like a ship.

03:00:47.705 --> 03:00:51.596
LIAM: Are we close enough to see if there's people
on the deck?

03:00:51.596 --> 03:00:54.702
MATT: You're not close enough. You're barely now
seeing that there's a ship.

03:00:54.702 --> 03:00:58.361
MARISHA: It's been six hours, you said, since I
did my scry.

03:00:58.361 --> 03:01:00.774
MATT: Probably about seven hours now, since you
did the spell.

03:01:00.774 --> 03:01:02.509
LAURA: They're going to be coming out any minute.

03:01:02.509 --> 03:01:04.335
MARISHA: They have one hour left.

03:01:04.335 --> 03:01:05.639
LAURA: Unless they're already out.

03:01:05.639 --> 03:01:09.373
LIAM: Yeah, that's the duration of the spell, the
eight hours. They could be back already.

03:01:09.373 --> 03:01:12.507
MARISHA: If we have one hour left, they could
fail. They could not find it at all.

03:01:12.507 --> 03:01:16.444
LAURA: Could we shoot the boat from above and
destroy their escape?

03:01:16.444 --> 03:01:23.477
TRAVIS: Could I make a song request? Could we drop
your big rocky ass from 300 feet up right through

03:01:23.477 --> 03:01:25.181
the bottom of their ship and sink that bitch?

03:01:25.181 --> 03:01:27.511
TALIESIN: I'll also say, there's nothing a ship
doesn't like more than fire.

03:01:27.511 --> 03:01:29.053
LAURA: Yes.

03:01:29.053 --> 03:01:33.711
MARISHA: I mean, all of these things are very
appealing to me right now. I'm just trying to

03:01:33.711 --> 03:01:37.453
understand why.

03:01:37.453 --> 03:01:38.710
SAM: Well, we can't let them escape.

03:01:38.710 --> 03:01:42.862
LIAM: It's better that they're floating on the
water than standing on the ship.

03:01:42.862 --> 03:01:45.059
TRAVIS: And if they have a teleportation circle on
the boat, we want to destroy it.

03:01:45.059 --> 03:01:47.752
MARISHA: She also has the cloak we want.

03:01:47.752 --> 03:01:51.704
LAURA: Right. So we wait until she drowns, and
then we take it from her.

03:01:51.704 --> 03:01:54.203
TALIESIN: We can retrieve it from the bottom of
the sea, if we have to.

03:01:54.203 --> 03:01:59.831
MARISHA: What do we know about magical items? Do
they get destroyed by things like fire or me being

03:01:59.831 --> 03:02:00.707
a meteor?

03:02:00.707 --> 03:02:04.667
MATT: Generally, no. Magical items, a part of the
enchantment is to make them resistant to the

03:02:04.667 --> 03:02:12.173
general elements. They endure, and the reason that
you find mostly just the enchanted objects in

03:02:12.173 --> 03:02:18.111
ancient ruins is because everything that would be
destroyed by the weathering of time, these items

03:02:18.111 --> 03:02:19.679
stay relatively pristine.

03:02:19.679 --> 03:02:21.615
MARISHA: Then yes, I'm down to fuck this shit up.

03:02:21.615 --> 03:02:30.295
LAURA: I wonder if she hired the boat, or if it's
hers. I would hate to kill innocent crew members.

03:02:30.295 --> 03:02:33.796
TALIESIN: I don't think they're innocent crew
members. I think she had help.

03:02:33.796 --> 03:02:36.268
SAM: She had five killers with her when she killed
those--

03:02:36.268 --> 03:02:44.374
MATT: You did see, for the record, in your
scrying, while there were five that leapt down

03:02:44.374 --> 03:02:45.965
with her, there were more on the ship.

03:02:45.965 --> 03:02:48.962
SAM: It's fine, we'll throw them a life raft or
something.

03:02:48.962 --> 03:02:53.840
LIAM: Then I'd like to put my vote in for the
meteor.

03:02:53.840 --> 03:02:57.355
TRAVIS: They're also in the bay, so they can swim
to shore.

03:02:57.355 --> 03:03:05.759
LIAM: Well, we can stop their retreat. They're
going to be in worse shape without that boat.

03:03:05.759 --> 03:03:08.387
TRAVIS: I want to send a message to the ship, is
all.

03:03:08.387 --> 03:03:15.611
MATT: The captain's like, "What do you want me to
do? Do you want me to head for the ship?"

03:03:15.611 --> 03:03:17.150
SAM: Up above the ship.

03:03:17.150 --> 03:03:22.921
TRAVIS: And Vax rides Keyleth down, like Dr.
Strangelove, the whole way.

03:03:22.921 --> 03:03:30.556
SAM: You're going to take a lot of damage?

03:03:30.556 --> 03:03:33.832
MARISHA: He can fly.

03:03:33.832 --> 03:03:40.515
LAURA: Can you cast Water Breathing on us before
you fly down, and that way-- or is that going to

03:03:40.515 --> 03:03:42.185
fuck up your spells?

03:03:42.185 --> 03:03:45.949
MARISHA: It's not a concentration spell, right?
Water breathing?

03:03:45.949 --> 03:03:47.599
MATT: No, it's not concentration.

03:03:47.599 --> 03:03:49.146
LIAM: And it lasts a long time.

03:03:49.146 --> 03:03:53.000
LAURA: 24 hours. So just in case we end up in the
water, we're not fucked.

03:03:53.000 --> 03:03:55.231
TALIESIN: We have ten people, 12 people?

03:03:55.231 --> 03:04:02.752
TRAVIS: Last song request. We destroy the ship,
right? It (burbling) and they all (burbling) come

03:04:02.752 --> 03:04:08.430
up to the top, they got to go one place, which is
where? The shore. So why don't we wait on the shore?

03:04:08.430 --> 03:04:11.109
MARISHA: Well do we want to drop your ass off on
the shore?

03:04:11.109 --> 03:04:14.927
TRAVIS: Oh, yeah, I mean, I'd love to be a
welcoming party. I'm just saying, if anyone else

03:04:14.927 --> 03:04:17.902
wants to come with, that's where I know they'll be
going.

03:04:17.902 --> 03:04:20.412
TALIESIN: I'm hoping to take care of this before
the ship even sinks.

03:04:20.412 --> 03:04:22.125
LAURA: I can be death from above on the broom.

03:04:22.125 --> 03:04:27.983
MARISHA: This is my favorite plan we've come up
with in a long time.

03:04:27.983 --> 03:04:30.664
SAM: We should probably make sure that this is the
right boat.

03:04:30.664 --> 03:04:34.261
LAURA: Yes, yes, we need to double check that this
is actually the boat.

03:04:34.261 --> 03:04:36.971
MARISHA: Does this look like the right boat?

03:04:36.971 --> 03:04:38.935
MATT: You're a little ways from it. Are you going
to wait until you get closer?

03:04:38.935 --> 03:04:42.267
TRAVIS: Is there a telescope on this ship?

03:04:42.267 --> 03:04:44.676
MATT: There is one that you've been using.

03:04:44.676 --> 03:04:48.001
LAURA: Can you cast a spell, just in case shit
happens, as soon as we get close enough to the ship?

03:04:48.001 --> 03:04:49.312
MARISHA: Dispel?

03:04:49.312 --> 03:04:51.380
LAURA: No, the spell, the breathing spell.

03:04:51.380 --> 03:04:55.549
MARISHA: Oh, yeah. What's our ETA, captain?

03:04:55.549 --> 03:05:01.340
MATT: "At this speed, I'd say 20 minutes."

03:05:01.340 --> 03:05:10.258
MARISHA: I'll wait ten minutes, because I like to
milk my time.

03:05:10.258 --> 03:05:17.370
MATT: All right, ten minutes go by. Who is keeping
watch through the telescope?

03:05:17.370 --> 03:05:18.514
LAURA: Me.

03:05:18.514 --> 03:05:20.852
MATT: All right, make a perception check.

03:05:20.852 --> 03:05:22.834
SAM: Wait, but Keyleth knows what the boat looks
like.

03:05:22.834 --> 03:05:24.440
LAURA: She told me all about it.

03:05:24.440 --> 03:05:25.602
MARISHA: Yeah.

03:05:25.602 --> 03:05:31.603
LAURA: 25.

03:05:31.603 --> 03:05:36.664
MATT: 25, all right. You're scanning across.
Looking at the ship: the sails are up, it is

03:05:36.664 --> 03:05:44.503
anchored, and there are maybe four individuals who
are currently playing cards on the upper deck.

03:05:44.503 --> 03:05:46.794
LAURA: It looks like the boat's been docked there
for a while.

03:05:46.794 --> 03:05:53.464
MATT: You also notice, scanning the area, it
catches your eye, there's a very lazy, very faint

03:05:53.464 --> 03:06:00.391
trail that looks like smoke on the shore of the
C-shaped bay on the eastern side of the island.

03:06:00.391 --> 03:06:10.194
LAURA: A camp on the shoreline?

03:06:10.194 --> 03:06:12.877
MATT: That might be a source for the smoke.

03:06:12.877 --> 03:06:14.544
LAURA: Is it close by the boat?

03:06:14.544 --> 03:06:21.240
MATT: If you're looking from your perspective,
this is the eastern side and it has this C-shaped

03:06:21.240 --> 03:06:27.928
bay right here, where this is the shoreline. The
ship is docked right about here in the water. It's

03:06:27.928 --> 03:06:32.137
surrounded by a reef. It's barely made its way in
there and it can't go any further without hitting

03:06:32.137 --> 03:06:36.817
reef. The smoke is right there. It's right on the
beach side.

03:06:36.817 --> 03:06:40.488
TRAVIS: Can we see the other side of the island,
or the water on the other side, from this vantage point?

03:06:40.488 --> 03:06:42.434
MATT: No, not from this vantage point.

03:06:42.434 --> 03:06:50.546
LAURA: Can you scry and see if she's still
underwater, or if she's camping? Because I see smoke.

03:06:50.546 --> 03:06:55.405
SAM: Can Keyleth look through the-- we have a
telescope of some sort?

03:06:55.405 --> 03:06:57.182
MATT: There is a telescope, yeah.

03:06:57.182 --> 03:07:01.456
SAM: Can she look and see if the boat looks right?
Did you see any identifying marks on the boat?

03:07:01.456 --> 03:07:04.167
TALIESIN: It's not like there's going to be a
dozen of them out here.

03:07:04.167 --> 03:07:05.830
LIAM: It would be a very big coincidence.

03:07:05.830 --> 03:07:09.780
MARISHA: I look through the telescope. Does it
look like the same boat?

03:07:09.780 --> 03:07:11.452
MATT: Perception check.

03:07:11.452 --> 03:07:16.742
MARISHA: I rolled an 18, so 29.

03:07:16.742 --> 03:07:22.916
MATT: Yes, this is very much the boat. Size,
color, shape, placement, this is the same ship.

03:07:22.916 --> 03:07:24.872
TRAVIS: Thought we were getting ready to kill a
cruise ship.

03:07:24.872 --> 03:07:26.355
MARISHA: Okay, so am I scrying?

03:07:26.355 --> 03:07:28.508
LAURA: Well I guess you don't need to now.

03:07:28.508 --> 03:07:32.627
SAM: We'd know if she's still underwater or if
she's on land.

03:07:32.627 --> 03:07:35.151
LAURA: There's people on the boat waiting still.

03:07:35.151 --> 03:07:40.681
MATT: You are ten minutes from getting there. It
takes ten minutes to cast scrying.

03:07:40.681 --> 03:07:42.839
TRAVIS: No, we don't need it.

03:07:42.839 --> 03:07:44.838
LAURA: But you should probably cast breathing.

03:07:44.838 --> 03:07:47.213
MARISHA: It takes me 30 seconds to scry once I get
there.

03:07:47.213 --> 03:07:48.671
SAM: Let's scry.

03:07:48.671 --> 03:07:50.344
MARISHA: I'm going to scry.

03:07:50.344 --> 03:07:52.207
LAURA: But cast breathing on us first.

03:07:52.207 --> 03:07:54.550
MARISHA: I'm going to cast Water Breathing, and
then I'm going to scry.

03:07:54.550 --> 03:07:55.995
TALIESIn: Wait, can you do me a favor?

03:07:55.995 --> 03:08:00.757
MARISHA: I'm dishing them out. I'm the magic ATM
right now. What do you want?

03:08:00.757 --> 03:08:07.052
TALIESIN: Once we're somewhat in the distance,
fire an eyeball and get a good look at that ship.

03:08:07.052 --> 03:08:13.192
I want to see if it's a trap. You have an arrow.

03:08:13.192 --> 03:08:15.945
LAURA: Yes, I do. Once we get close enough.

03:08:15.945 --> 03:08:22.558
MARISHA: Okay, so I go to everybody and I say, you
have Water Breathing, you have Water Breathing.

03:08:22.558 --> 03:08:34.744
And everyone has Water Breathing. Then I go,
everyone leave me alone for ten minutes. I drop

03:08:34.744 --> 03:08:36.105
down and I Scry.

03:08:36.105 --> 03:08:42.667
MATT: Okay. So you begin concentrating as you guys
get closer and closer to the ship. You can now see

03:08:42.667 --> 03:08:44.251
it getting closer and closer.

03:08:44.251 --> 03:08:46.961
TRAVIS: Do we want to raise our elevation as we're
getting closer?

03:08:46.961 --> 03:08:49.809
SAM: Yeah, we told him to go up above it.

03:08:49.809 --> 03:08:53.189
MATT: You guys begin to notice, you, Vex, as
you're looking through, the people who were

03:08:53.189 --> 03:08:56.629
playing cards start moving on the deck of the
ship. They start scattering.

03:08:56.629 --> 03:08:57.792
LAURA: Are they seeing us?

03:08:57.792 --> 03:09:01.833
MATT: They have seen you. You're not a hard vision
to see once they pay attention.

03:09:01.833 --> 03:09:06.902
LAURA: Do they look like they're looking over the
sides of the boat?

03:09:06.902 --> 03:09:10.355
MATT: Roll a perception check.

03:09:10.355 --> 03:09:17.311
SAM: This is like the Hindenburg flying up to a
rowboat.

03:09:17.311 --> 03:09:18.662
LAURA: 20.

03:09:18.662 --> 03:09:19.639
MATT: No.

03:09:19.639 --> 03:09:21.349
LAURA: No, they don't look like they're looking
over the side of the boat?

03:09:21.349 --> 03:09:27.597
MATT: No. Okay, you're starting to get closer and
closer. You watch as they all scatter into the

03:09:27.597 --> 03:09:33.868
bottom of the boat, except for one who stands on
the deck. You watch, (launching sound) this one

03:09:33.868 --> 03:09:39.420
sparkle of bright red arcane energy (fizzing) up
into the sky, (explosion)--

03:09:39.420 --> 03:09:41.017
SAM: A flare.

03:09:41.017 --> 03:09:48.432
MATT: --with a dull burst exploding sound, and
then vanishes. The explosion dissipates.

03:09:48.432 --> 03:09:50.199
LAURA: Yeah, it's a flare.

03:09:50.199 --> 03:09:52.815
SAM: To warn the people on land.

03:09:52.815 --> 03:09:55.001
MATT: Another one (fizzing).

03:09:55.001 --> 03:09:57.034
LAURA: Okay, okay. Shit.

03:09:57.034 --> 03:09:58.743
SAM: How do we get to land quickly?

03:09:58.743 --> 03:10:02.303
LAURA: I can fly there on my broom, but I don't
fly very quickly.

03:10:02.303 --> 03:10:04.788
TALIESIN: Are we close enough that one of her
arrows can make it?

03:10:04.788 --> 03:10:08.979
MATT: No, you're about three minutes out now from
approaching it.

03:10:08.979 --> 03:10:10.810
TRAVIS: The ship or the shore?

03:10:10.810 --> 03:10:12.047
MATT: The ship.

03:10:12.047 --> 03:10:18.859
SAM: We should split. Some should go to the beach,
some should continue with plan Drop Keyleth--

03:10:18.859 --> 03:10:20.753
TRAVIS: I'm going to the beach. I can't, yeah.

03:10:20.753 --> 03:10:22.432
SAM: How are you getting to the beach? You can't
fly.

03:10:22.432 --> 03:10:24.107
TRAVIS: Oh.

03:10:24.107 --> 03:10:27.048
TALIESIN: Once we're close enough, you can port
them down.

03:10:27.048 --> 03:10:30.266
SAM: I can make you a thing that flies, to get you
there.

03:10:30.266 --> 03:10:31.651
TRAVIS: What kind of thing?

03:10:31.651 --> 03:10:32.964
SAM: I don't know. Giant eagle?

03:10:32.964 --> 03:10:36.105
TRAVIS: You worry about other stuff.

03:10:36.105 --> 03:10:37.390
LAURA: A pterodactyl.

03:10:37.390 --> 03:10:42.263
TRAVIS: That sounds like our only option, yeah.

03:10:42.263 --> 03:10:46.196
LAURA: Three more minutes of scrying, still? Maybe
the scrying was ill-timed.

03:10:46.196 --> 03:10:47.466
MATT: Two minutes.

03:10:47.466 --> 03:10:50.177
SAM: All right, Grog. You and me. Come on, let's
go.

03:10:50.177 --> 03:10:53.931
LAURA: Oh jeez. I ready the broom. I get on the
broom and wait.

03:10:53.931 --> 03:10:57.670
TALIESIN: Prepare, I'm telling the men, prepare
the harpoons. It may be a trap.

03:10:57.670 --> 03:11:03.623
MATT: "Understood. Man the harpoons!" You see they
all run off to the various, the three different

03:11:03.623 --> 03:11:06.788
dragon arbalist stations.

03:11:06.788 --> 03:11:12.330
TALIESIN: Prepare for a hard turn to shore if they
begin to show any signs of magical attack.

03:11:12.330 --> 03:11:18.288
MATT: "Understood." You can now see the captain's
gone into war mode now. He's keeping focus forward

03:11:18.288 --> 03:11:20.012
as he's pushing the ship.

03:11:20.012 --> 03:11:23.348
TRAVIS: How do we communicate with the captain
once we're off the ship? Should we give him an

03:11:23.348 --> 03:11:24.419
earring?

03:11:24.419 --> 03:11:31.939
SAM: It won't reach, it's too far. Grog, I can
make you a thing that flies. Should I? All right,

03:11:31.939 --> 03:11:38.653
I make him a giant eagle using Polymorph. I can't
do it to me, though, so you're on your own.

03:11:38.653 --> 03:11:39.866
LAURA: Well you can hop on his back.

03:11:39.866 --> 03:11:41.294
SAM: Oh yeah, good call!

03:11:41.294 --> 03:11:43.026
TRAVIS: I'm a big-ass eagle.

03:11:43.026 --> 03:11:50.228
MATT: Second time. Now the wings flare out, and
you remember, oh, flying! I'm smarter! Your

03:11:50.228 --> 03:11:55.876
Flowers for Algernon moment comes in the form of a
feathered bird.

03:11:55.876 --> 03:11:58.164
LIAM: a^2 + b^2 = c^2.

03:11:58.164 --> 03:11:59.948
TRAVIS: No it doesn't.

03:11:59.948 --> 03:12:04.818
MATT: Scanlan, you have to rush to get there
because he's almost completely taken aback by the

03:12:04.818 --> 03:12:11.839
moment and goes to fly. You catch him, barely, as
he leaps off the side of the ship. You guys head

03:12:11.839 --> 03:12:12.996
off toward the--

03:12:12.996 --> 03:12:14.223
TRAVIS: In a wide arc.

03:12:14.223 --> 03:12:19.457
TALIESIN: I tell the captain, no matter what
happens, use your judgment with any man or sailor

03:12:19.457 --> 03:12:24.074
who wishes to parlay and come aboard, but if any
woman attempts to come on board you do not

03:12:24.074 --> 03:12:26.669
recognize as one of us, kill her. Kill her
immediately.

03:12:26.669 --> 03:12:29.650
TRAVIS: What if she's looking like nothing but
a--

03:12:29.650 --> 03:12:32.665
LAURA: Anybody that comes on board, lock them up.
Immediately.

03:12:32.665 --> 03:12:34.042
TALIESIN: At the very least.

03:12:34.042 --> 03:12:35.791
SAM: And kill them.

03:12:35.791 --> 03:12:37.521
TALIESIN: Check for a fake arm, and remove it.

03:12:37.521 --> 03:12:38.816
MATT: "Loud and clear."

03:12:38.816 --> 03:12:43.416
LAURA: I tell Trinket to hop in the necklace
because we're going to be traveling very quickly, dear.

03:12:43.416 --> 03:12:45.199
MATT: Into the necklace.

03:12:45.199 --> 03:12:52.151
TALIESIN: I'm trying to use the scope on my big,
on Bad News to see if anything interesting is

03:12:52.151 --> 03:12:55.658
happening on the deck. Can I see the person who
was firing the flares?

03:12:55.658 --> 03:12:59.718
MATT: The person that's now fired three flares is
now running below the deck.

03:12:59.718 --> 03:13:03.696
TALIESIN: All right. They're all below the deck?

03:13:03.696 --> 03:13:06.689
MATT: Seemingly everybody is below the deck right
now, yes.

03:13:06.689 --> 03:13:10.089
TALIESIN: It's a trap. Let's move away from the
ship. Move toward the beach.

03:13:10.089 --> 03:13:12.697
SAM: But we've got to sink the ship.

03:13:12.697 --> 03:13:14.765
TALIESIN: We're going to sink this ship from a
distance.

03:13:14.765 --> 03:13:17.074
LAURA: She's still scrying. We can, they might be
by the ship.

03:13:17.074 --> 03:13:18.571
TALIESIN: I tell them to turn. Turn now!

03:13:18.571 --> 03:13:20.522
MATT: "Aye, aye!"

03:13:20.522 --> 03:13:23.699
LAURA: I shoot the arrow and try to get to the
boat. The oracle arrow.

03:13:23.699 --> 03:13:29.051
MATT: The ship suddenly begins to list very
heavily to the left side. All the hands grab hold

03:13:29.051 --> 03:13:34.094
who are currently stationed at the various
elements. You can see things on the deck, ropes

03:13:34.094 --> 03:13:38.905
and various odds and ends, pieces of metal, coins,
all begin drifting to one side, some tumbling over

